- id: COG-054
  domain: COG
  title: "MISSION: pick a real user-facing problem and ship a feature that solves it"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today the fleet ships coordination-layer fixes — necessary plumbing but not
    the destination. Per project_offline_local_llm_mission.md the mission is
    offline solo devs on local LLMs. Need to pick a concrete user-facing problem
    and ship a feature that moves the mission, not the meta.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Operator picks ONE of three concrete options below and the chosen sub-feature ships as a single atomic PR (no bundle)
    - "Option A — Discord bot ergonomics: identify the operator's top-3 friction points in the current Discord workflow (file a feedback gap or read recent ambient kind=operator_friction events), ship fixes for at least 2"
    - "Option B — chump --briefing pretty output: current briefing dumps raw markdown. Ship terminal-formatted output with color, sections, and a single 'most-important-thing' top-line. Verified by operator on 3 different gaps"
    - "Option C — chump session-track dashboard URL: session-track currently dumps stdout. Ship a static-HTML dashboard at .chump/session-dashboard.html that lists active sessions, recent commits, current pickable queue. Linked from chump --briefing output"
    - "Whichever option ships: includes a brief 'why this moves the mission' note in the PR body (offline-solo-dev-on-local-LLM connection)"
    - "Does NOT count toward AC: another coord-tax fix, another META gap, another reaper hardening — those are plumbing"
    - "Closes when: (a) the chosen sub-PR merges and (b) operator confirms the feature actually changed their workflow"
  closed_pr: 1576

