- id: CREDIBLE-051
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: fail-closed when gh unavailable + fixture-aware state.db lookup in test-gap-closure-consistency.sh"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Two bugs in scripts/ci/test-gap-closure-consistency.sh surfaced by the
    CREDIBLE-050 force-fire harness:
    
    BUG 1 — Gate passes-by-default on gh API failure:
      Line ~108: 'merged_at=$(gh pr view ... || echo ERROR)'
      Line ~108: '[[ "$merged_at" == "ERROR" ]] && { warn ...; continue; }'
    
      When gh is rate-limited, network-partitioned, or the PR number does
      not exist, the per-gap iteration warns and continues. After 30+ skips
      the gate emits "all done gaps verified" and exits 0. The premature-
      closure gate is therefore silenced any time GitHub is degraded — the
      exact moment we most need it.
    
    BUG 2 — State.db resolution ignores per-invocation fixture:
      Line ~56-62: Resolves DB via 'git rev-parse --git-common-dir', which
      points back at the parent repo when run from a linked worktree or test
      fixture. CREDIBLE-050 fixture creates $tmp/.chump/state.db with a
      ghost closed_pr; the gate ignores it and reads the real repo's
      state.db instead.
    
      Should honor an explicit override (CHUMP_STATE_DB env or --db arg)
      and default to $PWD/.chump/state.db when present, falling back to
      git-common-dir only when --use-main flag given.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - test-gap-closure-consistency.sh exits non-zero (drift) when gh pr view returns ERROR for any gap (not skip+continue)
    - CHUMP_PREMATURE_CLOSURE_ALLOW_GH_FAIL=1 escape hatch documented in env-vars-internal.txt for legitimate offline use
    - DB resolution honors CHUMP_STATE_DB env first, then $PWD/.chump/state.db, falling back to git-common-dir only with --use-main
    - CREDIBLE-050 force-fire fixture for CREDIBLE-028 passes (gate fires on ghost closed_pr) without needing real gh
    - Shell test in scripts/ci/ asserts both behaviors (fail-closed on gh-fail; honors local state.db)
  notes: |
    Surfaced by CREDIBLE-050 (#1523). Currently 4/5 gates pass force-fire;
    only CREDIBLE-028 fails because of these two issues. Fixing this lets
    CREDIBLE-028 graduate to passing fixture and CREDIBLE-042/043 to
    promote gates to REQUIRED status.
  source_doc: scripts/ci/test-gap-closure-consistency.sh
  closed_pr: 1686
  outcome_id: CREDIBLE-000

