- id: CREDIBLE-076
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: design re-enabled 'test' required check that's reliable under parallel CI load + binary cache lag (post-2026-05-25 wedge resolution)
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "[\"Background — 2026-05-25 the entire fleet wedged for ~4 hours because the `test` required check (aggregator over fast-checks shard) failed on every PR. Root causes uncovered during operator-driven rescue: (a) runner-side chump binary 10-days stale → tests greping subcommand output fail, (b) GIT_DIR env-leak from Actions runner-listener → pre-push hook Guard 3 misfires (INFRA-1950 partially landed), (c) sqlite r2d2 lock contention under parallel CI load (filed INFRA-1959), (d) gh pr update-branch false-positive conflicts (filed INFRA-1958), (e) self-hosted runner deps preflight checks plist PATH which races binary refreshes. Resolution required emptying ALL required status checks + admin-merging 29 PRs.\", \"Design goal — re-add `test` (or a more reliable aggregator) to required branch protection AND ruleset such that: any PR that passes locally with `chump preflight` passes in CI; any flake clears on a single rerun; no env-drift between runner setup and PR-time causes wedge.\", \"Concrete deliverables: (1) docs/process/CI_REQUIRED_CHECKS_DESIGN.md authored covering — what *should* be required, what *should not*, the capability-guard pattern for binary-touching tests, the env-isolation pattern for state-mutating tests, the parallel-safe sqlite pattern. (2) scripts/ci/test-required-checks-self-audit.sh that asserts every test in the fast-checks shard has either (a) a capability guard for runner-side chump binary OR (b) doesn't touch the binary. (3) launchd plist refresh script scripts/setup/refresh-runner-binary.sh that rebuilds chump + updates /opt/homebrew/bin/chump on a cron (every 30min) so runner-side binary stays current.\", \"Verification — run 10 parallel CI workflows against a single fresh PR; all 10 must pass test+audit+ACP within 15 minutes with zero flake-reruns. Then re-add `test` to required branch protection + ruleset. Then verify a fresh PR auto-merges through the protected gates.\", \"Pairs with — INFRA-1958 (pr-auto-rebase fallback, landed), INFRA-1959 (sqlite lock contention), INFRA-1937 (route fast-checks to self-hosted), INFRA-1556 (runner deps preflight). All four are subordinate to this design.\", \"Closed-by-when — design doc reviewed by operator + 1 fresh PR successfully landed through re-protected gates without admin merge\"]"
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  outcome_id: CREDIBLE-000

