  description: |
    Operator framing 2026-06-05 22:55Z: 'We're getting fucked by ourselves... harden up the procedures.' The reality-check doctrine already exists (CLAUDE.md §reality-check-before-alarm-class-action, CREDIBLE-090). The compliance doesn't. This umbrella adds 3 ENFORCED gates instead of more words. Pairs with CREDIBLE-105 (durable-fix-doctrine doc, sibling in flight). PROOF the gates would work: every diagnosis-laziness failure I committed today (5+ instances catalogued in /tmp/diagnose-before-file-proposal.md) maps to exactly one gate. SUB-GAPS: (1) Gate 1 'chump gap reserve --priority P0/P1 RESILIENT/MISSION/CREDIBLE requires --evidence flag' (Rust, ~80 LOC, audit-priorities flags empty-evidence gaps); (2) Gate 2 'halt-class emitters must source scripts/lib/halt-class-emit.sh wrapper that calls reality-check.sh first' (bash, ~50 LOC + retrofit pass); (3) Gate 3 'docs/observability/HALT_CLASS_PREDICATES.yaml manifest + scripts/ci/test-halt-class-predicates.sh' (yaml + bash test, ~100 LOC). Each gate has an explicit BYPASS for legitimate cases (CHUMP_GAP_RESERVE_NO_EVIDENCE=1 + trailer, CHUMP_HALT_CLASS_SKIP=1 + trailer, manifest-allowlist entry). Empirical case study: RESILIENT-115 #3089 documents one full diagnose-laziness reversal — my first theory (Keychain rename) was wrong; live-test caught it. That's the discipline these gates would have caught up-front.
