- id: CREDIBLE-122
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: deliberator can't tally real votes — consensus_result structurally impossible (0 ever); fix tally seam + outcome-based health check + real e2e test"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    VERIFIED 2026-06-07: the deliberator daemon (only emitter of consensus_result) cannot tally real votes, so consensus_result has been 0 across the entire fleet history despite 48 A2A gaps marked done. Proven: 3 distinct reasoning agents voted +1 on a real proposal; 'chump consensus-tally --corr-id X' correctly returned yes=3 verdict=PASSED, but 'deliberator-loop.sh tick' returned yes=0 NO_QUORUM on the SAME votes. Triple-broken seam: (1) the gate 'chump consensus-tally --help | grep -q corr-id' NEVER matches (no help text; output says corr_id not corr-id) so the primary path is skipped; (2) even if it ran, consensus-tally outputs TEXT but the caller parses it as JSON via _jq_field → 0; (3) the bash fallback scans feedback.jsonl for kind=vote, but 'chump vote' writes kind=preference there (kind=vote only goes to ambient) → 0. The existing test-deliberator-tick-emits.sh passes because it hand-writes kind=vote events the real chump-vote path never produces — green test, broken production. Fix proven locally (parse consensus-tally text → consensus_result 0→1).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - deliberator-loop.sh _tally_corr_id uses chump consensus-tally directly (drop the broken --help gate) and PARSES its text output (yes/no/abstain/total/verdict); the bash fallback reads kind=vote from ambient.jsonl (where chump vote writes it), not kind=vote from feedback.jsonl
    - "end-to-end: 3 distinct sessions run `chump vote <corr> +1` then the production deliberator tick emits kind=consensus_result verdict=PASSED (consensus_result count 0→1) — proven against real logs, not a hand-written-kind=vote sandbox"
    - "fleet-doctor a2a-consensus check is OUTCOME-based: RED when an open proposal older than the grace window has no consensus_result (replaces the signal-based check that only verified the flag was set); passes when proposals get verdicts; skips cleanly when no proposals exist"
    - new CI test runs the REAL path (chump vote x3 distinct sessions -> deliberator tick -> assert consensus_result emitted) so this regression cannot recur silently
  closed_pr: 3099

- id: CREDIBLE-123
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: chump roadmap-status hallucinates starved outcomes — reports Week 1 as 0-shipped-6-open when ROADMAP.md says ✅ shipped with PR numbers (#1204 #1216 #1385 #1384 #1355 #1373 #1276)"
