    - "Diagnose: is roadmap-status reading docs/ROADMAP.md text and missing the ✅ markers? Reading a stale snapshot? Reading state.db with a different ID schema (UUID legacy vs INFRA-NNN)? Identify the source-of-truth mismatch"
    - "Fix: roadmap-status MUST cross-check each listed gap_id against (a) state.db status (b) ROADMAP.md ✅/PR-number markers (c) git log for matching shipped commit. A gap is 'open' only when state.db says status='open' AND it's not marked ✅ in ROADMAP.md AND no merged PR claims to close it"
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-roadmap-status-truth.sh: fixture state.db + ROADMAP.md where all listed gaps are shipped; assert roadmap-status reports 'starved_outcomes=' (empty) not phantom starvation"
    - "Doctrine cross-ref: CREDIBLE-105 case study — a tool that LOOKS like it's working (reports plausible drift numbers) while reading the wrong source-of-truth is the canonical band-aid in the analytics layer. Same family as fleet-brief banner ignoring slo-check (CREDIBLE-120) and Alerts(30m) drift (CREDIBLE-121)"

- id: CREDIBLE-124
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: autonomy_level file mutations are SILENT — no audit event, no reason, no actor — operator (or sibling) flipped to 0 at 15:32Z with no paper trail (8.5h of fleet-off without diagnosis surface)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Reproducer: ~/.chump/autonomy_level was mutated from prior value to '0' on Jun 7 15:32:11. grep autonomy .chump-locks/ambient.jsonl returns 0 events. git log shows nothing in the 14:00–16:00 window. The operator (or a daemon) made an irreversible-ish operator decision with zero audit trail"
    - "Doctrine cross-ref: CREDIBLE-105 meta-clause — every state change that affects fleet behavior must emit an audit event (kind=autonomy_set with reason + actor + prior_level + new_level + ts). A silent flip is the same lie family as fleet-brief saying healthy while ✗ broken"
    - "Fix: wrap autonomy_level mutations in a single chump fleet level <N> --reason <text> command. The command MUST emit kind=autonomy_set to ambient + refuse without --reason flag (operator can pass --reason 'silent' if they want, but the explicit-empty IS the audit signal)"
    - "Fix: scripts/dispatch/fleet-brief.sh integrates the autonomy state — if autonomy_level == 0, banner reads '⚠ FLEET STOPPED (autonomy=0 set <duration> ago, reason=<from-last-audit-event>)' NOT '✓ healthy'. Same fix shape as CREDIBLE-120 (brief↔slo)"
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-autonomy-audit.sh: flip autonomy via the wrapper, assert ambient gets kind=autonomy_set within 1s; flip directly via echo, assert pre-commit / file-watcher catches and emits kind=autonomy_silent_mutation (the safety-net for backwards-compat writes)"
    - "Add a backfill: on every chump invocation that READS autonomy_level, if there's been no audit event for the current value, emit kind=autonomy_unaudited as a one-time signal so the operator sees the silent-state-of-record in their next session-start brief"
  notes: |
    [2026-06-08T00:57:45Z] AC EXTENSION 2026-06-08: original AC covered the AUDIT GATE (kind=autonomy_set on flips). Add the AUTOPILOT HALF per operator framing 2026-06-08 ('this system should be self-healing and self-improving'): (7) A launchd daemon dev.chump.autonomy-autoheal watches AUTONOMY_LEVEL + ambient for kind=autonomy_set. On flip to 0 WITHOUT a recent legitimate audit event, auto-re-enables to last-known-good level, emits kind=autonomy_autohealed with the diagnosis. (8) On 3+ silent-flip recurrences within 24h, auto-files a follow-up gap (kind=autonomy_silent_flipper_unknown) so the writer gets found by the next picker, not the operator. (9) Escalates to operator ONLY when: auto-heal failed N=3 times OR the writer process can't be identified after N attempts. Default = fleet figures it out. Cross-ref: this is the autopilot pattern for the page-budget-class (see new META gap on operator-notification budget — humans paged only on novel/irreversible/authority decisions).

- id: CREDIBLE-125
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: verify-merge Gate-1 CI-delta — judge a PR on its CI delta (pre-existing red is advisory, NEW red blocks) so the autonomous loop can fix broken-CI repos as product work instead of deadlocking on their pre-existing red"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Gate 1 in src/external_verify_merge.rs fetches terminal check-runs for BOTH base SHA and head SHA; FAILURE present on head but SUCCESS-or-absent on base → HELD(ci_regression) naming the check; FAILURE on both → logged as pre-existing-red (non-blocking); SUCCESS on head → pass.
    - Gate 1 PASSES when there are zero newly-introduced failures; it does NOT pass when checks that were green on base are now red on head (regression still blocks).
    - "A new helper fetch_check_runs_for_sha(repo, sha, gh_bin) reuses the existing gh/cache mechanism; it accepts an arbitrary SHA (not just the PR HEAD) and returns Vec<serde_json::Value>."
    - "Four new serial_test::serial tests cover: (a) head greens one check while others are red on BOTH base+head → PASS; (b) check SUCCESS on base but FAILURE on head → HELD(ci_regression); (c) all-green base+head → PASS unchanged; (d) all-head-checks-red but all also red on base → PASS (pre-existing). All existing verify_merge and improve tests remain green."

- id: CREDIBLE-126
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: operator-notification budget — every detector/monitor that surfaces to a human MUST first try self-heal, recurrence-track, and gap-file; human pages reserved for novel/irreversible/authority-only"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Operating principle (operator framing 2026-06-08): 'this system should be self-healing and self-improving' — a human is paged ONLY when (a) novel class never seen, (b) irreversible decision exceeding operator authority, (c) auto-heal attempted N=3 times and failed. Everything else: fleet detects, diagnoses, heals, files-on-recurrence — without paging"
    - "Audit the existing alert surfaces (operator_recall, slo_breach, fleet_paused_*, blame_bot, fresh_eyes_disagreement, every kind ending in _alert/_breach/_critical) and classify each as: (i) page-worthy per the above criteria, (ii) self-heal candidate (build the autopilot), (iii) self-improve candidate (file recurrence-gap automatically), (iv) noise (remove the emitter). The current 384 operator-recalls / 7d SLO breach proves the audit is overdue"
    - "Add docs/process/OPERATOR_PAGE_BUDGET.md codifying: every new monitor/detector MUST include (a) a self-heal attempt OR a documented why-not, (b) a recurrence-track + auto-file path, (c) escalation criteria (when does this REALLY need the operator), (d) a budget — max N pages per kind per week"
    - "Pre-commit gate: any new ambient emit of kind matching */alert|breach|critical/ MUST point at an OPERATOR_PAGE_BUDGET entry OR carry a Page-Budget-Bypass: <reason> trailer (audit signal mirrors INFRA-2429 no-new-bypass-env-vars pattern). Prevents the recall storm from re-accumulating"
    - "Backfill: existing 384 operator-recall events in last 7d are sampled (random 20) and triaged into the 4 buckets above; results inform which auto-healers to build first. Highest-volume kind = first autopilot built"
    - "Doctrine cross-ref: this is the alerting-class application of CREDIBLE-105 (durable-fix). A noisy detector that pages the operator instead of self-healing IS a band-aid in the observability layer — it 'looks fixed' (someone got notified) but the cause repeats and the operator burns attention. Sibling-class to CREDIBLE-106 (diagnose-before-file gates), CREDIBLE-114 (A2A enforcement / drain), and CREDIBLE-124 (autonomy_set audit + autopilot)"
    - "Concrete first autopiloter to build (proof point): dev.chump.autonomy-autoheal per CREDIBLE-124 AC #7. Validates the pattern end-to-end before applying to the rest"

- id: CREDIBLE-127
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: hermetic auth tests — with_env must redirect CHUMP_HOME, not read operator real ~/.chump/config.toml"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Root cause: src/auth.rs test helper with_env() CLEARS CHUMP_HOME instead of redirecting it. chump_config_path() (auth.rs:510) then falls back to $HOME/.chump/config.toml, which holds LIVE creds on every operator/fleet machine (control.sh refreshes every 5 min). So the no-creds assertions (neither_present_resolves_none, api_key_only_resolves_api_key_mode asserting !has_oauth, fleet_doctor_warns_when_no_creds) read the operators real token and panic. Clean in CI (no ~/.chump) so it false-passes there; RED on every operator-machine pre-push (cargo test --bin chump) so it blocks interactive ship without a bypass. Fix: with_env redirects CHUMP_HOME to a throwaway temp dir (unless the test sets CHUMP_HOME via vars, which wins), making config.toml/token-file resolution hermetic for the whole auth::tests module.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - with_env() in src/auth.rs redirects CHUMP_HOME to a unique throwaway temp dir; a test needing a specific CHUMP_HOME passes it via vars and that wins
    - "cargo test --bin chump auth::tests is green on a machine WITH populated env creds AND a real populated ~/.chump/config.toml (the operator-machine condition that currently fails)"
    - no auth test resolves credentials from the operators real $HOME/.chump
    - fix lives in the shared with_env helper so every auth test inherits hermeticity (regression guard)

- id: CREDIBLE-128
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: env-mutating Rust tests must be sandboxed + serialized for reliable operator-machine pre-push"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Re-homes work first attempted under CREDIBLE-127 (that id collided with a gap closed on origin/main). Two pre-existing test-infra bugs make operator-machine cargo test --bin chump (the pre-push gate) fail while CI clean env passes: (1) auth::tests with_env() CLEARED CHUMP_HOME so chump_config_path() read the operators real ~/.chump/config.toml (live creds) and the no-creds assertions panicked — fix: redirect CHUMP_HOME to a throwaway temp dir; (2) auth + improve env-mutating tests shared no lock, so concurrent std::env::set_var (UB in Rust 2024) crashed the test binary unparseably and defeated flake-rerun — fix: #[serial_test::serial] on all env-mutating auth + improve tests, unifying with the existing external_verify_merge convention.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - with_env() redirects CHUMP_HOME to a unique throwaway temp dir (a test that sets CHUMP_HOME via vars wins)
    - "all env-mutating auth + improve tests are #[serial_test::serial] so concurrent set_var cannot occur"
    - cargo test --bin chump is green on an operator machine (populated env creds + real ~/.chump/config.toml) across repeated runs
    - no auth/improve test reads the operators real $HOME/.chump

- id: CREDIBLE-129
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: fleet-brief ship-count intermittently returns 0 while fleet is actively shipping — false fleet-dead signal at SessionStart
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Observed 2026-06-08: fleet-brief banner (SessionStart hook) showed 'Ships: 0 (24h) | last 1h: 0' + '✓ fleet looks healthy', but ground truth at the same moment was: git log origin/main = 2 merges last 1h / 7 last 6h; 24 worker.sh procs, 42 claude -p procs, 13 bot-merge procs in-flight, 2 active leases. ~30 min earlier the SAME script reported 'Ships: 43 | last 1h: 9' (correct). The ship-count intermittently collapses to 0 — likely a transient failure inside fleet-brief.sh (git fetch timeout / swallowed subshell error -> empty -> 0). This is the ROOT of the #1 operator false-positive ('fleet is dead', mis-called 4x per CLAUDE.md): the brief is the first thing every SessionStart shows, so a false 0 makes every fresh agent misdiagnose fleet-death. Sibling of CREDIBLE-086 (merge-queue lie) + META-287 fresh-eyes comparator_6 (brief-says-healthy-but-not-shipping).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. fleet-brief ship-count NEVER silently returns 0 on a transient error — it retries, reports the real count, or prints an explicit 'ship-count unavailable (<reason>)' instead of a misleading 0. 2. Root-cause the intermittent-0 (candidate: git fetch failure / swallowed subshell error inside the script). 3. The 'looks healthy' verdict incorporates ship-rate — a 0-ship state with live workers is NOT 'healthy', it is 'measurement failed / investigate'. 4. Regression test: synthetic scenario where the count query fails -> brief shows 'unavailable', not '0 + healthy'."

- id: CREDIBLE-130
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: run-fleet INFRA-621 probe mislabels 'credit balance too low' as 'ANTHROPIC_API_KEY authentication failed' — manufactures auth-dead false positives
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    2026-06-08: fleet down because the Anthropic API account hit 'Credit balance is too low' (key VALID, authenticates fine, len 108; CHUMP_AUTH_MODE=api-key forces the empty account). But run-fleet.sh INFRA-621 probe reports 'ERROR: auth probe failed / ANTHROPIC_API_KEY authentication failed' — a BILLING failure mislabeled as an AUTH failure. This is the #1 false-positive class (auth-dead, mis-called 4x): the mislabel sent diagnosis through auth/flag/lease theories before a direct probe revealed the real cause (credit). Fix: classify the failure.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. INFRA-621 probe parses the error and reports the ACTUAL class (auth-invalid vs credit-exhausted vs rate-limit vs network), not a blanket 'authentication failed'. 2. On credit-exhaustion: actionable message (top up / switch CHUMP_AUTH_MODE=oauth). 3. Emits a distinct ambient kind (e.g. fleet_credit_exhausted) so operator-recall routes it correctly."

- id: CREDIBLE-131
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: mass-deletion guard underscore/space token mismatch false-positives cold-water RED_LETTER PRs"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    check-mass-deletion.sh Rule B builds file token red_letter (underscore) from docs/audits/RED_LETTER.md, but in CI gh pr view returns empty on detached-HEAD checkout so it falls back to commit messages which say 'Red Letter' (space); grep -F red_letter cannot match -> false-positive blocks EVERY weekly cold-water RED_LETTER PR (live: #3103 net -867). Fix: normalize _ - . to space on both sides of the match in lines ~134-142. Distinct from META-272 (detached-HEAD push-path). Test sibling: scripts/ci/test-mass-deletion-guard.sh.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Rule B in check-mass-deletion.sh normalizes separators (_ - . treated as equivalent to space) on both the file token and PR context before matching, so a >100-line net deletion from docs/audits/RED_LETTER.md is NOT flagged when PR title/commit says 'Red Letter'.
