    - All pre-existing test-mass-deletion-guard.sh cases still pass.
    - "No new false-negative: a genuine unrelated mass deletion from a file not mentioned in any separator-variant still fails the guard."

- id: CREDIBLE-132
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: CI (Linux) false-greens macOS-incompatible Bash-4 constructs (declare -A/-n, mapfile) — no lint catches scripts that break on the Bash-3.2 fleet"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    CI runs on Linux (Bash 5) but the fleet runs on macOS (Bash 3.2 /bin/bash). Scripts using Bash-4-only constructs PASS CI yet FAIL on the fleet at runtime. Live example: scripts/ops/pillar-balance-check.sh (INFRA-902 / closed PR #3117) used 'declare -A' at line 38 → 'declare: -A: invalid option' on macOS → 'chump gap audit-priorities' (Command::new bash) would error on the target platform, but CI was green. No lint catches this class. Risk surface: any scripts/**/*.sh invoked by Rust (Command::new bash), worker.sh, bot-merge.sh, or a launchd plist.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Audit scripts/**/*.sh for Bash-4-only constructs (declare -A, declare -n, mapfile, readarray, parameter-case ${v^^}/${v,,}, assoc-array indexing) and enumerate current usages, flagging which run on a fleet hot-path (Rust Command::new bash / worker.sh / bot-merge.sh / launchd plist)."
    - Add a CI lint + mirror it in 'chump preflight' (INFRA-1867 parity) that flags NEW Bash-4-only constructs in scripts/, with a documented bypass trailer for scripts that legitimately need Bash 4+ AND self-guard with a loud version check.
    - "Hot-path scripts must be Bash-3.2 clean OR self-guard: e.g. 'if ((BASH_VERSINFO[0]<4)); then echo needs-bash4 >&2; exit 3; fi' so failure is loud not silent."
    - "Smoke test: lint flags a known-bad fixture (script with 'declare -A') and passes a clean one."

