    - "cargo test --bin chump auth::tests is 0-failed regardless of ~/.chump contents."

- id: CREDIBLE-134
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: chump unknown-subcommand routes to brain LLM and exits 0 (scripting footgun + hallucinated output); must print usage + exit non-zero"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump <unknown-subcommand> (e.g. chump zzznotacommand) prints a usage/error message listing valid subcommands and exits NON-ZERO
    - the brain/LLM natural-language fallback is gated behind an explicit opt-in (dedicated subcommand like chump ask, or a flag/config) so a bare typo'd token never silently invokes the LLM
    - "CI smoke test asserts: chump <bogus-token> exits non-zero AND stdout does not contain 'Response from Agent'"
    - all real subcommands and their --help paths continue to work unchanged
  closed_pr: 3138
  evidence: |
    COMMAND: chump zzznotacommand (also: chump proposals list). OUTPUT: prints 'chump config: enabled=[discord,...,brain]' then 'Response from Agent: ...It seems like you've entered something that doesn't appear to be a command... If you're feeling sleepy (given the zzz)...' — a conversational LLM hallucination — and exits 0. THEORY: unrecognized subcommands fall through to the brain/discord agent dispatch instead of the clap unknown-subcommand error path, and the agent path returns exit 0. ALT: brain-fallback for natural-language queries may be intentional, but it must NOT swallow obviously-typo'd subcommand tokens and must NEVER exit 0 on unrecognized CLI input — a fleet script with a typo'd chump subcommand currently 'succeeds' silently.

- id: CREDIBLE-135
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: test-pwa-prefs failing on main — ambient-viewer.js never integrated chumpPrefs (3 assert) + index.html loads prefs.js AFTER app.js (script-order)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
