- id: CREDIBLE-136
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: auth-status.sh validity probe FALSE-NEGATIVE — reports BROKEN + fires farmer_auth_dead/operator_recall AUTH_DEAD while real claude -p with fleet creds succeeds"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - auth-status.sh does NOT serve a cached BROKEN verdict to halt-class consumers (farmer/operator-recall) without a fresh re-probe — a transient failure must not be cached + replayed as AUTH_DEAD while a fresh probe + real claude -p succeed
    - "the farmer re-probes (or auth-status re-probes) before emitting farmer_auth_dead / operator_recall AUTH_DEAD, per CREDIBLE-090 (signal≠outcome: don't fire halt-class on one cached/transient failure)"
    - "repro: a 13:49Z transient failure was cached + replayed as BROKEN for the TTL window while ANTHROPIC_API_KEY/oauth claude -p both returned OK and the forced --probe returned 'AUTH ✓ OK'"
    - "optional: cap the BROKEN-verdict cache TTL well below the OK-verdict TTL, or invalidate the cache on a subsequent OK"
  notes: |
    Refined 2026-06-21: forced --probe returns AUTH ✓ OK (oauth validated). Root cause = stale cache: a transient claude -p failure cached as BROKEN + served without re-probe, firing farmer_auth_dead + operator_recall AUTH_DEAD spuriously. Non-blocking (self-clears next fresh probe) but pages operator + risks farmer tearing down workers during the stale window. Fix is durable: re-verify before halt-class action.
  evidence: |
    COMMAND: bash scripts/coord/auth-status.sh (farmer ran it 13:49Z) → 'AUTH ✗ BROKEN — no credentials found' + emitted farmer_auth_dead{reason:validity_probe_broken,mode:oauth} + operator_recall{reason:AUTH_DEAD}. CONTRAST: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=$(launchctl getenv ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) claude -p 'reply FLEET_AUTH_OK' → returns FLEET_AUTH_OK; oauth-only path also OK; bogus key → 'Invalid API key' (rejected) proving the working test is NOT my-login-contaminated. OUTPUT: probe says dead, real claude -p says alive — they disagree; auth genuinely WORKS. THEORY: probe caches a transient/stale failure (saw '(cached)') OR its claude -p PONG invocation/match differs from a working call OR the api-key REST sub-probe fails (depleted key) and the oauth fallback in the probe misjudges. ALT: maybe my test inherited ~/.claude config — REFUTED by the bogus-key rejection. IMPACT: the #1 false-positive class (CLAUDE.md, mis-called 4x); spuriously pages operator_recall and would make the farmer tear down workers the moment the fleet is spun up — blocks trusting the fleet's own go/no-go signal.

- id: CREDIBLE-137
  domain: CREDIBLE
  title: "CREDIBLE: fleet workers use DEPLETED ANTHROPIC_API_KEY over valid subscription OAuth — 'Credit balance is too low' (api 400) → rc=1 → circuit-break → fleet ships nothing"
  status: open
  priority: P0
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - worker.sh refresh_oauth_token() unsets ANTHROPIC_API_KEY when a valid OAuth token (file or env) is present, before each claude -p spawn, so claude uses the subscription instead of a key it prefers-but-may-be-depleted
    - with a present-but-depleted api-key + valid oauth token, a worker's claude -p uses oauth — no 'Credit balance is too low' (api 400) → no rc=1 → no circuit-break
    - "a 2-worker fleet on the subscription completes a real gap cycle (cycle log is_error:false) instead of failing rc=1 + tripping worker_circuit_open"
    - "fallback preserved: when no oauth token is available, the worker still falls back to ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (unset only happens when oauth IS present)"
  evidence: |
    COMMAND: FLEET_SIZE=2 run-fleet.sh → worker cycle log /tmp/chump-fleet-*/agent-1-cycle3-INFRA-1612.log. OUTPUT: {"type":"result","is_error":true,"api_error_status":400,"result":"Credit balance is too low"} — claude -p authenticated fine but used the metered API key (depleted) not the flat-rate subscription; 3 consecutive rc=1 → worker_circuit_open(pause=300s) → worker_exit. THEORY: claude -p PREFERS ANTHROPIC_API_KEY when both it and CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN are set (CLAUDE.md precedence trap). run-fleet.sh unsets the key (line 207) but only in ITS shell — the tmux worker panes inherit the depleted key from the launchd/auth-floor-setenv env, and worker.sh refresh_oauth_token() set CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN but did NOT unset ANTHROPIC_API_KEY before each claude -p spawn. ALT: not auth-dead (oauth-only claude -p returns OK; bogus key rejected) and not a gap-specific failure (every gap fails identically). FIX: worker.sh unsets ANTHROPIC_API_KEY when a valid oauth token is present (operator pays subscription, NOT metered API — explicit operator directive 2026-06-21). IMPACT: this is THE blocker preventing any autonomous fleet shipping; the conductor/mission cannot work until workers transact on the subscription.

