- id: EFFECTIVE-017
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: WorkBackend trait + plug-in worker variants — abstract `claude -p` so chump can dispatch opencode, aider, local-Ollama-loop workers"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    src/dispatch.rs currently hard-codes `Command::new("claude")` as the
    worker subprocess (19 claude refs vs 1 other-provider ref). A solo dev
    on Llama-only Ollama cannot run chump's fleet dispatcher today —
    they're stuck before the first gap claim.
    
    The chump-first doctrine (docs/process/CHUMP_FIRST_DOCTRINE.md, this
    PR) says: chump is a universal coordination platform; Claude is one
    backend among many. This gap operationalizes that for the worker layer.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "src/dispatch.rs defines `trait WorkBackend { fn spawn(&self, prompt: &str, opts: &SpawnOpts) -> Result<Child>; fn name(&self) -> &str; }`"
    - "Implementations shipped: ClaudeBackend (current default, no behavior change), OpencodeBackend (`opencode -p <prompt>`), AiderBackend (`aider --message <prompt>`), OllamaLoopBackend (HTTP loop against local Ollama)"
    - WorkBackend selection driven by CHUMP_WORK_BACKEND env var (claude|opencode|aider|ollama) with default=claude for backward compat
    - Each backend documents its required env vars + auth path (claude needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY or CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN; opencode reads ~/.opencode/auth; ollama needs OLLAMA_BASE_URL; etc.)
    - spawn_claude_worker() (existing function) wrapped in ClaudeBackend; no behavior change for current users
    - "scripts/ci/test-work-backend-trait.sh: mock-spawn a worker, assert each backend's spawn signature is consistent and returns the same Child shape"
    - scripts/dispatch/run-fleet.sh accepts --backend flag; sets CHUMP_WORK_BACKEND for spawned workers
    - Documented in docs/process/CHUMP_FIRST_DOCTRINE.md + CLAUDE.md (or AGENTS.md per EFFECTIVE-020) as the canonical worker-pluggability story
    - "Test the OllamaLoop variant end-to-end: dispatch a gap whose AC is 'write a hello world function', assert the worker produces a commit with that function from a local Ollama model"
  closed_pr: 1516
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

