- id: EFFECTIVE-021
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: SessionStart auto-digest dispatch/cascade/funnel summaries — delta-only output"
  status: done
  priority: P3
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Backlog-promoted 2026-05-16 — SessionStart hook already prints fleet brief + ambient digest (~30 lines). Adding three more digests (dispatch, cascade, funnel CLIs) at SessionStart risks signal-to-noise collapse.
    - Pattern — DELTA-ONLY output. Each digest writes its last-rendered state to ~/.chump/session-digest-cache/<name>.json. Next SessionStart compares current vs cached; only emit section if delta exceeds threshold (configurable, default 1 new event / 5% rate change).
    - If no delta — OMIT entirely. SessionStart should stay under 40 lines total or operators stop reading.
    - Three digests to wire up — chump dispatch summary, chump cascade summary, chump funnel summary. Each gets a wrapper that does the diff math.
    - SessionStart hook integration — add to scripts/hooks/session-start.sh after fleet brief. Hook output goes to system-reminder; respect 40-line cap by tail-truncating with `(N more, run chump fleet digest --full)`.
    - Smoke test scripts/ci/test-session-start-digest-delta.sh — seed cache, drive 0-delta path (no output) AND positive-delta path (output present), assert behavior.
    - Pair with INFRA-TBD-1547 war-room hook gap — that gap is broader; this is the narrow SessionStart wiring.
    - Telemetry — emit kind=session_start_digest_rendered with fields digests (names array), lines_added.
    - Out of scope — full war-room dashboard (separate gap).
  closed_pr: 1680
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

