- id: EFFECTIVE-037
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: A2A L5 — event-sourcing coordination bus (typed subjects + subscriptions + corr_id sagas)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Tier-1 L5 per docs/design/A2A_MASTER_PLAN_2026-06-03.md — the highest-leverage upgrade: convert ambient.jsonl from write-only telemetry into a typed domain-event log on NATS JetStream with SUBSCRIPTIONS. Builds on INFRA-1118 (delivery, done). Today agents broadcast telemetry into the void; they do not react to each other.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - ambient/mesh events are typed domain events on named NATS subjects (e.g. chump.gap.claimed, chump.test.failed, chump.pr.merged)
    - agents SUBSCRIBE to relevant subjects and react automatically (gap.claimed -> overlap-scan, test.failed -> ci-audit, pr.merged -> ship) instead of polling
    - each event carries a corr_id; a failed step triggers saga compensation (replay compensating events by corr_id)
    - a subscribed reaction is demonstrated firing end-to-end with no polling loop
  notes: |
    [2026-06-08T01:09:35Z] CUTTING-EDGE (research 2026-06): event-sourcing proven (Temporal $5B Feb-2026). ADD: each agent = named CONSUMER GROUP with committed read OFFSET (crashed agent replays from last offset = no msg loss); at-least-once + IDEMPOTENCY KEYS (no double-process on replay); DEAD-LETTER topic after N retries + alert. The bus-consuming deliberator must be a DURABLE consumer + DETERMINISTIC FOLD over the log (not an LLM snapshot — recoverable mid-tally). Refs: arXiv 2602.08009 (RAPS), Temporal.
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

- id: EFFECTIVE-038
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: A2A L2 — task state machine with input_required + auth_required (suspended, not failed)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Tier-1 L2 per docs/design/A2A_MASTER_PLAN_2026-06-03.md (Google A2A 8-state task machine). The two missing states: input_required (agent is 70% done, needs an operator decision, then RESUMES) and auth_required (a credential is missing) — auth_required is EXACTLY the failure mode that silently killed the fleet for 46h (see RESILIENT-054). Today a gap is either running or failed.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - gap gains status=waiting_operator carrying a structured question payload (not a free-text follow-up gap)
    - chump gap respond <ID> --answer JSON RESUMES the suspended gap from where it paused
    - an agent that hits a missing credential enters auth_required and suspends (does not silently die) — ties RESILIENT-054
    - an ambiguous-decision case suspends to waiting_operator instead of guessing-wrong or filing a follow-up gap
  notes: |
    [2026-06-08T01:09:35Z] CUTTING-EDGE (research 2026-06): input_required/auth_required EXACTLY match Google A2A v1.0 task lifecycle — validated. BUT A2A proves they're SIGNALING not ENFORCEMENT: task hangs FOREVER if no agent responds (A2A has no timeout). ADD: SLA on input_required — max_wait_seconds; on elapse auto-transition failed + emit task_stalled (no silent hang). Wire: task→input_required emits a P0 inbox msg to the responder, whose CREDIBLE-114 hook drains it first. Refs: a2a-protocol.org spec, arXiv 2604.02369.
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

- id: EFFECTIVE-039
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: A2A L3a — Contract-Net gap assignment (CFP -> BID -> AWARD, fitness-scored)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Tier-1 L3 per docs/design/A2A_MASTER_PLAN_2026-06-03.md (Contract Net Protocol). Replace first-available pull with a lightweight competitive bid so the fittest worker wins, not the fastest-polling one.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - coordinator announces a pickable gap (CFP with skills + size) on the mesh
    - capable idle workers submit a bid within a 5s TTL; coordinator AWARDs to the highest score = w1*skill_match + w2*(1/load) + w3*class_success_rate
    - on awarded-worker failure the gap is automatically re-announced with no human intervention
    - first-available pull is replaced by the bid cycle for the P0/P1 lane; a test shows a higher-fitness worker winning over a faster one
  notes: |
    [2026-06-08T01:09:35Z] CUTTING-EDGE (research 2026-06): CNP validated (COALESCE arXiv 2506.01900: 20.3% cost cut). ADD: (1) epsilon-greedy exploration at announcer — else all work converges to one bidder (routing monoculture = single-agent fleet); (2) resource-budget contracts per task (max tokens/deadline/rollback — Agent Contracts arXiv 2601.08815, prevents recursive-$47k-bill); (3) no-bid dead-letter + escalation; (4) auction_log to bus for capability-concentration audit. Refs: arXiv 2506.01900, 2601.08815.
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

