- id: EFFECTIVE-088
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE P0: autonomous conductor loop — orchestrator as a daemon (not a human session) that prioritizes/routes/decides/ships, obeying the dial"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xl
  description: |
    The brain that empties the chair. Today orchestrator-opus is a HUMAN-run session (the operator role-plays the conductor). Build it as an autonomous loop (launchd daemon) that does what the human did this session: read the queue, prioritize toward the active Outcome (MISSION-008 FK), route work to agents via typed handoffs/assign, resolve conflicts THROUGH consensus (not by asking the operator), and escalate ONLY on true halt-class. It runs at and obeys the autonomy dial (level 4 = full auto; level<=2 = propose/assist only) and stops instantly on the kill switch. Depends on: the cockpit (must obey dial+kill), consensus firing (RESILIENT-062 routing + RESILIENT-061 deliberator), and the farmer (RESILIENT-068, so the conductor can't be killed by the substrate).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - an orchestrator daemon runs the prioritize->route->decide->ship cycle with NO human session — verified by a window where coordination acts are 100% agent-performed
    - decisions route through consensus (consensus_result drives the choice), not operator-ask
    - it obeys the autonomy dial (level-gated) and halts within one tick on chump fleet stop
    - escalates ONLY on true halt-class (not routine)
    - supervised dry-run shows it prioritizing toward the active Outcome + dispatching >=1 gap end-to-end with no human input
    - "VERIFIED 2026-06-20: consensus deliberator TALLIES correctly but dies at NO_QUORUM — 0 .curator-opus-*.lock voters online. So self-rescue (non-halt-class) must use propose->objection-window->act (veto by -1), not block on a quorum that cannot form until autonomous curator-voters exist (sibling gap)."
  depends_on: [RESILIENT-073]
  closed_pr: 3134
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

- id: EFFECTIVE-089
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: collapse 29-gate pre-commit web to 3 hard gates + warn-the-rest + bypass debt-ceiling (best-in-class QA, kill the ship-tax)
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Pre-commit HARD-blocks reduced to exactly 3, all fast (<2s): cargo fmt --check, cargo check (compile), credential-scan. Today there are 29 numbered blocking gates each with its own bypass var (29 bypasses = each routinely escaped = each suspect)."
    - "Every other pre-commit gate (event-registry, obs-budget, gap-divergence, AC-enforce, hardcoded-date, main-worktree-config, branch-protection-align, preflight-vs-CI-parity, gaps.yaml-discipline, the CREDIBLE-001 shellcheck/clippy smoke, build-check) flips to WARN-default: it prints, never exit-1. CI remains the single enforcer. Principle: a gate that needs a routine bypass is wrong — warn it or delete it."
    - "Bypass debt-ceiling (the addition tax): the no-new-bypass gate goes NET-NEGATIVE — adding any CHUMP_*_(BYPASS|SKIP|IGNORE|CHECK) var requires deleting one. Count must ratchet DOWN from the current 227 (vs the 113 INFRA-2525 cited) → <100 → <10."
    - "CI = single source of merge-truth: the test suite on the PR + merge-queue verification of the actual merge commit; remove the dual ship paths (batched-integrator Mode A vs per-PR Mode B both fail-closed SPOFs). No policy-gate may block a merge that the tests pass."
    - "MEASURED outcome: a clean tested fix commits + pushes + merges with ZERO bypass env vars (today it takes ~7). Each surviving gate must justify: catches a real, recurring, costly failure CI cannot, in <2s, ~0 false-positives — else deleted."
  closed_pr: 3008
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

