- id: EFFECTIVE-097
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: pre-push test-gate sccache probe uses --version (client-only, passes while server dead) → false-fails Rust pushes → forces CHUMP_TEST_GATE=0; heal via idempotent --start-server"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "The INFRA-2184 sccache liveness probe in scripts/git-hooks/pre-push (~line 733-739) replaces the client-only `--version` check with an idempotent server-liveness probe (`--start-server`): when the sccache server is dead, the probe HEALS it so the test gate runs WITH caching, instead of false-failing."
    - Only when the server genuinely cannot start does the probe fall back to disabling the wrapper (CARGO_BUILD_RUSTC_WRAPPER= RUSTC_WRAPPER=) — gate still runs (slow but correct), never a false fail. Echoes a distinguishable message to stderr (healed vs disabled) — no new ambient kind (avoids registry collision with in-flight RESILIENT-059).
    - "Regression test scripts/ci/test-prepush-sccache-probe.sh: stop the server, run the probe logic in isolation, assert it ends with a LIVE server (heal) and exit 0 — proving the --version weakness is gone."
    - Removes the sccache-death class from the CHUMP_TEST_GATE=0 bypass reasons. EFFECTIVE-089 ship-path-unification slice.
  closed_pr: 3010
  outcome_id: EFFECTIVE-000

