- id: EFFECTIVE-218
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: chump-commit.sh cargo-fmt git add -A sweeps untracked files despite explicit argv"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/coord/chump-commit.sh line ~687 — after cargo fmt --all, the script runs git add -A which captures any untracked file in the worktree (e.g. .chump-no-reap marker) and commits it
    - "Fix: replace bare git add -A with git add -- \"${FILES[@]}\" (the same argv used at line 342) so cargo-fmt re-staging stays scoped to user's declared files"
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-chump-commit-argv-scope.sh: create untracked .chump-no-reap; run chump-commit foo.rs -m '...' with cargo fmt touching foo.rs; verify commit contains foo.rs ONLY (not .chump-no-reap)"
    - If cargo fmt touches a file OUTSIDE the declared argv (e.g. an unrelated .rs file in workspace), chump-commit FAILS LOUD with a diagnostic rather than silently re-staging it
    - "Doctrine cross-ref: this gap is a CASE STUDY referenced in docs/process/DURABLE_FIX_DOCTRINE.md (CREDIBLE-105) — the 2026-06-05 RESILIENT-110 ship attempt was forced into a soft-reset cycle by this bug"

- id: EFFECTIVE-219
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: background daemon deletes docs/gaps/<ID>.yaml between chump gap reserve and chump claim — state.db row remains"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Reproducer: chump gap reserve --domain X --title 'foo' → docs/gaps/X-NNN.yaml written → within minutes, file is gone from disk while state.db row remains open"
    - "Identify the deleting daemon — survey candidates: scripts/ops/gap-doctor-safe-sweep.sh, scripts/ops/orphan-yaml-prune.sh, scripts/ops/registry-orphan-reaper.sh, gap-lifecycle-manager (INFRA-NNN). Confirm via fsevents/dtruss OR by inspecting each daemon's deletion logic."
    - "Fix: any daemon deleting docs/gaps/<ID>.yaml MUST first verify the state.db row is ABSENT (NOT just status:done/status:closed). YAML+state.db divergence means STATE WINS — daemon emits an audit event and rewrites the YAML from state.db rather than deleting it."
    - "Add audit emit: kind=yaml_orphan_pruned with gap_id, file_path, reason, daemon_name (so the source-of-deletion is identifiable next time)"
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-yaml-orphan-prune-state-aware.sh: state.db row X-NNN exists, X-NNN.yaml exists → daemon does NOT delete. state.db row absent, YAML present → daemon deletes WITH the audit emit."
    - "Doctrine cross-ref: CASE STUDY referenced in docs/process/DURABLE_FIX_DOCTRINE.md (CREDIBLE-105) — the 2026-06-05 RESILIENT-110 ship attempt was forced into a YAML-rewrite cycle by this bug"

- id: EFFECTIVE-220
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "chump preflight: per-gate cargo output truncated at ~23k bytes — error line cut off, real diagnostic invisible (blocked 4 preflight retries today)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "`chump preflight` per-gate output capture must preserve the FINAL N lines (where errors usually live) rather than truncating mid-stream. Current behavior: each gate output truncated at ~23k bytes WITH the truncation midway, leaving the real error line cut off."
    - "Alternative: write full per-gate output to a deterministic file path (e.g. `target/preflight-logs/<gate>.log`) and print the path on FAIL so the operator can `cat` it."
    - "Regression repro: artificially produce a 30k-byte cargo error stream and verify the user-visible truncated output contains the LAST 5 lines (the conclusion + \"error: could not compile\" lines), not just the middle."
  notes: |
    Empirical evidence 2026-06-05: 4 preflight retries today (EFFECTIVE-216, RESILIENT-118) each showed truncated cargo output ending mid-"Checking" line, no error visible. Had to re-run cargo clippy --workspace directly to see the actual diagnostic (turned out clippy was fine; failures were sccache/reaper races). Truncation made root-cause diagnosis 10× slower than necessary.

- id: EFFECTIVE-221
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "EFFECTIVE: chump-commit auto-inject Net-new-docs trailer + surface commit-msg-hook rejections"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    Adding a new docs/*.md file requires a 'Net-new-docs: +N' commit trailer (CHUMP_DOCS_DELTA_CHECK), enforced at the commit-msg stage. chump-commit.sh PRINTS the requirement during pre-commit but does NOT auto-inject the trailer, so the commit-msg hook rejects the commit — and when chump-commit output is piped (e.g. '| tail'), the pipe's exit code masks the rejection (cost 2 failed commit attempts on CREDIBLE-105 before manual git-log verification caught it). chump-commit already computes the docs delta (it prints 'net +1'), so it can either auto-append the trailer or fail loudly.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump-commit.sh auto-injects the correct 'Net-new-docs: +N' trailer when the staged set adds N net-new docs/*.md files (matching the commit-msg gate), OR"
    - "if not auto-injecting, chump-commit.sh exits NON-ZERO and prints a clear 'COMMIT REJECTED — add Net-new-docs: +N trailer' as its LAST output line (survives a '"
    - " tail' pipe)"
    - "regression test: committing a new docs/foo.md via chump-commit.sh either succeeds without the caller manually adding the trailer, or fails non-zero with the clear message"

- id: EFFECTIVE-222
  domain: EFFECTIVE
  title: "A2A IGNITION: broadcast.sh persistent fan-out queue — every msg lands in ~/.chump/comms/<recipient>.queue.jsonl, future sessions drain on start (today: 0-lock-files = msg lost forever)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/coord/broadcast.sh writes EVERY message to ~/.chump/comms/<recipient>.queue.jsonl (one JSONL per recipient) in addition to ambient + curator-lock fan-out. For broadcast --to all-opus, write to ~/.chump/comms/all-opus.queue.jsonl. For broadcast --to <session-id>, write to ~/.chump/comms/<session-id>.queue.jsonl.
    - "On SessionStart, inbox-poll.sh / inbox-check-urgent.sh drain the queue files relevant to this session (own session-id + all-opus + role-based aliases like all-curator-opus-shepherd if session matches role pattern) and emit them in the session digest under \"Pending broadcasts\"."
    - After drain, the read entries are moved to ~/.chump/comms/.read/<recipient>/<ts>-<corr_id>.jsonl (cursor preserved for audit but not re-presented).
    - "Reaper: queue files >30 days old are pruned (audit log only)."
    - "Smoke test: broadcast.sh --to all-opus from session A with NO other live sessions; spawn fresh session B; assert SessionStart digest contains the message; assert second start of session B does NOT re-present it."
  notes: |
    ROOT-CAUSE evidence (2026-06-05): broadcast.sh FEEDBACK fan-out checks .chump-locks/.curator-opus-*.lock and silently no-ops if 0 found. Today even the operator's 23:14:33Z broadcast to all-opus only landed in ambient — no inbox writes because no curator-opus locks were live. ~/.chump/inbox/ doesn't exist; ~/.chump/comms/ doesn't exist. This is the missing 'subscribe-side' from A2A_MASTER_PLAN_2026-06-03.md L1/L5. Without this, every broadcast is a coin-toss based on who happens to be running at fan-out time. Pairs with: CREDIBLE-114 (enforcement hook), INFRA-1944 (delivery receipts), INFRA-1862 (umbrella).

