- id: EVAL-094
  domain: EVAL
  title: "CREDIBLE: n=50/cell paired naturalized-framing evaluation — quantify evaluation-awareness bias in chump fixture suite (EVAL-087 follow-through)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md §4 requires that any mechanism claim with |Δ|>0.05 cite either
    a paired naturalized-framing comparison from the RESEARCH-026/EVAL-094 result set OR
    a written justification for why the fixture is not susceptible to evaluation-context
    discrimination. This gap is the measurement leg: run the actual n=50/cell paired eval.
    
    Naturalized framing: same task presented without lab-style preamble (no "evaluate", no
    numbered rubric, no "assistant" role header) vs. standard chump fixture framing. If
    the model's score distribution shifts significantly between framings, any delta measured
    with standard fixtures is confounded by evaluation-awareness.
    
    Signal: IAPS 2026, arXiv:2508.00943 (16–36% monitor-bypass on Claude-class models),
    Meta Muse Spark April 2026 (19.8% benchmark flagging vs 2.0% internal) — external
    evidence that the confound is real at scale.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Preregistration at docs/eval/preregistered/EVAL-094.md is committed before any data collection; includes: fixture class, framing-pair specification, n-per-cell, judge list, hard-fail conditions, analysis plan"
    - "Fixture class: 20 representative tasks drawn from the chump gap-implementation suite (xs/s effort, concrete AC) — same fixtures used in RESEARCH-026 for cross-study comparability"
    - "Two framing conditions per fixture: (A) standard chump framing, (B) naturalized framing with lab markers stripped; 50 trials per cell = 100 trials per fixture × 20 fixtures = 2000 trials total"
    - "Judges: claude-haiku-4-5 + one non-Anthropic judge (Together AI Llama-3.3-70B or equivalent); kappa reported per framing condition"
    - "Result doc at docs/eval/EVAL-094-naturalized-framing-<date>.md: per-condition means, B−A bootstrapped 95% CI, kappa, effect size, n=2 smoke-check output"
    - "Decision rule: if |B−A| < 0.03 across fixture classes → naturalized-framing confound is not dominant; RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md standing caveat lifted. If |B−A| ≥ 0.03 → file a fixture-redesign gap."
    - "RESEARCH_INTEGRITY §1 §2 §6 compliance verified by runner before launch: n≥50 per cell, non-Anthropic judge, exit-code scorer not used"
    - Result doc cross-links RESEARCH-026 (companion qualitative analysis)
  notes: |
    Cited by: docs/process/RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md §4 (phantom-ID fix: RESEARCH-001)
    Companion: RESEARCH-026 (qualitative fixture taxonomy for same fixture class)
    Depends on: EVAL-103 (prereg-enforcement runtime gates) recommended but not hard blocked

- id: EVAL-101
  domain: EVAL
  title: "CREDIBLE: cognition A/B with fleet evidence — does the cognition stack improve agent task outcomes? (PROTOCOL VIOLATION — see EVAL-102 for valid re-run)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Preregistration at docs/eval/preregistered/EVAL-101.md is committed before data collection
    - Run uses claude-sonnet-4, n≥50/cell, all 3 cells (A/B/C), dual LLM judges
    - "Result doc at docs/eval/EVAL-101-cognition-ab-<date>.md: cell means, 95% CI, judge kappa"
    - Decision rendered per §9 of the prereg
  notes: |
    EVAL-101 was closed 2026-05-10 as a null result (delta=+0.025) but violated
    RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md on four counts: wrong model (Qwen 2.5 14B, not Sonnet),
    n=20/cell (below n>=50 floor), Cell C skipped, no LLM judge. The deviations
    section in docs/eval/preregistered/EVAL-101.md was "(none yet)" at close — this
    YAML (filed as INFRA-824 resolution) retroactively documents the violations.
    EVAL-102 is the registered correct re-run. EVAL-103 ships prereg-enforcement
    gates to prevent recurrence.
  closed_date: '2026-05-10'

- id: EVAL-102
  domain: EVAL
  title: "CREDIBLE: EVAL-101 re-run with corrected protocol — n=50/cell, Sonnet 4.6 (not Qwen), Cell C included, dual judges incl. non-Anthropic, deviation-locked"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Preregistration at docs/eval/preregistered/EVAL-102.md is committed (SHA recorded in prereg's locked-fields manifest) BEFORE any data collection
    - Smoke-check (n=2 per cell, ~$0.05) runs end-to-end and writes a parseable result doc — verified before launching n=50 sweep (anti-EVAL-076-pattern)
    - EVAL-103 (prereg-enforcement runtime gates) ships and passes its own tests BEFORE EVAL-102 main sweep launches
    - "Primary sweep: 200 trials (50 × 4 cells: A, B, C, A') using claude-sonnet-4-6, completes in ≤ 48h wall-clock"
