  description: |
    Today every rescue tool (pr-rescue, queue-driver, bot-merge) uses gh pr * GraphQL shortcuts.
    When GraphQL bucket hits 0/5000 (1-2x per active day), all rescue is gagged for ~30 min.
    REST core bucket stays healthy in parallel (4868/5000 typical). Adding a --rest-only mode
    to pr-rescue.sh as the minimum-viable rescue path lets the operator still recover stuck PRs
    during GraphQL exhaustion. REST merge is immediate (no auto-merge); accepted limitation:
    only use when PR is already green and you want to force-land it now.
