  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1026
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump --release --lease <X> ignores --lease arg, releases current session"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Discovered 2026-05-13 trying to clean a stale INFRA-995 lease: chump --release --lease claim-infra-995-44750-1778698509 printed "released session_id=chump-8dbd924f..." — clearly some OTHER session ID (the current chump CLI's, not the one passed). Worked around with raw sqlite3 DELETE. Small fix, real operator hazard: today the only way to release another session is bypassing the CLI.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - src/main.rs --release --lease <SESSION_ID> deletes the named session from state.db AND its corresponding .chump-locks/<SESSION_ID>.json (today it ignores --lease and acts on the current process's inferred session)
