  description: |
    Observed 4x today: bot-merge --fast hits cargo clippy --fix 240s timeout (cargo target-dir lock contention from parallel /tmp worktrees — see sibling INFRA-XXXX), logs "INFRA-587 hang ALERT emitted", logs "clippy --fix pre-flight done", logs "Skipping tests", then process dies silently. Branch is committed locally, no PR opened, no auto-merge armed — operator must recover manually via git push + REST PR open (the pattern used 4 times today). The silent exit hides the failure: looks like success in operator scrollback because the previous line is "clippy --fix pre-flight done". Root cause likely in the "Skipping tests" branch: an unhandled non-zero rc propagates via set -e before reaching "git push". DIFFERENT from INFRA-1030 (arm-AM order), INFRA-1031 (gh pr create GraphQL fallback), INFRA-1034 (tee log).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "bot-merge.sh after the cargo clippy --fix 240s timeout (INFRA-587 hang ALERT path) currently logs \"Skipping tests\" then exits silently without git push, gh pr create, or _bm_fail — observed 4x 2026-05-13 (INFRA-1040, INFRA-1042, INFRA-1038, original INFRA-995/999 retries)"
    - either continue past the timeout properly (push + open PR), OR exit non-zero with _bm_fail so the operator sees a clear failure-class code
    - investigate the set -euo pipefail interaction with the `
    - ""
    - " true` after run_timed_hb clippy --fix invocation that swallows the 124 timeout — somewhere between Skipping tests and git push, set -e is killing the script silently"
    - "test: simulate 124 from clippy step, assert bot-merge either reaches push step OR exits non-zero with explicit log line"
