- id: INFRA-1068
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: fleet-state.json lock contention reduction — batch writes, async updates"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    With multiple concurrent workers each calling fleet_state_set_field per field per curator cycle, every write grabs an exclusive flock on fleet-state.json. Under fleet-size >= 3, these serial acquisitions cause measurable contention (timeouts, delays).
    Solution: introduce a queue+flush pattern. fleet_state_set_field enqueues updates locally; fleet_state_flush applies all queued updates in ONE flock acquisition at end of each logical unit. Adds contention telemetry (fleet_state_lock_contention when wait > 1s) and batch-flush telemetry (fleet_state_batch_flush) so operators can observe the improvement.
    Rough shape:
      (a) scripts/coord/lib/fleet-state-writer.sh — new sourced library
      (b) emergency-fast-path.sh update-jq subcommand + contention emit
      (c) opus-curator.sh: source lib, modify fleet_state_set_field, add flush call
      (d) CI test: scripts/ci/test-fleet-state-batch-writes.sh
      (e) EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml: register both new event kinds
  closed_pr: 2033
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1074
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: active-target-reaper sweeps in-flight chump-claim worktrees under /tmp — destroys uncommitted work"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    TODAY'S incident: while I was committing INFRA-1053 (CHUMP_WORKTREE_BASE wiring) in worktree /private/tmp/chump-infra-1053, the worktree was force-removed mid-commit by a daemon — losing the committed work. Worktree /private/tmp/chump-product-099 was also nuked. The likely culprit is scripts/ops/active-target-reaper.sh (or sibling) running on launchd schedule (~hourly), scanning /tmp/chump-* as a candidate, and force-removing on its own staleness heuristic. The presence of a lease file in .chump-locks/ + active git index activity should have been the "in flight" signal — but the reaper didn't check.
    
    Symptom evidence: commit task showed exit 0 BUT the resulting worktree dir was gone immediately after and no commit ended up on the branch ref. git fsck --unreachable showed no orphan with the INFRA-1053 commit message; the entire commit chain was nuked along with the worktree.
    
    Acceptance:
    1. active-target-reaper.sh + stale-worktree-reaper.sh + worktree-prune.sh must SKIP any worktree whose .chump-locks/<session>.json lease file shows heartbeat_at within last 15 min OR whose .git/index has been touched within last 5 min OR whose git status shows pending uncommitted/unpushed work.
    2. Add ambient emit kind=worktree_reaper_skipped_active when a reaper decides to skip a worktree for one of the reasons above (so we have evidence the protection fired).
    3. Test: create a worktree with an active lease, run the reapers in --execute mode, assert the worktree survives.
    4. Hit by INFRA-1053 commit today — full chain destroyed mid-flight; only recoverable because the diff was small enough to redo from memory.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - active-target-reaper.sh + stale-worktree-reaper.sh + worktree-prune.sh must SKIP any worktree whose .chump-locks/<session>.json lease shows heartbeat_at within last 15 min OR whose .git/index was touched within last 5 min OR whose git status shows pending uncommitted/unpushed work
    - emit kind=worktree_reaper_skipped_active to ambient.jsonl when a reaper skips an active worktree so the protection can be audited
    - "test: create worktree with active lease, run reapers in --execute mode, assert worktree survives"
    - add CHUMP_REAPER_SAFETY_CHECK=0 bypass env var for testing the reaper itself
  closed_pr: 3041
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

