    Today bot-merge.sh checks PR CI status via gh api repos/X/commits/SHA/check-runs — that is one of the highest-frequency calls. Caching check_runs server-side via webhook events eliminates that polling. Unlocks INFRA-1108 bot-merge migration. Pairs with INFRA-1081 schema additions.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "new table check_runs in .chump/github_cache.db: (head_sha TEXT, name TEXT, status TEXT, conclusion TEXT, started_at TEXT, completed_at TEXT, fetched_at_local TEXT, PRIMARY KEY (head_sha, name))"
    - "webhook receiver: on check_suite.completed AND workflow_run.completed events, parse the payload check_runs/jobs array and upsert into check_runs table"
    - "new helper cache_lookup_checks <head_sha> in scripts/coord/lib/github_cache.sh: returns JSON array of check statuses for the SHA"
    - "reconcile script: for each open PR, fetch /commits/<sha>/check-runs (1 REST call per PR, bounded by max-fetch budget) only if check_runs table missing rows for that SHA"
    - "test: synthesize check_suite webhook → assert check_runs rows created"
