  title: "EFFECTIVE: A2A Layer 2b — RPC / request-response with deadlines + 5 use-case wrappers (META-061)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump-coord exports `call_rpc(target_session, method, args, timeout_ms) -> Result<Response>` and `serve_rpc(method, handler)` strongly-typed async APIs; integration test in `tests/a2a_layer2b.rs` covers both sides
    - "Five use-case wrappers shipped and integration-tested: `ask-eta` (remaining seconds on gap), `ask-overlap` (INTENT holders on paths), `ask-handoff` (WIP + stand-down), `ask-progress` (percent_complete + last commit), `ask-capability` (does session have capability X)"
    - Every RPC carries `request_id`; server-side handler de-dups within 60s so retries are idempotent (network blip / timeout reissue safe)
    - "Client deadline enforced: if server doesn't respond within `timeout_ms` (default 10 000ms), `kind=a2a_rpc_timeout` emitted to ambient.jsonl; no blocking call ever exceeds deadline"
