- id: INFRA-1122
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: A2A Layer 3e — multi-agent deliberation primitives with deterministic comparator (META-061)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "`chump-coord::deliberate(gap_id, my_progress, other_session) -> DeliberationOutcome` implements deterministic comparator: (1) higher `percent_complete` wins, (2) tie → more recent `last_commit_sha` wins, (3) further tie → older `started_at` wins (seniority)"
    - Comparator is property-tested over 10K random (my_progress, other_progress) scenario pairs in `tests/a2a_deliberation_comparator.rs`; both sides running the same algorithm always agree on winner (no divergent outcomes)
    - "When INFRA-1116 INTENT overlap is detected: detecting session opens `ask_progress` RPC (Layer 2b) to other session; both exchange `{percent_complete, last_commit_sha, last_activity_ts, remaining_ac[]}`; loser broadcasts HANDOFF with WIP commit SHA and retracts lease within 5s"
    - "Fairness monitor: `deliberation_wins` / `deliberation_losses` per session tracked in scratchpad (Layer 3d); emits `kind=deliberation_fairness_violation` when one session wins > 80% over 50 deliberations"
    - "Edge cases tested: (a) unresponsive side → `a2a_rpc_timeout` after deadline, detected side wins; (b) both at 0% → seniority; (c) WIP conflict → loser attaches diff patch to HANDOFF; (d) three-way overlap → pairwise deliberation in session_id lex order"
    - EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml entries for `deliberation_started`, `deliberation_resolved`, `deliberation_handoff`, `deliberation_fairness_violation` present before code ships
    - "Release gate: 7-day fleet run with > 5 deliberations resolved (verified via `kind=deliberation_resolved` events in ambient.jsonl), zero operator-interventions for overlap conflicts"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1123
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: A2A Layer 4f — signed provenance with key rotation + revocation + trust anchor (META-061)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "`chump init-session-key` generates an ED25519 keypair at session start; private key stored at `.chump-locks/keys/<session-id>.priv` (0600 permissions); public key published in capability manifest `pubkey_b64` field (Layer 2c)"
    - "Every `broadcast.sh` invocation and every NATS publish appends `sig: <base64>` covering `{event, session, ts, gap, files, body}` (signature excludes the `sig` field itself); signing overhead < 5ms p99 (benchmarked in `benches/a2a_signing.rs`)"
    - Verifier reads pubkey from current manifest for the emitting session; signature mismatch → event dropped and `kind=sig_verification_failed` emitted; revoked key → `kind=sig_verification_revoked` emitted
    - "`chump revoke-key <session_id> --reason <text>` persists revocation to scratchpad key `keys.revoked`; revocation is effective fleet-wide within 30s (verified in CI chaos test)"
    - Old pubkeys archived 30 days in `.chump-locks/keys-archive/<yyyy-mm>/<session-id>.pub` for retroactive audit
    - "CI chaos test `scripts/ci/test-a2a-layer4f-revocation.sh`: revoke a session key mid-cycle, assert all subsequent events from that session are dropped within 30s"
    - "Trust model documented: in-fleet sessions on same machine trust each other; cross-host requires operator-signed `trust-anchor.pub` config; `CHUMP_A2A_LAYER=4` enables verify-required mode (warn-only during transition)"
    - "Threat model doc `docs/design/A2A_SECURITY.md` covers: compromised agent, prompt injection, replay attacks, cross-fleet impersonation, equivocation; reviewed by ≥ 2 external reviewers before merge"
    - EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml entries for `sig_verification_failed`, `sig_verification_revoked`, `session_key_rotated` present before code ships
    - "Release gate: all six A2A layers running under signed-event mode for 7 days with `CHUMP_A2A_LAYER=4`; one chaos test for key revocation; < 0.5 CPU overhead at 32 workers × 100 events/min"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

