- id: INFRA-1139
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: auto-close open PRs whose gap is already marked done (inverse of bounced-pr-detector)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Today's evidence (2026-05-14): PR #1736 (INFRA-1024) sat open DIRTY for ~7 h
    against main. INFRA-1024 gap was already status=done; the functionally-
    equivalent fix had landed via INFRA-1057 (#1778). The rebase loop wedged
    every 5 min trying to re-resolve a semantic conflict for a branch that
    should have been closed at gap-ship time. Cost: ~6 wasted queue-driver
    runs + operator attention to close manually.
    
    This is the inverse of bounced-pr-detector.sh (INFRA-781):
    - bounced-pr-detector: PR closed unmerged → gap still open (work lost).
    - orphan-pr-closer:    gap marked done   → PR still open (branch eats CI).
    
    Rough shape: (a) scripts/coord/orphan-pr-closer.sh, REST-only (INFRA-1080
    critical background work), dry-run by default with --apply, (b) extract gap
    ID from PR title or branch name, (c) call `chump gap show <id>`, act only if
    status=done, (d) freshness gate skips PRs updated in last 30 min so we don't
    race a merging PR, (e) idempotency via .chump-locks/orphan-pr-seen.txt, (f)
    operator escape hatch: "orphan-pr-closer-skip" token in PR title.
    
    Follow-up: structural integration into `chump gap ship` so the moment a gap
    is marked done, any other open PRs for it are closed atomically. Sweeper
