- id: INFRA-1141
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: queue-driver resolve_dirty_pr — refetch before push (stale-info rejection) + don't mask push exit code with tail"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Discovered while validating INFRA-1137 (#1804) in production 2026-05-14. Bug 1: stale-info push rejection — resolve_dirty_pr pushes with --force-with-lease but doesn't refetch the branch first. After concurrent auto-merge attempts or sibling rescue runs, local view of origin/<branch> is stale; lease refused with "stale info". Rescue logic completed but push fails silently and PR stays DIRTY. Bug 2: masked push exit code — push piped to `tail -1` to keep output short, masks exit code. Function reports "✓ clean rebase pushed" even when push failed. queue-driver outer `if resolve_dirty_pr` treats failure as success. Real impact: #1751 reported success 3 consecutive runs while never landing push. Required manual fetch+retry. Fix shape: (a) `git fetch origin "$branch" --quiet || true` before push, (b) save push output to var, check $? before logging.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - resolve_dirty_pr in scripts/coord/queue-driver.sh runs `git fetch origin <branch>` before pushing to refresh lease
    - Push exit code captured into variable; success path only taken when rc==0
    - On push failure emit kind=dirty_pr_push_failed via chump ambient emit (INFRA-1048) with --field pr=N --field branch=X --field error_tail=Y and return 1; also retrofit existing direct-printf calls to use same CLI
    - EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml registers dirty_pr_push_failed
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-queue-driver-push-rescue.sh: stub failing git push; assert function returns non-zero and emits push_failed (not auto_resolved)"
    - Both clean-rebase and merge-driver-resolution code paths get same treatment
