- id: INFRA-1142
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: per-job path filters in ci.yml — split monolithic code filter into rust/web/tauri/scripts/acp"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Current .github/workflows/ci.yml uses a single code paths-filter that matches ~25 patterns (basically everything except whitespace-only diffs). The wide filter exists because INFRA-272 hit the skipped != passing footgun on PR #803 (docs-only PR forever blocked). Cost: every PR pays full CI even when only docs/scripts/web changed. With current job times that means ~25 min CI for a docs-only PR.
    
    Solution depends on the synthetic-green stub pattern (sibling gap) so we can have fine-grained filters without re-triggering the skipped != passing bug.
    
    Rough shape: (a) replace the single code output with: rust (src/**, crates/**, chump-tool-macro/**, Cargo.toml, Cargo.lock), web (web/**, e2e/**, src/web_server.rs, src/routes/**), tauri (desktop/**, e2e-tauri/**), scripts (scripts/**, .github/workflows/**, scripts/git-hooks/**), acp (src/acp*.rs, crates/chump-tool-macro/**), docs (docs/**). (b) re-point each downstream job if: to its specific filter output. (c) update fast-checks (mixed: needs rust OR scripts), clippy / cargo-test / coverage (rust), e2e-pwa (web), tauri-cowork-e2e (tauri), ACP smoke (acp).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "ci.yml changes job emits 6 filter outputs: rust, web, tauri, scripts, acp, docs"
    - Each downstream job if condition references its specific output (e.g. clippy uses needs.changes.outputs.rust)
    - push and merge_group events still trigger every job (the bypass is preserved for main-branch CI)
    - Docs-only PR (only docs/** changed) runs ≤2 min wall-clock total (vs current ~25 min)
    - Rust-only PR skips e2e-pwa + tauri-cowork-e2e jobs
    - Web-only PR skips clippy + cargo-test + coverage
    - "Pre-commit guard in scripts/ci/test-path-filter-coverage.sh: take last 50 closed PRs, project what each filter would have triggered, verify no required check would have been missed"
    - This gap depends on the synthetic-green stub gap (sibling) — file both together
  depends_on: [INFRA-1143]
  closed_pr: 1824
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1143
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: synthetic-green stub pattern for required CI checks — fixes skipped != passing footgun"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Required status checks in branch protection block forever when their gating filter says they should skip. This forced INFRA-272 to widen the code filter to ~25 patterns, defeating the point of path filtering.
    
    The fix is a synthetic-green stub: every required check has TWO sibling jobs (the real heavy one, conditional on path filter) and a 5-second stub (conditional on the opposite). A third rollup job depends on both and exits success if either succeeded. Branch protection points at the rollup name.
    
    This pattern is what GitHub Actions docs recommend for required + conditional combinations (see actions/runner discussions). It is the prerequisite for the per-job-path-filter gap (sibling).
    
    Rough shape per required job (clippy, cargo-test, audit, ACP, fast-checks rollup): (a) keep the existing job, add if: needs.changes.outputs.<filter> == true. (b) add <job>-stub with the inverse if and a 5s echo step. (c) add <job>-required with needs: [<job>, <job>-stub], if: always(), and a case-based exit. (d) update branch-protection contexts (out-of-band, operator does this) to point at the -required suffix. (e) document in scripts/coord/README.md as the canonical pattern for adding new required checks.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "ci.yml has the synthetic-green stub pattern for at least 4 required checks: clippy, cargo-test, audit, ACP protocol smoke"
    - Each required-check rollup job (clippy-required, etc.) name is what branch protection enforces
    - On a docs-only PR (no rust changes), clippy-stub runs in <10s and clippy-required reports success
    - On a rust PR, clippy runs as today and clippy-required reports its result
    - test-required rollup (used by branch protection today) refactored to use this same pattern
    - Documented in scripts/coord/README.md under a Required-check pattern section
    - "Migration path documented: which branch-protection contexts need to change names and in what order"
    - "Validated: PR #803-class case (docs-only diff) merges in <2 min after this lands"
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1144
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump gap ship atomically closes other open PRs for the same gap (structural zero-orphan)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    Structural fix for the orphan-PR pattern (today's #1736 mess; INFRA-1139
    is the sweeper-style stopgap). When a gap is marked `done` — either via
    `chump gap ship`, the commit-subject auto-close path, or any other code
    path that flips status to done — we should *atomically* close any other
    open PR whose title or branch references the same gap ID. Zero orphan
    state, zero sweeper required.
    
    Why this complements INFRA-1139:
    - INFRA-1139 (orphan-pr-closer.sh): cron-style sweeper; eventually
      consistent; runs every N min; needs operator to wire to cron.
    - INFRA-1144: structural at write time; eventually-immediately consistent;
      no sweeper needed; runs whenever any code path flips gap status to done.
    
    Both should ship — INFRA-1139 is the safety net (catches any path that
    INFRA-1144 doesn't cover, including external scripts), INFRA-1144 is the
    primary closure.
    
    Rough shape: in src/gap_store.rs (or the canonical gap-ship Rust entry
    point), after the status=done transition is durably committed:
    1. Query open PRs whose title contains the gap ID (REST: gh api
       pulls?state=open + grep, or use the .chump/github_cache.db).
    2. For each match where head SHA hasn't been pushed in the last 30 min
       (don't race a merging PR), close via gh api PATCH /pulls/N state=closed
       with a "superseded — gap marked done via #closed_pr" comment.
    3. Emit kind=orphan_pr_closed_at_ship for each.
    
    Operator escape hatch: same as INFRA-1139 — title token
    "orphan-pr-closer-skip" exempts a PR. CHUMP_GAP_SHIP_NO_ORPHAN_CLOSE=1
    disables the whole behavior.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - gap-ship code path (Rust) queries for open PRs matching the gap ID and closes orphans atomically after the status=done transition is committed
    - "Freshness gate: skip PRs whose head_sha pushed_at is within 30 min (CHUMP_GAP_SHIP_ORPHAN_FRESHNESS_MIN, default 30)"
    - "Operator escape hatch: skip PRs with 'orphan-pr-closer-skip' in title"
    - "Bypass: CHUMP_GAP_SHIP_NO_ORPHAN_CLOSE=1 disables this behavior"
    - Emits ambient kind=orphan_pr_closed_at_ship via `chump ambient emit` (INFRA-1048) with --field pr=N --field gap=X --field ship_pr=Y; EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml registers it
    - "Test: integration test creates a fake PR, marks gap done via chump gap ship, asserts the fake PR is closed and the ambient event landed"
    - "Idempotent: re-running chump gap ship on an already-done gap does not re-attempt to close PRs already closed (avoids gh API spam)"
  closed_date: '2026-05-15'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

