- id: INFRA-1193
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: fix atomic_claim nats_dual_write_conflict_emits_ambient_event flake — subprocess/file-read race"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  description: |
    The test spawns a coord-shim subprocess and then reads back ambient.jsonl to
    verify that a NATS dual-write conflict emits the expected event. Under high
    parallel cargo test load, the subprocess exit may race with the parent's file
    read — the write buffer may not be flushed by the OS before the parent's
    read_to_string call.
    
    First observed: 2026-05-14 in PR #1772 (INFRA-998) CI run 25847086604,
    job 75945251696. Test passed in all other parallel contexts (1927/1928).
    
    Rough fix: add a brief spin-poll for the ambient file after the subprocess
    returns, or ensure the subprocess flushes before exit. If the race is between
    two parallel instances of the test mutating the same temp path (unlikely given
    tempdir), use serial_test.
  opened_date: '2026-05-14'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1194
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: fix kpi_report::infra617_leverage_counts_depends_on parallelism race under full test suite"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    Under parallel test-suite execution, this test fails with 'should have leverage entries' despite passing in isolation. Likely cause: tempfile collision or global state leakage when another test spawns a worktree concurrently. The test creates its own tempdir + GapStore, but git commands inside the test may pick up the outer worktree's git context.
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

