- id: INFRA-1199
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: ci-yml-add-row merge-driver injects orphan '- name:' steps without 'run:' during rebase — breaks workflow file"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    TODAY'S incident: While rebasing chump/infra-987-claim onto main (INFRA-987 deletes gap-claim.sh + gap-preflight.sh), the scripts/git/merge-driver-ci-yml-add-row.sh helper appended this single line at the end of .github/workflows/ci.yml each time:
        - name: gap-reserve concurrency (INFRA-021)
    without a matching 'run:' directive. GitHub Actions then rejected the workflow file outright ('This run likely failed because of a workflow file issue'; zero jobs created); none of the required CI checks ran, blocking the merge.
    
    The proper version of the same step ('gap-reserve concurrency + preflight (INFRA-021)' with full 'run: |' block) already exists earlier in the same file. The driver appears to be:
    1. Detecting that a 'gap-reserve concurrency' step is mentioned in conflict-resolution as 'add row'
    2. Appending JUST the '- name:' header, dropping the body
    
    This regression hit the INFRA-987 rebase chain at least 3 times in sequence today:
      - eb178c88 fix(INFRA-987): drop malformed ci.yml step injected by rebase merge-driver
      - ae188e84 fix(INFRA-987): trim trailing orphan comments from ci.yml end
      - ec8ec80e fix(INFRA-987): drop malformed ci.yml step injected by ci-yml-add-row merge-driver (3rd recurrence)
    
    Each time, the next rebase undoes the fix. Until INFRA-987 lands, every rebase against main triggers it.
    
    Acceptance:
    1. scripts/git/merge-driver-ci-yml-add-row.sh: refuse to inject a '- name:' step header unless its matching 'run:' (or 'uses:') body is also present in the conflict resolution context.
    2. CI test: synthesize a ci.yml with a missing 'run:' step, run the driver, assert it either preserves the body OR aborts with a clear error rather than silently appending an invalid step.
    3. Document the regression mode in docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md so future operators recognize the symptom faster.
    4. Optional: when the driver finds it cannot resolve safely, emit kind=ci_yml_merge_driver_abort to ambient.jsonl for auditability.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. scripts/git/merge-driver-ci-yml-add-row.sh: refuse to inject a '- name:' step header unless its matching 'run:' (or 'uses:') body is also present in the conflict resolution context; abort safely instead of writing a malformed step"
    - "2. scripts/ci/test-merge-driver-ci-yml-add-row.sh: synthesize a ci.yml with an orphan '- name:' conflict, run the driver, assert it does NOT write a step without 'run:', assert a valid step IS written when the body is present"
    - "3. docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md updated with a '### ci-yml merge-driver orphan step' subsection describing the symptom, root cause, and workaround"
    - 4. CI step added to .github/workflows/ci.yml running the new test
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1201
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: web/v2/index.html hot-file — merge=union driver + duplicate-script-tag pre-commit guard"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Live break observed 2026-05-14: web/v2/index.html is a PWA append-only hot file. Each new PWA feature (PRODUCT-NNN/INFRA-1011/1013-style) adds a <script src=X.js> entry to the script-loading block + (optionally) a <chump-X></chump-X> custom-element placement before </body>. Both are append-only zones; concurrent feature PRs hit the same blocks and produce textual conflicts. 3 PRs stuck DIRTY (#1827 INFRA-1011 web_server+index, #1860 PRODUCT-090 index, plus others) for hours. Fix: mark web/v2/index.html as merge=union in .gitattributes (same proven pattern as EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml + env-vars-internal.txt). Side-effect risk (union merges line-unique entries — two PRs adding the same exact tag both land) mitigated via pre-commit guard catching duplicate <script src= and <chump-X></chump-X>.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - web/v2/index.html declared merge=union in .gitattributes
    - scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit-pwa-index-uniq.sh exists, executable, rejects duplicate <script src=X.js> lines
    - Guard rejects duplicate <chump-X></chump-X> top-level placements
    - Guard passes on clean unique content
    - Guard wired into scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit; bypass via CHUMP_PWA_INDEX_UNIQ_CHECK=0
    - "Test scripts/ci/test-pwa-index-merge-driver.sh validates all of the above + end-to-end: two divergent feature branches with different <script src> additions merge cleanly via union with no conflict markers, all additions preserved"
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  closed_pr: 1873
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

