- id: INFRA-1237
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml drift — 22 emit-without-register kinds + 88 register-without-emit orphans; pre-commit guard only checks staged diff"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    Source: 2026-05-14 resilience+observability+UX audit, Part 2 finding #7 — top signal.
    
    scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit-event-registry.sh:42 enforces EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml on STAGED ADDITIONS only ('git diff --cached … -- '*.rs' …'). Existing emit sites that predate INFRA-754 or were committed while the guard was bypassed never get caught. Result today:
      - 22 emit-without-register kinds in production: dup_pr_blocked (bot-merge), gh_secondary_limit_hit (lib/github.sh), meta_filed (gap-reserve), pr_scope_divergence, session_rescue, timeout_rescue, lint_storm, … and 15 more.
      - 88 register-without-emit orphans: adversary_alert, auto_merge_armed, branch_protection_drift, cost_budget_breach, gap_abandoned, daemon_silent, … the registry is currently aspirational doc, not ground truth.
    
    Consumers (waste-tally, fleet-brief, kpi-report) parse these events to drive operator decisions. Registry drift degrades trust silently — operator dashboards display kinds that nobody emits and miss kinds that fire daily.
    
    Why P0: this is the credibility floor of the whole observability layer. Until fixed, every claim about 'we emit X' from CLAUDE.md is unverified.
    
    Acceptance:
    1. scripts/ci/test-event-registry-coverage.sh: full repo grep for `"kind":"..."` literals in src/ + crates/ + scripts/ ; diff against EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml; fail on either direction (emit-without-register OR register-without-emit, with allowlist for intentional reserved kinds).
    2. Add to fast-checks in .github/workflows/ci.yml so the gate is enforced on every PR, not just staged-diff.
    3. Initial reconciliation: register the 22 emitters; either implement-or-prune the 88 orphans.
    4. Document the registry as ground truth in docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml header.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "scripts/ci/test-event-registry-coverage.sh exists: greps src/ + crates/ + scripts/ for `\"kind\":\"...\"` JSON literals; parses docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml; reports emit-without-register AND register-without-emit drift"
    - Drift gate fails the build on either direction unless the kind is in an explicit reserved-kinds allowlist (scripts/ci/event-registry-reserved.txt) with a comment explaining why
    - "Initial reconciliation lands: every emit-without-register kind is added to EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml with proper {emitter, trigger, consumers, fields_required}; every register-without-emit orphan is either implemented or removed from the YAML"
    - Audit script wired into fast-checks in .github/workflows/ci.yml so it runs on every PR (not just staged diff like the existing pre-commit-event-registry.sh)
    - "EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml header updated to state explicitly: this file is the ground-truth contract — fleet-brief, waste-tally, kpi-report consumers depend on it; CI gate enforces both-direction coverage per INFRA-1237"
    - "Fixture test: a tmp .rs file with an unregistered emit fails the audit; same emit registered passes; an unmatched register entry also fails"
  closed_pr: 1949
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1238
