- id: INFRA-1247
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: alert classifier false-positives — silent_agent ignores operator sessions; pr_stuck excludes closed PRs"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Session-start brief shows 27 silent_agent + 18 pr_stuck alerts in last 30 min — looks alarming but is 100% noise. Diagnosis 2026-05-14:
    
    silent_agent (201/30min in raw stream): ALL from a single session "chump-Chump-1776471708" — the operator's persistent IDE session (ts indicates early April 2026 creation, well past any worker lifecycle). The classifier fires silent_agent on any session that has held a lease >N min without a heartbeat, but the operator session intentionally doesn't beat (interactive use, no per-tool emit). False positive per event.
    
    pr_stuck (102/30min): 63 events have no PR# attached (parse fallback). Top-attributed are #1154/#1336/#1080/#1076 — all closed days ago. Alerts re-fire on stale state.
    
    Cost: operator opens session brief, sees 45+ alerts, has to decide whether to investigate. Today's answer: every alert is noise. Signal-to-noise on this surface is effectively 0%. Eventually the operator stops reading alerts.
    
    Fix shape:
      (a) silent_agent emitter checks session.kind or session_id prefix; if it matches operator IDE pattern, skip emit
      (b) pr_stuck emitter cross-checks PR state via cache_lookup_pr (INFRA-1081) before emitting; if pr.state is closed or merged, skip
      (c) Add a kind alert_classifier_suppressed ambient event with original_kind and reason so we can measure suppression rate
    
    Bonus: an alerts(30m) line in the session brief that distinguishes real signals from suppressed would tell the operator at a glance whether to look.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - silent_agent emitter (scripts/coord/silent-agent-detector.sh or equivalent) skips sessions whose lease files match the operator pattern (chump-Chump-* or kind=operator)
    - pr_stuck emitter (scripts/coord/pr-stuck-detector.sh or equivalent) calls cache_lookup_pr (INFRA-1081) before emit and skips closed/merged PRs
    - kind=alert_classifier_suppressed event registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml with fields ts, kind, original_kind, reason, target_id; used to measure suppression rate
    - Session brief alerts(30m) line splits real vs suppressed counts so operator can tell at a glance whether N alerts means anything
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-alert-classifier.sh: synthesize 5 fake silent_agent events (2 operator, 3 real) + 5 pr_stuck events (3 closed, 2 open), verify 3 silent_agent + 2 pr_stuck emit and 5 suppressed events fire"
    - After this lands the next session brief shows real_alerts(30m)=0-2 instead of 45+ on a healthy fleet
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  closed_pr: 1903
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

