- id: INFRA-1257
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: install chump-planner binary + launchd plist running it hourly — write top-N scored gaps to .chump-locks/gap-priority.json for the fleet picker to consume"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    The chump-planner crate (INFRA-1021, merged today) exists at crates/chump-planner/ and produces topo-aware scored gap rankings. But the binary isn't installed (`which chump-planner` returns 'not found') and nothing runs it on a schedule. The scoring logic is built; the production loop is missing.
    
    Acceptance:
    1. Add chump-planner binary to the workspace install path. Either:
       (a) make 'chump-planner' an additional [[bin]] in the root Cargo.toml that ships with 'cargo install --path .' (preferred — one binary, multiple subcommands)
       (b) keep as separate workspace bin, ship as 'cargo install -p chump-planner'
    2. New scripts/setup/install-chump-planner-launchd.sh + plist running hourly via 'chump planner rank --top 50 --json > .chump-locks/gap-priority.json'.
    3. INFRA-1258 (the picker-consumes-priority follow-up) reads .chump-locks/gap-priority.json.
    4. Schema doc: gap-priority.json contains [{gap_id, score, rationale, pillar, effort, blocker_degree}, ...] ordered by score desc.
    5. CI test: scripts/ci/test-chump-planner-rank.sh — exercises rank with a synthetic state.db; asserts JSON schema + ordering invariants.
    
    Source: 2026-05-14 prioritization-automation audit. chump-planner is 80% built (crate exists, logic ships); 20% wired (no install, no schedule).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. cargo build --bin chump-plan succeeds; binary callable as chump-plan\n2. launchd plist dev.chump.gap-planner installed via scripts/setup/install-gap-planner-launchd.sh; runs hourly\n3. .chump-locks/gap-priority.json exists after first run; schema: [{gap_id,score,rationale,pillar,effort,blocker_degree,layer,critical_path_days}] ordered score desc — layer=0 means no deps, layer=N means longest dep chain depth; critical_path_days=longest chain in effort-days from this gap to a leaf dependent\n4. CI test scripts/ci/test-chump-planner-rank.sh: run binary against fixture gaps dir, verify JSON schema + layer/cp fields + ordering invariants\n5. stale file (>2h) triggers WARN in picker log\n6. Two gaps with same score but different layers: lower layer always ranks higher (tier-0 before tier-1)"
  closed_pr: 1909
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1258
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: fleet picker (worker.sh / _pick_and_claim_gap.py / chump pick INFRA-1228) consumes .chump-locks/gap-priority.json — pick BEST gap not first-matching"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today the fleet picker (scripts/dispatch/worker.sh + scripts/dispatch/_pick_and_claim_gap.py — or chump pick post-INFRA-1228) selects the FIRST gap matching status=open + no_deps + FLEET_DOMAIN_FILTER. No scoring. A betweenness-high P1 looks identical to a leaf P3 to the picker. Result: critical-path bottlenecks linger while leaves get shipped.
    
    Depends on INFRA-1257 (planner installed + producing .chump-locks/gap-priority.json).
    
    Acceptance:
    1. Picker reads .chump-locks/gap-priority.json if present; pick highest-score gap that also matches the worker's filter.
    2. Fallback: if priority file is stale (>2h old) or absent, fall back to current first-fit behavior with a warning to ambient.jsonl (kind=picker_priority_stale).
    3. New kind=picker_used_priority emitted when scored pick succeeds; includes the rank delta vs. first-fit (so we measure 'how much would we have wasted picking the first match').
    4. CI test: scripts/ci/test-picker-priority.sh — synthesize 3 candidate gaps with priority scores, assert highest-scored is chosen.
    5. Source: 2026-05-14 prioritization-automation audit.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. picker reads gap-priority.json when file exists and age < 2h; picks highest-score matching gap over first-fit\n2. picker respects layer ordering: will not claim a gap at layer N if any layer < N gap is open+unclaimed and matches worker filter (prevents two workers grabbing tier-2 siblings while tier-0 foundation sits unpicked)\n3. picker falls back to existing sort + logs WARN kind=picker_priority_stale when file absent or stale\n4. kind=picker_used_priority emitted to ambient with {file,age_s,scored,layer_enforced} fields; registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml\n5. CHUMP_SKIP_LAYER_GATE=1 bypass env var available for operator override\n6. CI test scripts/ci/test-picker-priority.sh: inject fixture priority file with mixed layers, verify picker selects highest-score tier-0 gap over higher-score tier-2 gap"
  depends_on: [INFRA-1257, INFRA-1281]
  closed_date: '2026-05-15'
  closed_pr: 2076
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

