- id: INFRA-1281
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: add layer + critical_path_days to chump-plan JSON output — enable tier-aware picker (INFRA-1257 follow-on)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    chump-plan (INFRA-1257, merged) outputs gap-priority.json with score + unblocks_count but no topological layer or critical path. Without these fields the fleet picker (INFRA-1258) cannot enforce tier ordering — workers can pile onto tier-2 leaves while the tier-0 foundation (INFRA-988, INFRA-1116 etc.) sits unpicked. The unblocking_bonus×50 score signal partially compensates but cannot prevent two workers from simultaneously claiming sibling gaps that both block on the same unstarted parent.
    
    Add to each item in gap-priority.json:
      layer: u32  — 0 = no deps (foundation), 1 = only layer-0 deps, N = longest dep chain depth. Computed as BFS depth from graph roots.
      critical_path_days: f32 — longest chain of effort-days from this gap through all its transitive dependents to a leaf. Uses petgraph longest-path on the DAG with effort_to_days(effort) node weights.
    
    Source: petgraph DAG already built in crates/chump-planner/src/graph.rs; topo_order() and unblocks() are available. Layer = reverse BFS from roots. Critical path = single-source longest path (DAG so no cycles).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. chump-plan --format json output includes 'layer' (u32) and 'critical_path_days' (f32) for every item\n2. layer=0 for gaps with no dependencies; layer=N for gaps whose longest dep chain has N hops\n3. critical_path_days = sum of effort_to_days() along the longest forward chain (this gap + all transitive dependents to a leaf)\n4. gaps with layer=0 always have >= layer=1 score in the absence of other signals (layer itself does not penalise, but the layer field enables INFRA-1258 to enforce tier ordering)\n5. CI test: fixture DAG of 5 gaps (root, two layer-1, one layer-2, one isolated); verify layer values and critical_path_days monotonically longer toward root\n6. Schema doc in crates/chump-planner/src/output/json.rs updated with new fields"
  closed_pr: 1962
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1282
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: gh shim transparently rewrites 'gh pr view N' to REST /pulls/N + cache_lookup_pr — kills ~100 GraphQL calls/hr"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Diagnosis 2026-05-14 of throttle storms: gh pr view is the #1 GraphQL burner at 74 calls/hr. 6 caller scripts (pr-watch.sh, bot-merge.sh, worktree-prune.sh, opus-curator.sh, bounced-pr-detector.sh, queue-driver.sh) use it directly. INFRA-1107 cache exists with fresh data (31 PR rows, webhook events 3min ago) but they bypass it. Rather than migrating 6 callers one-by-one, rewrite at the shim layer: when gh sees 'pr view N', transparently translate to REST /pulls/N + cache_lookup_pr. Single PR fixes all 6 callers' GraphQL-to-REST migration. Estimated impact: kills ~100/150 GraphQL calls/hr, drops throttle events from 200/hr to <50/hr.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/coord/lib/gh-shim/gh detects 'gh pr view <PR-or-branch> [--json X] [-q jq]' before forwarding to real gh
    - "For matched invocations: numeric arg uses cache_lookup_pr; branch-name arg resolves via pr_state head_ref column"
    - "On cache HIT: shapes the cached REST JSON to match gh pr view --json output; emits kind=cache_hit ambient event"
    - "On cache MISS: REST gh api repos/X/pulls/N (NOT GraphQL); emits cache_miss; writes result through cache lib"
    - "Backward compat: -q/--jq still works on translated output; --watch/--comments/--web fall through to real gh"
    - Unsupported --json fields fall through (return 2) so caller gets canonical gh output
    - "Bypass: CHUMP_GH_SHIM_NO_REWRITE=1 forces real gh pr view"
    - "Field mapping covers: number, state (upper), title, body, url, headRefName, baseRefName, isDraft, mergeable, mergeStateStatus (upper), autoMergeRequest (reshape with mergeMethod), createdAt/updatedAt/closedAt/mergedAt, author (wrap login)"
    - Test scripts/ci/test-gh-shim-pr-view-rewrite.sh 12 assertions including branch-name resolution and ambient emission
  closed_date: '2026-05-14'
  closed_pr: 1933
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

