- id: INFRA-1319
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: GitHub Liaison Phase 3 — mutation routing via NATS request/reply (workers never call GitHub directly)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: l
  acceptance_criteria:
    - A chump-github-liaison daemon receives GitHub mutation requests from workers via NATS request/reply on subject chump.github.mutations.<action>; only the liaison process holds the GH_TOKEN; workers have no direct GitHub API access
    - "Supported mutation types in Phase 3: pr.create, pr.merge, pr.comment, pr.label, pr.update-branch; each request carries {request_id, action, params}; response carries {request_id, result, gh_response_code}"
    - "Rate-limit enforcement: liaison enforces CHUMP_GH_MAX_CALLS_PER_MIN centrally (one token bucket for the entire fleet); workers that would exceed the limit receive a 429_queued response and may retry after retry_after_ms"
    - "Call criticality honored: request carries criticality: critical|background; when GraphQL remaining < 10%, background mutations are queued; critical mutations proceed"
    - Workers that previously called gh or chump_gh directly are refactored to use the NATS request/reply wrapper; audit scripts/coord/ and src/web_server.rs for direct gh calls and migrate them
    - "Offline fallback: when NATS is unavailable, workers fall back to direct gh calls (Phase 1/2 behavior); emit kind=github_liaison_fallback to ambient.jsonl"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-github-liaison-phase3.sh: mock NATS + mock gh; 5 concurrent workers send pr.create mutations; assert all 5 requests serialized through the liaison, rate limit enforced, responses correlated by request_id"
    - "Events: github_mutation_queued, github_mutation_sent, github_mutation_failed, github_liaison_fallback registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml before code ships"
