- id: INFRA-1325
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: auto-detect CHUMP_GITHUB_MODE=offline at startup — graceful degradation when GitHub unreachable, auto-recovery when reconnected (OFFLINE_FIRST.md Phase 4)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - At chump startup (and on each worker cycle), a connectivity probe checks GitHub reachability; if probe fails, CHUMP_GITHUB_MODE is auto-set to offline without operator intervention
    - "In offline mode: all GitHub mutation operations (pr create, pr merge, pr comment) are queued to .chump-locks/github-queue.jsonl with a queued_at timestamp; gap-work continues using local state.db and ambient.jsonl only"
    - "Auto-recovery: background probe re-runs every 60s; when GitHub becomes reachable again, queued mutations are drained in order (FIFO) with dedup by request_id, and kind=github_offline_recovery is emitted"
    - "Events: kind=github_offline_detected emitted when probe first fails (includes fail_reason, queue_depth); kind=github_offline_recovery emitted when drain completes (includes mutations_replayed, mutations_skipped_stale)"
    - "Stale-queue guard: mutations older than 4h at recovery time are dropped with kind=github_queue_item_stale event (not replayed)"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-github-offline-autodetect.sh: mock gh to return ECONNREFUSED, assert offline mode detected within 10s, queued item replayed on recovery, 5h-old item dropped with stale event"
    - "chump health output includes GitHub mode line: github: online | offline (queue: N items) so operator can see current state at a glance"
  notes: |
    [2026-05-30T04:21:09Z] [2026-05-29 offline-first classification] Public-side, Phase 5 of INFRA-2246 offline-first roadmap. Operator-controllable + auto-detect via reachability probe; chump fleet doctor reports current mode.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

