- id: INFRA-1347
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: worktree reaper must skip worktrees with uncommitted/unpushed work (INFRA-779/-1200 follow-up — destroys mid-session edits)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Today: scripts/coord/worktree-prune.sh (or whichever reaper currently runs) removes worktrees aggressively after some idle window. Two concrete losses in 2026-05-15 session: INFRA-1346 attempt #1 (~40 lines of bot-merge.sh edit + EVENT_REGISTRY entry) and INFRA-1346 attempt #2 (worktree + gitdir both gone) — work had to be re-derived from the design file. The reaper deleted worktrees that contained uncommitted edits AND an active git lease + branch."
    - "Required pre-delete checks (each independently sufficient to SKIP delete):"
    - (a) `git status --porcelain` returns non-empty (uncommitted changes — including untracked + staged)
    - (b) HEAD differs from origin/<branch> (unpushed commits — `git rev-list --count origin/<branch>..HEAD > 0`)
    - (c) lease file `.chump-locks/<session>.json` exists with `gap_id` matching the branch name AND lease.expires_at > now (lease still live per session TTL)
    - (d) any file under the worktree was modified within the last 30 minutes (cheap mtime check)
    - When any of the above is true, the reaper emits `kind=worktree_prune_skipped` to ambient with the specific reason and the path it spared.
    - When all of the above are false AND the worktree is genuinely stale (last mtime > N hours, default 6), proceed with delete and emit `kind=worktree_orphan_pruned` (existing event kind, already registered).
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-worktree-prune-protects-live-edits.sh: create a temp worktree, write an uncommitted file in it, invoke the reaper, assert the worktree still exists and `worktree_prune_skipped` was emitted with reason=uncommitted_changes. Then commit the file but DO NOT push, re-invoke reaper, assert still spared with reason=unpushed_commits. Then push, mark the worktree old via touch -t, re-invoke reaper, assert it IS deleted."
    - "Docs: update docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md under existing \"Linked worktree git path confusion (INFRA-779)\" section — add a sentence noting INFRA-1347 protects in-flight work, and warning operators not to disable the protection in production."
    - "Out of scope: lease-TTL reconciliation (separate concern); reaper performance (one git status per worktree is cheap)"
  closed_date: '2026-05-15'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1348
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: audit non-required CI jobs for rollup-FAILURE trap (INFRA-1342 audit follow-up — 22 candidate jobs in ci.yml)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Background: INFRA-1342 (shipped 2026-05-15) fixed the rollup-FAILURE trap for tauri-cowork-e2e specifically. The same trap can fire for ANY of the 22 other non-required CI jobs in .github/workflows/ci.yml whenever they flake. This gap is the case-by-case audit."
    - "Process: for each non-required job (anything NOT in branch-protection required_status_checks list — currently `test`, `audit`, `ACP protocol smoke test (Zed / JetBrains compatible)`), classify into one of:"
    - (a) Real correctness gate — MUST fail loud; no change (clippy, cargo-test, fast-checks-required, audit-required, etc.)
    - "(b) Flaky/environment-sensitive — apply `continue-on-error: true` (tauri-cowork-e2e is the precedent)"
    - (c) Long-running / cron-only — drop the PR trigger entirely, schedule via `workflow_dispatch` + cron (e2e-battle-sim, e2e-pwa, e2e-golden-path are candidates)
    - For each job that gets either (b) or (c), emit a single commit with the change + a comment referencing INFRA-1348 and the classification reasoning.
    - "CI smoke test scripts/ci/test-rollup-not-blocked-by-flaky-job.sh: parse ci.yml job names, cross-reference with branch protection required_status_checks list, assert every non-required job is EITHER `continue-on-error: true` OR has a PR-trigger exclusion (no `pull_request` event in `on:` list). Anything else is flagged."
    - "Doc update: CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md \"Auto-merge rollup-FAILURE trap\" section (added in INFRA-1342) gets a sentence pointing at this audit gap and the smoke test for ongoing enforcement."
    - "Out of scope: required-checks list editing (a separate ops decision); third-party CI (codecov, etc.) — only owned workflows."
  closed_date: '2026-05-15'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1349
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: target/ artifact reaper — prune cargo build dirs in stale worktrees when disk > 80%"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Existing worktree-prune (INFRA-1347) deletes whole worktrees only when stale. While a PR is in-flight, the worktree's target/ dir lives forever and consumes 5-8GB each. With 254 worktrees in /private/tmp/, the math doesn't work — disk hit 97% today. Build artifacts are reproducible; they should auto-prune when disk pressure exceeds threshold OR when the worktree's last build is > N hours old. Independent of full worktree deletion (which requires uncommitted/unpushed checks per INFRA-1347).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/coord/target-dir-reaper.sh scans /private/tmp/chump-* + .claude/worktrees/*/target
    - Deletes target/ dirs in worktrees idle > 6h when free-disk < 20% (configurable thresholds via env)
    - Emits kind=target_artifact_reaped to ambient with {path, freed_gb, worktree_age_h}
    - Skip if worktree has active lease
    - launchd plist scripts/plists/dev.chump.target-reaper.plist runs every 30 min
    - Smoke test scripts/ci/test-target-dir-reaper.sh
    - docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md updated under disk-hygiene section
  depends_on: [INFRA-1347]
  closed_pr: 2083
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

