  effort: xs
  description: |
    INFRA-484 ALREADY auto-stages docs/gaps/<id>.yaml after chump gap reserve. The bug isn't missing auto-stage — it's that auto-stage runs in the worktree where reserve was invoked. Today's cascade (PR #2063 killed by orphan-closer): I ran 'chump gap reserve' from session worktree A, yaml auto-staged in A, but pushed PRs from worktree B. The yamls never made the PR commits → orphan-closer couldn't see them. Required 2 rescue PRs (#2071, #2077) to staple them into main. The fix: chump gap reserve should ALSO write the yaml to the main repo's docs/gaps/ (regardless of cwd), so any worktree's next pull picks it up. OR: emit a clear warning when the current worktree's HEAD branch is NOT the operator's likely shipping branch.
