- id: INFRA-1377
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: enable GitHub Merge Queue, deprecate gh pr merge --auto — kills convoy CI thrash (~800 min/hr wasted right now on cancelled runs)"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    Observed 2026-05-15: 30 PRs auto-armed simultaneously, last 8 completed CI runs ALL cancelled, ~800 CI-min/hr burned with zero ships. Root cause is the standard GitHub auto-merge mechanism: every main-bump cascades a merge-back into all open PRs, restarting their CI. Merge Queue serializes — PRs queue, CI runs once against the target merge state, no cross-PR invalidation. This is GitHub's first-party fix for exactly this convoy pattern. Highest-leverage single-change in the entire CI cleanup arc. PAIRS with INFRA-1378 (cancel-in-progress) for belt-and-suspenders.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Enable GitHub Merge Queue on main branch via GH branch-protection API (or web UI): gh api repos/repairman29/chump/branches/main/protection --method PUT with required_pull_request_reviews.merge_queue.enabled=true"
    - Convert scripts/coord/bot-merge.sh and chump gap claim flow to use `gh pr merge --merge-queue` (or equivalent gh-api call) instead of `gh pr merge --auto`
    - Branch-protection drift gate (existing) updated to assert merge_queue.enabled stays true
    - CI test scripts/ci/test-merge-queue-armed.sh asserts merge-queue is enabled for main and that one fresh PR enters the queue (mocked or live)
    - docs/process/MERGE_QUEUE.md (new) documents the operator flow + how to bypass to direct-merge for emergency fixes
    - "Measure: ambient counter of \"cancelled CI runs in last 24h\" before vs after — expect >80% drop"
  closed_date: '2026-05-16'
  closed_pr: 2146
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1378
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: add concurrency.cancel-in-progress to every workflow — old CI dies instantly on re-push, saves the 17-23min burn-then-cancel cycle (~20 cancelled runs in last hour)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Observed: ~20 cancelled CI runs in last hour, each burning 17-23 min before timing out. With cancel-in-progress, the moment a PR receives a new commit (incl auto-merge bot main-merge) the previous run dies in seconds. Cheap belt-and-suspenders alongside INFRA-1377 Merge Queue. Single-line YAML addition per workflow. Total surface: ~10 files, ~5 lines each. Highest leverage-per-line in the whole CI cleanup arc.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Per-PR runner-burner workflows have a DEADLOCK-SAFE concurrency block: pull_request keyed by PR number (cancellable), push/merge_group/schedule keyed by run_id (never cancelled, so the merge_group required check is safe). ci.yml + integrations.yml done."
    - "DONE: integrations.yml (the remaining per-PR burner) gets the deadlock-safe concurrency block (PR #3015). ci.yml already had it."
    - "Follow-up: scripts/ci/test-workflow-cancel-in-progress.sh asserting every pull_request-triggered workflow has a deadlock-safe concurrency block (release/build/nightly excluded), + branch-protection drift flag."
  notes: |
    DONE via PR #3015 (integrations.yml). Scope correction: the two HEAVY per-PR
    workflows are ci.yml (already had cancel-in-progress) and integrations.yml (the
    remaining burner — runs on pull_request with NO concurrency block, ~11min/run).
    #3015 closes that gap. The other cancel-in-progress:NO workflows are
    nightly/weekly/release (cargo-audit-nightly, ci-nightly, build-ci-image,
    release-plz, …) — blanket-adding cancel-in-progress there is WRONG (must not
    cancel a release or image build mid-flight), so "every workflow" is intentionally
    NOT taken literally.
    AC CORRECTION (the AC predates INFRA-2452): the prescribed group key
    `${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}` is DEADLOCK-UNSAFE — it cancels
    merge_group runs, fails the required check, and wedges every merge. The shipped
    pattern keys pull_request on PR-number (cancellable) and push/merge_group/schedule
    on the unique run_id (never cancels). Follow-up filed for the test + drift-gate.
  closed_pr: 3015
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

