  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Most PR failures fail unit tests (logic bugs, type errors, fmt). Integration tests run anyway on a known-broken PR, wasting ~10min. Tiering: fast tier (lib/bins unit, ~2-3min) runs first; slow tier (integration tests, ~10-15min) skips when fast fails. Faster failure feedback for the operator AND saves CI minutes on broken-PR cycles. Cleanest as a Cargo workspace split since most integration tests already live in tests/*.rs files which the --tests flag exclusively targets.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Split cargo-test job in ci.yml into cargo-test-fast (unit tests only, --lib + --bins, no --tests) and cargo-test-slow (integration --tests in tests/ + crates/*/tests/)
