- id: INFRA-1392
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: state.db status only flips on PROOF-OF-MERGE (local main commit OR webhook merged=true) — kills today's INFRA-1368/1363 stale-status churn WITHOUT coupling ground truth to GitHub"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today INFRA-1368 and INFRA-1363 were both marked status=done in state.db within minutes of being filed — sibling claim flipped status before the PRs actually merged. Caused me to abandon claim attempts and burn worktree-create cycles on already-done gaps. The right pattern: webhook receives merged=true event, then and only then flips state.db. Webhook plumbing already exists (smee+receiver+sqlite). Just wire pull_request.merged → gap_store.mark_shipped.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Root-cause reframe (Chief of Product, 2026-05-16): the original spec said 'webhook is the only authority'. That fix breaks docs/design/OFFLINE_FIRST.md — Pi mesh and airplane deployments have no webhook. The actual bug is that 'chump claim' or some adjacent path flips status to done before the work has landed anywhere. Fix that bug without inverting the offline mission."
    - "state.db is canonical and remains so in offline mode. Two equivalent proofs of merge are accepted: PROOF_LOCAL_MERGE = a commit on the local main branch whose subject or body references the gap ID (chump-ship trailer or 'gap: <ID>' line); PROOF_WEBHOOK = a github_webhook_event row with action=closed AND merged=true matching the gap ID via PR title or commit trailer."
    - chump claim no longer mutates gap status. Period. Claiming creates a worktree + lease + NATS reservation, nothing else. Status remains open until a PROOF_* arrives.
    - "chump gap ship enforces proof: refuses to flip status=done unless one of (a) PROOF_LOCAL_MERGE found via 'git log main --grep=<ID>' since last status change, (b) PROOF_WEBHOOK row exists in state.db, (c) explicit operator override --bypass --reason '<text>' (writes audit row to gap_status_overrides table with operator, reason, timestamp)."
    - "Schema: add gap_proof_of_merge table (gap_id, kind ENUM(local_merge,webhook,operator_bypass), evidence_ref TEXT, recorded_at TIMESTAMP). gap_store.mark_shipped REQUIRES at least one row in this table for the gap before flipping status. ALTER existing gaps with closed_pr set: backfill kind=webhook,evidence_ref=closed_pr."
