- id: INFRA-1435
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: chump gap consolidate --apply mode — auto-close higher-ID dup, re-point depends_on references, emit kind=gap_dup_archived"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump gap consolidate today is read-only (advisory). Add --apply mode that mechanically resolves clear-cut dups so the operator doesn't manually 'chump gap set X --status done' for each one (tax I paid today on INFRA-1268).
    - "Apply policy: keep the LOWER gap ID, archive the higher. Rationale: lower ID is older, has more depends_on backlinks, more likely to be cited externally."
    - "For each pair above --threshold (default 90 in --apply mode, stricter than the 80 advisory default): (1) close the higher ID with status=done, notes='duplicate of <lower-id>; auto-archived by chump gap consolidate --apply' and CHUMP_BYPASS_CLOSED_PR_GUARD=1; (2) rewrite any depends_on entries pointing at the higher ID across all open gaps to point at the lower ID; (3) emit ambient kind=gap_dup_archived {kept_id, archived_id, similarity_score}."
    - "--apply requires --reason '<text>' and writes an audit row to gap_dup_archive_audit (kept_id, archived_id, score, reason, operator, ts). Defensive: refuses to act if any active lease exists on either gap."
    - "--dry-run shows what --apply would do without mutation (default in non-CI; --apply implies --no-dry-run)."
    - "JSON output mode: emits {pairs:[{kept,archived,score,depends_on_rewrites:[]}]} for downstream automation."
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-consolidate-apply.sh: seed 2 dup pairs in state.db; run --apply --reason 'test'; assert higher IDs status=done, depends_on rewritten, audit rows present, ambient events emitted."
    - "Daily cron via existing scheduled-tasks infra: chump gap consolidate --apply --reason 'daily-auto-sweep' at 03:00 local with threshold 95 (only act on near-identical pairs)."
  closed_date: '2026-05-16'
  closed_pr: 2199
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1436
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: semantic-similarity option for gap dedup — local embeddings over title+description+AC (offline-compliant per OFFLINE_COMPLIANCE_RUBRIC)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Today's class-of-bug (Chief of Product, 2026-05-16): three gaps got rescoped because they framed the same intent in different titles (INFRA-1392 'webhook only' vs the local-equivalent path; INFRA-1405 'pull_request.synchronize webhook' vs local-push-hook). Lexical Jaccard on titles missed all three. Add a semantic-similarity option that catches different-titled-same-intent gaps."
    - "Embedding source: use the existing local embeddings module (src/lesson_embeddings.rs or src/memory_brain_tool depending on which is the canonical one). MUST work in CHUMP_LOCAL_ONLY=1 / CHUMP_GITHUB_MODE=offline (per OFFLINE_COMPLIANCE_RUBRIC.md §1 — this is a 'required' offline_class)."
    - Embed (title + first 500 chars of description + first AC item) for every open + recently-closed gap; cache embeddings in state.db with content-hash invalidation. Re-embed only on AC/title/description change.
    - chump gap reserve gains --semantic-check (default OFF in v1, evaluate before enabling by default). When enabled, computes cosine similarity of the proposed gap against the cached set; warn at 0.85, block at 0.95.
    - chump gap consolidate gains --semantic flag that reports near-dup pairs by cosine, side-by-side with Jaccard. Output shows both scores so operator can judge whether semantic sim is firing on real dups vs same-domain-different-feature.
    - "Performance budget: <500ms for the reserve-time check on a registry of 500 open gaps (M4 Mac with the local model). If exceeded, fall back to Jaccard with a warning event kind=semantic_check_too_slow."
    - "Failure-class: TRANSIENT={local_model_loading} → fall back to Jaccard, emit kind=semantic_check_degraded; PERMANENT={no_local_model_available_and_no_anthropic_key} → fall back to Jaccard with one-time operator nudge; DEGRADED={embeddings_cache_stale} → re-embed in background, use Jaccard for this call."
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-gap-semantic-similarity.sh: seed 5 pairs (3 lexical-different-semantic-same, 2 lexical-similar-semantic-different); assert semantic catches the first 3, Jaccard catches the last 2; both methods run in <2s on the test fixture."
    - "Pairs with INFRA-1418 (offline-check linter): both run at chump gap reserve. Order: offline-check first (cheap regex), semantic check second (slower embeddings). Both must pass for reserve to proceed."
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

