- id: INFRA-1473
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: shared memory team-vector-space for cross-agent context propagation"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Team-tier ($49/operator/month) headline feature missed in 2026-05-15 audit pass. Persona-1 (Marcus) named this explicitly as one of two reasons to swipe the Team-tier card: 'If Agent 3 discovers a hyper-specific quirk about how our legacy database handles an indexing edge case, and that context gets instantly committed to a shared team vector space, the next guy on my team running a fleet doesn't have to suffer through the same failure mode.' Without this, the $49 tier is just a paid solo tier — the commercial value prop falls apart.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Each agent's discoveries during a fleet run (gotchas, dead-ends, useful patterns, failure modes) are captured as structured 'context-nuggets' to a team-scoped store
    - Context-nuggets are embedded + queryable; subsequent agent runs on the same repo (different operator, different week) retrieve relevant nuggets via semantic similarity before starting work
    - Operator can browse, edit, and delete nuggets via chump --web cockpit (team-mind view)
    - "Privacy boundary: nuggets stay within a team scope; one team's nuggets do not leak to another team's fleet"
    - "Store backend pluggable: local SQLite for solo trial, hosted vector store for Team-tier subscribers (operator chooses)"
    - "CI test: fleet A runs against repo, hits a failure mode, commits a nugget; fleet B (different operator) running similar work retrieves the nugget and reports having read it before starting"
    - Documented schema for nugget shape — repo-scoped, gap-derived, agent-attributed, timestamped
    - "Hosted vector store backend: encrypted at rest (AES-256), TLS in transit, SOC 2 Type II posture targeted by launch; per-team row-level isolation enforced at DB layer not just application layer"
    - Operator/customer can request data export + deletion (GDPR-aligned); configurable retention windows; default 30-day on telemetry, indefinite on operator-flagged keeper-nuggets
    - "SecOps procurement doc: data-flow diagram showing exactly which fields leave operator machine and which stay local"
  notes: |
    MARCUS M-D (Team-tier substrate). P1 retained 2026-05-16. Reason #1 to swipe Team-tier card. Depends on M-A trust gate + M-B canonical demo landing first or value-prop is invisible.
  closed_date: '2026-05-29'
  closed_pr: 2337
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

