- id: INFRA-1478
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: offload-ready 5-minute onboarding for remote dedicated machine"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    Audit miss from 2026-05-15. Persona-1 dealbreaker: 'Give us a dead-simple way to point Chump away from our individual laptops and toward a dedicated, high-spec local Linux box or an internal team server — what you called a neural farm.' INFRA-1462 covers single-machine onboarding (180s chump init). This gap covers the OTHER side: chump init for the 'point my workers at a remote box' workflow. Architecturally exists via NATS push tier (FLEET-034) with WORKER_MACHINE env var, but is undocumented and not a smooth onboarding ramp.
