  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1479
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: flaky-test detection + retry-aware sandbox health check"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    Audit miss from 2026-05-15. Persona-1 Phase-2-graduation criteria: 'In a 35-engineer startup, our CI pipeline has flaky integration tests. If Chump fails a worktree because of a known flaky test, it needs the intelligence to recognize it, retry, or isolate it without wasting hours of compute or throwing a false alarm to the human supervisor.' Today an agent that hits a test failure has no concept of flake-vs-real; it commits the broken state, opens a PR, and operator manually sorts truth from noise. RESILIENT pillar because the value is preventing waste cycles + false-positive operator interrupts, not delivering a user-facing feature.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Agent's sandbox run-test wrapper detects test runs that fail then pass on retry within N attempts (default 3); marks those as 'flaky' rather than 'failed'
    - Repo-scoped flaky-test registry (sqlite or jsonl) that accumulates known-flaky test identifiers over multiple fleet runs
    - Subsequent agent runs read the registry; tests flagged as flaky get auto-retry budget and don't immediately fail the worktree
    - "Threshold: a test must flake at least K times across J fleet runs before being added to the registry (avoid spurious classification)"
    - Operator can browse + edit + reset the flaky registry via cockpit
    - chump fleet doctor reports flake rate per repo (% of failures that retry-passed) over rolling window
    - "CI test: synthetic flaky test that fails 50% of the time; verify agent retries, classifies, registers, and doesn't blow the worktree"
    - "Concurrency-class validation: when agent's diff touches async/concurrent code paths (Promise.all, channels, locks, AWS SDK batch ops, mutex/RwLock), sandbox runs a synthetic-load test before declaring worktree green — N concurrent invocations against changed code path, verify no memory growth, no duplicate processing, no resource leaks"
    - Concurrency-test heuristic-detection from file content + AST + operator hints in .chump/concurrency-validation.toml
    - "CI test: agent introduces a known closure-race-in-Promise.all bug (the Marcus SQS-batch-delete class); verify concurrency-validation catches it and fails the worktree before PR opens"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1480
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: SAST + dependency-vulnerability scan in agent sandbox before PR opens"
  status: open
  priority: P3
  effort: m
  description: |
    Audit miss from 2026-05-15. Persona-1 SecOps-sign-off section: 'The orchestrator passes all generated code through our local Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tools and dependency vulnerability scanners inside the sandbox before a human ever sees the diff.' Growth-tier ($149) trust commitment — agents catching their own security issues before opening PRs. CREDIBLE pillar because the value is auditor/SecOps confidence in the agent output, not raw feature delivery.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Agent sandbox includes hooks to run configured SAST tools (semgrep, bandit, gosec, etc — language-detected) on the diff before commit/push
    - Hooks include dependency-vulnerability scan (npm audit, cargo audit, pip-audit, etc) on any deps the agent added or bumped
    - "Findings: hard-fail the worktree (no PR opens) on HIGH/CRITICAL, log + report on MEDIUM/LOW"
    - Operator can configure SAST tool set and severity thresholds per repo (.chump/sast.toml)
    - "Findings reported to ambient.jsonl with kind=agent_sast_finding + severity + tool + file:line"
    - Documented integration with common operator SAST stacks (CodeQL, Snyk, Semgrep Cloud — at least references; deep integration is downstream)
    - "CI test: agent generates code with a known-vulnerable dep; verify SAST hook fails the worktree before PR opens; finding logged"
    - "Hallucinated-dependency detection: when agent adds a new dep, verify (a) package exists in canonical registry, (b) registered for ≥30 days, (c) download count above operator-configured minimum (default 1000)"
    - Hard-fail worktree on any hallucinated-dep check failure; emit ambient event kind=agent_hallucinated_dep with package name + which check failed
    - "Mitigates the AI Hallucination Poisoning attack vector (Marcus's SecOps concern): agent invents nonexistent package, attacker pre-registers it as malicious"
    - "CI test: agent introduces a dep named e.g. lodash-helper-2025 (nonexistent); verify check fires, worktree fails, ambient event emitted with correct payload"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1481
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: Growth-tier governance bundle (RBAC + spend caps + repo access control)"
  status: open
  priority: P3
  effort: l
  description: |
