- id: INFRA-1485
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: synchronous Command::output() in axum handlers starves tokio runtime — single hang kills ALL endpoints"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Real bug 2026-05-16: chump --web process alive (PID 15924, state SN) but ALL endpoints time out after probes hit /api/fleet-status (INFRA-1464) and /api/health/pillars (INFRA-1466). Root cause: those handlers use std::process::Command::output() which BLOCKS the tokio worker thread. Default tokio runtime has limited workers; a few blocked workers can wedge the whole server. Even /api/health stops responding after 2-3 minutes of probes. This is a SEVERITY MULTIPLIER on every other Command::output() call in src/web_server.rs.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Audit src/web_server.rs for every std::process::Command::output() call"
    - "Replace with tokio::process::Command + .output().await (non-blocking)"
    - "OR wrap in tokio::task::spawn_blocking to move off worker pool"
    - "Bonus: bound tokio worker count via Builder + add explicit timeout layer in axum router"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-server-survives-slow-endpoint.sh: hit /api/fleet-status with 100ms timeout, immediately hit /api/health, assert /api/health returns <500ms"
    - "Repro: with 25 leases, hit /api/fleet-status 3× concurrently, observe /api/health degrades to >5s"
  closed_date: '2026-05-16'
  closed_pr: 2211
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1486
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: per-gap agent execution budgets (wallclock, file-touches, dep-adds, LLM-cost)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Audit miss from 2026-05-15 second pass. Persona-1 (Marcus) described the Devin compounding-failure mode as the disqualifying behavior: 'By the time I checked back in after two hours, it had modified 14 different files, introduced three brand-new dependencies I would never allow in our codebase, and completely distorted the original intent of the feature. The code looked like Frankenstein monster.' Chump today has CHUMP_SUBAGENT_BOT_MERGE_BUDGET_S for one specific phase, but per-gap budgets across multiple dimensions (wallclock, file-touches, dep-adds, LLM-cost) are missing. This is the structural prevention for hallucination-compounding.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Per-gap budgets settable at claim time across 4 dimensions: max_wallclock_minutes (default 30), max_file_touches (default 10), max_dep_adds (default 0), max_llm_cost_usd (tier-derived: see AC #11)"
    - Defaults configurable per repo via .chump/budgets.toml
    - Budget tracked in real-time during agent run via ambient.jsonl events
    - Soft warning emitted at 75% of any budget; soft-pause (enables INFRA-1476 nudge) at 100%
    - "Operator-overridable: chump nudge --extend-budget <gap-id> <dimension> <new-limit>"
    - Aggregate budget tracking per fleet (across all in-flight gaps) — prevents weekend-API-bill-shock scenario Marcus described
    - chump fleet doctor reports per-repo budget-hit rate over rolling window
    - "CI test: agent in synthetic compounding-failure mode hits file-touch budget at 11 files, soft-pauses cleanly with the right ambient event"
    - "COST-ATTRIBUTION (folded from backlog item 2026-05-16): per-gap cost recorded in cost_tracker at close. Aggregate by (effort, domain) to a rolling median."
    - "TIER-DEFAULT POLICY: max_llm_cost_usd defaults to tier-derived budget: xs=$0.50/haiku, s=$2/haiku-then-sonnet, m=$5/sonnet, l=$20/sonnet-then-opus. Each gap inherits the budget for its effort."
    - "TIER ESCALATION: if agent stalls (no commit in N minutes OR same error 3×) on a tier, escalate to next tier. Emit kind=agent_model_tier_escalated {gap_id, from_tier, to_tier, reason}."
    - "CEILINGS NOT FLOORS: any gap can claim ANY tier; the budget caps how much it can spend. xs gap CAN run on opus if operator explicitly --tier opus, but $0.50 cap still applies — agent will halt fast."
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-tier-routing-escalation.sh: synthetic gap, force agent stall, assert tier escalates + ambient event emitted + budget remains within ceiling."
    - "Out of scope (separate gap if needed): historical cost re-rating after model price changes; cross-org cost pooling."
  notes: |
    MARCUS M-A (trust gate). Promoted P2→P0 2026-05-16: Marcus's stated disqualifying behavior (Frankenstein-monster compounding failure). All Marcus features downstream depend on this trust gate landing first. Without budgets, no operator will leave a fleet unattended.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2296
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

