    - "If prior session was a subagent (already exited) OR worker is dead: dispatch fresh agent with explicit handoff brief — 'You are inheriting <gap_id> from session <prior_id> (type: <worker"
    - "subagent>, last seen <T>). Prior PR: <#N>. Prior commit: <sha>. Prior fail class: <name>. Prior attempts: <count>. Start fresh — do NOT try to inherit worktree state.'"
    - Emit kind=claim_handed_off {gap, from_session, from_type, to_session, prior_outcome, handoff_brief_id} on transfer
    - Paramedic daemon (INFRA-1375) on rule 'pr stuck >N hours' fires CLAIM_HANDOFF action
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-claim-handoff-worker.sh: fixture worker with prior claim_history alive, assert continuation request emitted + worker claims within 30s"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-claim-handoff-subagent.sh: fixture subagent-prior-claim (exited), assert fresh dispatch with full handoff brief"
    - "Today's signal: 7 subagents dispatched without affinity tracking; any follow-up on their PRs went to a fresh subagent with no memory of prior attempt — wasteful re-work, sometimes regressed prior progress. Workers vs. subagents have fundamentally different lifecycle: workers stay alive across many gaps (paged via NATS), subagents are one-shot (only handoff-brief possible)"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

