    (c) Verify <chump-status-footer> already renders all four removed signals (per PRODUCT-107). If a slot is missing functionality (e.g. autopilot toggle), file a follow-up rather than blocking — the footer is the right home regardless.
    (d) Header CSS cleanup: remove now-orphan padding-bottom rules at index.html:117-123 for the removed elements.
    (e) INFRA-1276 (<=640px header overlap, P3) becomes auto-resolved — close it with a reference to this gap.
    (f) Playwright e2e/pwa-header-dedup.spec.ts: assert #app-header has ≤4 direct children at 1440px AND at 640px AND at 375px.
    
    Open design question (resolve in PR): does <chump-repo-switcher> stay in header, or move to CONFIG cadence? Header keeps it cheap to switch projects; CONFIG keeps the header truly minimal. Default to header; if the operator says move, do it in a follow-up.
    
