- id: INFRA-1593
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: PWA component inventory + design-system style guide — docs/design/PWA_STYLE_GUIDE.md with token reference, 32+ chump-* component inventory, composition rules, mobile breakpoints, a11y minimums"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    The PWA has competent design tokens (3 themes, WCAG-AAA high-contrast variant), ~32 chump-* web components, and a 4-cadence canvas — but none of this is documented as a system. OPERATOR_CONSOLE_V2.md describes the canvas at concept level; PWA_STATE_SCHEMA.md (INFRA-1280) documents persistence; nothing documents the visual + component vocabulary.
    
    Consequences observed:
    - New components (welcome.js, cockpit.js) invented their own tokens because there was no canonical reference to point them at.
    - Mobile breakpoint at 640px is implicit across many @media rules with no central definition.
    - Component composition rules (header vs footer vs view chrome vs floating overlay) are not stated anywhere — operators add new components in whatever slot looks free.
    - A11y minimums (contrast ratios, focus order, target sizes) are honored in places but not codified.
    
    This gap creates docs/design/PWA_STYLE_GUIDE.md as the single source of truth.
    
    Rough shape — sections to write:
    (a) Design tokens — table of every CSS variable in :root, [data-theme='light'], [data-theme='high-contrast']. Columns: variable name | dark value | light value | HC value | intended use. Pull verbatim from web/v2/index.html:14-64.
    (b) Component inventory — for each chump-* custom element in web/v2/, one row: tag name | source file | owns (what part of the UI) | introduced by (PRODUCT-/INFRA- ticket). Generator script scripts/dev/gen-pwa-component-inventory.sh greps customElements.define() across web/v2/*.js to keep this fresh.
    (c) Composition rules — when to put a new component in header vs footer vs view chrome vs floating overlay vs cadence sub-tab. Decision tree.
    (d) Mobile breakpoints — single table: 375px (iPhone narrow), 640px (mobile cap), 768px (tablet), 1024px (laptop narrow), 1440px (laptop wide). Each row: what changes at this breakpoint and why.
    (e) A11y minimums — contrast ratios (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large, 7:1 high-contrast variant), focus order rules, minimum target sizes (44x44 per Apple HIG, 48x48 per Material), prefers-reduced-motion handling, screen-reader landmarks expected.
    (f) Token-discipline rules — link to INFRA-1590's CSS_TOKEN_DISCIPLINE.md.
    (g) 'When to add a new component vs extend an existing one' — short decision tree (does it fit in an existing cadence/footer slot? does it duplicate existing data? is it cross-cutting? etc).
    (h) Anti-patterns — show + warn against: duplicate data displays (header + footer for same metric), modal overlays without escape key, color literals outside tokens, fixed-pixel widths in mobile media queries.
    
    Ownership: per project_doc_infrastructure memory, tech-writer agent (hourly) owns this doc after creation — it amends the inventory section as new components ship. Author the initial doc; tech-writer maintains.
    
    Wiring:
    - Link from CLAUDE.md 'On-demand docs' section.
    - Link from web/v2/README.md (if exists; create if not).
    - Reference from PR template: 'Touched web/v2/**? Did you check PWA_STYLE_GUIDE.md?'
    
    When picked, run chump gap decompose <ID>; this is mostly authorship work, single PR realistic if scope respected.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "docs/design/PWA_STYLE_GUIDE.md exists with 7 sections: tokens / inventory / composition rules / breakpoints / a11y / token-discipline link / when-to-add-component"
    - "Token table populated verbatim from web/v2/index.html :root + theme overrides (dark/light/HC values for every variable)"
    - Component inventory lists every chump-* element with source file + owns + introduced-by ticket
    - scripts/dev/gen-pwa-component-inventory.sh greps customElements.define() to keep inventory fresh
    - Composition rules state where new components go (header vs footer vs view chrome vs floating)
    - Mobile breakpoint table covers 375/640/768/1024/1440 with semantics per breakpoint
    - "A11y minimums section: contrast ratios + focus + target sizes + prefers-reduced-motion + landmarks"
    - Anti-patterns section calls out duplicate data displays + modal-without-escape + color literals outside tokens
    - Linked from CLAUDE.md 'On-demand docs' section
    - "PR template addition: 'Touched web/v2/**? Style guide checked?'"
    - Tech-writer agent prompt updated to maintain inventory section (per memory project_doc_infrastructure)
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

