- id: INFRA-1603
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: PWA hot-reload on PR merge — SSE event triggers service-worker invalidation + live component re-registration; operator watches canvas evolve without refresh"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today the operator opens the PWA, the fleet ships 4 PRs in the next hour, and the operator sees nothing change until they hit refresh. The fleet feels invisible. The 'stitching is the differentiator' thesis (per feedback_no_drafts_ship_and_stitch memory) says forward motion should be VISIBLE in real time, not hidden until next reload.
    
    This gap makes PR merges propagate to live operator PWA sessions in <5 seconds.
    
    Pipeline:
      GitHub webhook → existing scripts/ops/github-webhook-receiver.py
        → emit kind=pr_merged to ambient.jsonl (already partially wired)
        → web_server SSE channel /api/events broadcasts pr_merged event
        → PWA service worker (web/v2/sw.js) catches event
        → if merged PR touched web/v2/**: skipWaiting() + clients.claim() the new asset bundle
        → live component re-registration: dispatch custom event 'chump:component-updated' to all open clients
        → affected chump-* custom elements call this.connectedCallback() again (or full re-attach via remove + re-define + replaceWith)
    
    Rough shape:
    (a) Ensure github-webhook-receiver.py emits kind=pr_merged with {pr_number, head_sha, merged_files[], merged_at} to ambient.jsonl.
    (b) web_server SSE endpoint /api/events already streams ambient — verify it forwards pr_merged events to PWA clients (filter list may need update).
    (c) Update web/v2/sw.js to handle pr_merged: if merged_files contains web/v2/**, fetch /v2/manifest.json with cache-busting query, compare asset SHAs, skipWaiting() new SW + clients.claim() if changed.
    (d) Add web/v2/hot-reload.js module: listens for SSE pr_merged, decides if reload is safe (no unsaved form state, no open modal), either auto-applies via componentscustom-element re-registration OR shows a non-modal banner 'New version live — [reload]'.
    (e) Per-component reload-safety opt-in: chump-* components declare static get reloadSafe() { return true; } if they can hot-swap; default false means show banner.
    (f) Telemetry: emit kind=pwa_hot_reload_applied {pr_number, components_swapped[]} to ambient on success; kind=pwa_hot_reload_deferred {reason} when blocked.
    (g) Smoke test scripts/ci/test-pwa-hot-reload.sh: spin up fixture web server, simulate pr_merged SSE event, assert reload triggered in headless browser within 5s.
    (h) docs/process/PWA_HOT_RELOAD.md: how the pipeline works, how to mark a component reload-safe, debug commands.
    
    Composes with INFRA-1198 (ambient viewer) — same SSE channel. Composes with PRODUCT-094 (notification center) — banner UX can reuse those primitives. Composes with INFRA-1591 (visual snapshots) — hot-reload safety verified by snapshot baselines.
    
    When picked, run chump gap decompose <ID>.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - github-webhook-receiver.py emits kind=pr_merged with {pr_number, head_sha, merged_files[], merged_at}
    - SSE /api/events forwards pr_merged events to PWA clients
    - "web/v2/sw.js handles pr_merged: cache-bust manifest, skipWaiting+clients.claim if asset SHAs changed"
    - web/v2/hot-reload.js module listens for SSE pr_merged and either auto-reloads OR shows non-modal 'New version live' banner
    - "Per-component opt-in: static get reloadSafe() { return true; } default false→banner"
    - kind=pwa_hot_reload_applied + kind=pwa_hot_reload_deferred ambient events emitted
    - "scripts/ci/test-pwa-hot-reload.sh end-to-end test: simulated PR merge → headless browser reload within 5s"
    - docs/process/PWA_HOT_RELOAD.md documents pipeline + reload-safe opt-in + debug
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1604
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: deepen claim-collision detection beyond INFRA-1394 — full path-set intersection of lease.paths[] instead of 5-hot-file AC-scan; supports globs + directory overlap"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    INFRA-1394 shipped a claim-collision check that:
    - Hardcodes 5 hot files (ci.yml, EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml, web_server.rs, app.js, main.rs) in scripts/coord/lib/hot-files.yaml
    - Parses the gap's AC TEXT for any reference to those files
    - Warns + requires --force-overlap if found
    
    That catches the worst cases but misses the long tail. Real collisions happen on dozens of files, not 5; and they're declared in the lease's paths[] field (per INFRA-1240), not in AC text. The check should compute the actual set intersection of {new claim's paths} ∩ {each active lease's paths} — which is what the lease system was designed for.
    
    Today's shape (INFRA-1394) is heuristic. This gap makes it structural.
    
    Rough shape:
    (a) chump claim, after computing the new lease's paths[] (from --paths CLI or from auto-detection per INFRA-1240), reads all sibling .chump-locks/claim-*.json files and extracts each sibling's paths[].
    (b) For each sibling lease, compute intersection of new paths and sibling paths. Globs and directory prefixes count: 'src/foo/*.rs' overlaps 'src/foo/bar.rs'; 'docs/' overlaps 'docs/gaps/X.yaml'.
    (c) Helper crate or inline impl: scripts/coord/lib/path-overlap.sh OR a Rust helper in crates/chump-coord (preferred per META-064 Rust-first rule — this is hot-path lease infra).
    (d) If overlap detected: surface ALL overlapping paths + the sibling session_id/gap_id; print one line per collision; require --force-overlap to proceed.
    (e) Existing INFRA-1394 hot-file AC-scan stays as a SECONDARY check (defense in depth — catches the case where lease paths[] is incomplete).
    (f) Emit kind=lease_path_collision {claim_gap, sibling_gap, overlap_paths[], paths_count} to ambient.jsonl on every detection (warning OR bypass). Existing kind=claim_hot_file_overlap stays for the AC-text path.
    (g) Test scripts/ci/test-deep-claim-collision.sh: synthesize 3 sibling leases with overlapping path globs, attempt to claim a gap with a 4th path set, assert detection + correct exit code with/without --force-overlap.
    (h) Update docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md 'Linked worktree git path confusion' adjacent section to describe the deep collision check.
    
    This is what the 'pre-claim file-conflict prediction' stitching primitive should be — making parallel shipping safer by surfacing the actual file-graph collision BEFORE both workers spend an hour on conflicting work.
    
    When picked, run chump gap decompose <ID>.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump claim reads sibling lease paths[] (not just hardcoded hot-file list) and computes set intersection
    - "Glob + directory-prefix overlap detection: 'src/foo/*.rs' overlaps 'src/foo/bar.rs'; 'docs/' overlaps 'docs/gaps/X.yaml'"
    - Helper lives in crates/chump-coord (Rust-first per META-064) OR scripts/coord/lib with Rust-First-Bypass trailer
    - Overlap detection prints all overlapping paths + sibling session_id/gap_id; one line per collision
    - "--force-overlap flag bypasses; existing INFRA-1394 AC-text-scan stays as secondary defense-in-depth check"
    - Emit kind=lease_path_collision ambient event with {claim_gap, sibling_gap, overlap_paths[], paths_count}
    - "scripts/ci/test-deep-claim-collision.sh: 3 sibling leases with glob overlap, 4th claim detection, exit codes correct with/without --force-overlap"
    - docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md updated to describe the deep collision check
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1605
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: PR-bot visual-diff comments on every PWA PR — GitHub Action runs INFRA-1591 snapshot suite + posts screenshot diffs as PR comment (audience: design collaborators / external reviewers like Marcus)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Once INFRA-1591 lands the visual snapshot suite, the natural next step is to MAKE THE DIFFS VISIBLE in code review without the reviewer having to clone + run anything. The operator (Jeff) may not need to inspect every screenshot — but external collaborators (Marcus, future design reviewers, ultrareview operators) absolutely benefit from seeing the visual delta inline on the PR.
    
    Stitching pattern: bring the operator's eye to the PR, not the PR to the operator's eye.
    
    Rough shape:
    (a) .github/workflows/pwa-visual-diff.yml — triggers on PRs touching web/v2/**.
    (b) Runs INFRA-1591 snapshot suite against the PR branch.
    (c) For each baseline that diffs > 0% (regardless of whether it crosses the CI-failure 0.5% threshold):
        - Render a side-by-side image: baseline + PR-version + diff overlay
        - Upload as a PR-attached artifact OR to a per-PR S3-like store (use GitHub's own pull-request comment attachment if available)
    (d) Post a single PR comment via gh api with markdown table:
        | View | Viewport | Pixel delta | Diff |
        | NOW | 1440px | 2.3% | ![diff](url) |
    (e) Update existing comment on subsequent PR pushes (don't spam).
    (f) Comment includes a footer: 'Re-baseline locally: npx playwright test e2e/pwa-visual --update-snapshots. Visual review: <link to artifact bundle>'.
    (g) Failure mode: if snapshot infra not yet wired (INFRA-1591 not landed), action no-ops with a warning comment ('Visual diff bot waiting on INFRA-1591').
    (h) docs/process/PWA_VISUAL_DIFF_BOT.md describes the action + how to read the comment + how to add a new view to the diff set.
    
    Composes with INFRA-1591 (snapshots — strict dep). Pairs naturally with ultrareview workflow per CLAUDE.md (ultrareview is operator-triggered cloud review; this is automatic per-PR visual diff).
    
    When picked, run chump gap decompose <ID>.
    
    DEPENDS_ON: INFRA-1591 (snapshot suite must exist).
