- id: INFRA-1606
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: PWA AMBIENT cadence live-diff stream panel — last N commits with semantic-aware diff summaries, real-time SSE feed; the fleet becomes visible to the operator"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    The fleet currently ships 80+ PRs/24h. The operator can see this in git log, gh pr list, the ambient.jsonl stream, the bot-merge logs — but nowhere in the PWA. Each surface is a different shape: git log is hashes, gh pr list is metadata, ambient is events. None is 'here is the codebase EVOLVING, right now.'
    
    This gap makes that visible. The fleet stops feeling like background noise and starts feeling like the alive coordination layer it actually is.
    
    Pairs with INFRA-1603 (hot-reload PWA on PR merge): hot-reload makes the operator's PWA evolve; live-diff stream makes the codebase evolution itself visible.
    
    Rough shape:
    (a) New endpoint /api/codebase-stream (Rust, src/web_server.rs): SSE stream emitting one event per merged PR (replay last N=50 on connect). Each event: {pr_number, title, sha, merged_at, files_changed[], net_lines, gap_id_if_any, pillar_if_any, one_line_semantic_summary}.
    (b) Semantic summary v1: heuristic — pick from PR title (strip the gap-prefix), file-class summary ('5 src/, 2 tests/, 1 docs/'). v2: LLM-generated 8-word summary cached per-PR. v1 ships; v2 is a follow-up.
    (c) Backend feed source: github-webhook-receiver.py (already lands pr_merged events) + replay from gh api on cold start.
    (d) New PWA component <chump-view-codebase-stream> placed in AMBIENT cadence as a sub-tab (per docs/design/OPERATOR_CONSOLE_V2.md §AMBIENT — 'live event tail + filtered fleet state').
    (e) Visual treatment: chronological list, newest top, each row collapsible. Click expands to: full file list, gap card (if gap_id known), pillar grade context. Animate in new rows with subtle fade (respect prefers-reduced-motion).
    (f) Filter chips: pillar / domain (INFRA/PRODUCT/META) / file-type (touched web/v2/** vs not) / 'mine' (PRs the operator authored vs fleet workers).
    (g) 'Codebase evolved' counter top-right: 'N commits in last 24h / Mh / Mm' — matches the fleet brief stats Jeff gets at session-start.
    (h) ACP-style click-through: every row has [open commit in editor] (chump://acp/open?sha=X — composes with PRODUCT-110 ACP deeplinks).
    (i) Smoke test: scripts/ci/test-pwa-codebase-stream.sh — fixture web server with 5 synthetic merged PRs, asserts SSE delivers 5 events in order, PWA renders them in correct sort, filter chips work.
    
    Marketing value: this is a screenshot-worthy demo of the 'fleet of agents shipping in parallel' thesis. Today the demo is 'look at this CLI'. With this view, the demo is 'look at the codebase moving.'
    
    When picked, run chump gap decompose <ID>.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - /api/codebase-stream SSE endpoint emits one event per merged PR with full schema (pr_number, title, sha, merged_at, files_changed[], net_lines, gap_id, pillar, summary)
    - Replays last N=50 events on connect
    - <chump-view-codebase-stream> renders in AMBIENT cadence as a sub-tab per OPERATOR_CONSOLE_V2.md
    - Newest-top chronological list, each row collapsible with file list + gap card + pillar grade context
    - "Filter chips: pillar / domain / file-type (web/v2/** vs not) / mine"
    - "'Codebase evolved' counter top-right: N commits / Mh / Mm window"
    - Each row has ACP deeplink [open commit in editor] composing with PRODUCT-110
    - Semantic summary v1 = heuristic (PR title + file-class breakdown); LLM-summary follow-up filed for v2
    - Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
    - "scripts/ci/test-pwa-codebase-stream.sh: 5 synthetic PRs round-tripped through SSE → PWA render → filter chip"
    - Visual snapshot baseline added to INFRA-1591 suite
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

