    chump-brain/ is gitignored (correctly — it is per-host learning state). But this means newly-installed fleets start with an empty brain and the orchestrator-instruction "create skills from successful patterns" produces nothing for weeks until enough patterns accumulate. Today 2026-05-17 chump-brain/skills/ on the operator host has 3 prototype skills (verify-existence, claim-without-collision, pre-ship-ci-prediction) drafted from session-observed pain. They live at skills-bundle/<name>/SKILL.md in the repo (committed, not gitignored). Need: chump init (or chump skill bundle install) copies skills-bundle/* into chump-brain/skills/ on a fresh install. Each install starts with operator-curated baseline curriculum instead of zero.
