- id: INFRA-1620
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P0: PWA web/v2/app.js has been syntactically broken on origin/main since 2026-05-14 (commit c64ddd676) — 5 classes truncated with missing closing braces; PWA fails to parse with 'Private field must be declared in enclosing class' error"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Root cause: commit c64ddd676 (PRODUCT-111 PWA <chump-view-audit>) and subsequent PRs (PRODUCT-112 network audit, INFRA-1203 fleet-health, INFRA-1204 coord, INFRA-1207 roadmap) shipped class bodies that are truncated mid-method or mid-template-literal with missing closing braces. JS parser fails at the first private-field reference (this.#escAttr line 2059) because the enclosing class never closed. All 5 classes are affected."
    - "Acute mitigation already applied 2026-05-17: web/v2/app.js reverted locally to 5a92978b3 (PRODUCT-113 pre-truncation, 3613 lines vs 5192 truncated). PWA parses + works for the ~16 view-classes that landed before the breakage. Reversion is LOCAL only (not committed); next git pull will restore the broken file."
    - "Permanent fix: rebuild the 5 truncated classes from their original PR diffs. Likely candidates: re-extract each class body from #2000 (PRODUCT-111), #2020 (PRODUCT-112), #2023 (INFRA-1203), #2021 (INFRA-1204), #2025 (INFRA-1207) and re-apply with full closing braces. OR rewrite each minimally to satisfy its acceptance contract."
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-pwa-app-js-parses.sh: run 'node --check web/v2/app.js'; exit non-zero on syntax error. Wired into pr-hygiene job so future truncations bounce at PR time."
    - "Cross-link: 2026-05-17 operator hit the parse error on first PWA load. The class boundary at line 2070 (post this.#load(); missing }} before next class) is the canonical seam — likely all 5 truncations share the same authoring mistake (forgot to close before next class definition)."
  notes: |
    ROOT CAUSE (diagnosed 2026-06-20): bad merge in e716c909e (PRODUCT-112 #2020, 2026-05-14) — NOT c64ddd676. c64ddd676 added ChumpViewAudit WELL-FORMED (258 self-contained lines, own #esc/#escAttr/#shortSession, with its customElements.define). The very next app.js commit e716c909e (+211/-2) mis-ordered the merge hunks: it truncated ChumpViewAudit's innerHTML template mid-content and interleaved the 5 view classes' bodies. node --check fails at the first orphaned private-field use (this.#escAttr in ChumpViewAudit's connectedCallback) because that class's helper defs got relocated. The 4 later classes (NetworkAudit/e716c909e, Roadmap/601e2adf2, FleetHealth/3d0b689b5, Coord/8525de0f5) were all added on the already-broken base, so NO single ancestor commit has all 5 well-formed. CURRENT STATE: 5 classes open at lines 2121/2181/2244/2325/2730; their methods+helpers are jumbled+duplicated (two each of #load/#render/#renderRow/#export/#esc) in the 2333-2935 pile; all 5 customElements.define calls DO exist (clustered 2937-3130). RESTORATION RECIPE: (1) Audit = restore the 258-line clean block from c64ddd676:web/v2/app.js. (2-5) NetworkAudit/FleetHealth/Coord/Roadmap = reassemble each from its feature-commit diff +lines (e716c909e/3d0b689b5/8525de0f5/601e2adf2). (6) Replace the tangled region lines 2121..(before define cluster) with the 5 well-formed blocks in order; keep/dedupe the 5 defines. (7) Verify: node --check web/v2/app.js exits 0. SCOPE: ~800 lines, focused reconstruction — too large/delicate for a loop-tick (band-aid risk). Sibling P0 EVAL-125 is the same bug; close both on ship.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 3135
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

