  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Self-hosted M4 runners (jeffs-macbook-air-10-2/-10-3/etc.) failed actions/checkout@v6 repeatedly in <30s during the 2026-05-20 Marcus cron-loop session. Master kill-switch was flipped (CHUMP_SELF_HOSTED_ENABLED=false) + 5 RUNNER_* lane-vars deleted to bypass; all CI is now on ubuntu-latest, M4 hardware idle. Need root cause before flipping back, else next push hits the same flake.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Reproduce the <30s actions/checkout@v6 failure on jeffs-macbook-air-10-X
    - Identify root cause (disk full / stale runner registration / network / queue contention)
    - Land fix OR document operational workaround in docs/process/SELF_HOSTED_RUNNERS.md
    - Re-enable CHUMP_SELF_HOSTED_ENABLED=true on master toggle; verify one full CI cycle passes
    - Restore RUNNER_AUDIT/COVERAGE/E2E_PWA/E2E_GOLDEN_PATH/TAURI_COWORK_E2E to ['self-hosted','macos-arm64','chump-fleet'] one lane at a time, watching for flake recurrence (use INFRA-1567 per-lane toggle)
    - Emit ambient kind=runner_health_restored on success
  notes: |
    FOLLOW-UP from 2026-05-20 Marcus cron-loop session. Discovery: 0-step CANCELLED failures recurring on jeffs-macbook-air-10-* runners specifically at actions/checkout@v6 step. Worked around by flipping all toggles off; that's a degraded mode (free M4 capacity idle). Per CLAUDE.md memory hardware-economics: hardware is paid; idle == waste.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1656
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: nightly main-health watchdog — file P0 gap on red main"
