  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1657
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: wire conflict-resolver-agent into bot-merge.sh rebase-failure path (closes INFRA-1488 loop)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    INFRA-1488 shipped scripts/coord/conflict-resolver-agent.sh default-OFF (CHUMP_CONFLICT_RESOLVER_ENABLED=1 to enable). But nothing calls it — bot-merge.sh still treats rebase conflict as terminal. Marcus's '45 min mental focus per PR rebase' time-sink only resolves if bot-merge dispatches the agent automatically.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - bot-merge.sh's rebase step detects conflict (exit code from git rebase != 0 with conflict markers present)
    - On conflict, invokes scripts/coord/conflict-resolver-agent.sh with GAP_ID env
    - If agent exits 0 (resolved + rebase --continued), bot-merge resumes normal flow
    - If agent exits 1 (handoff), bot-merge calls git rebase --abort + emits existing handoff path
    - Default behavior preserved when CHUMP_CONFLICT_RESOLVER_ENABLED!=1 (agent self-skips per its existing flag-gate)
    - "CI test: synthetic 2-file conflict + flag-on → verify dispatch invoked; flag-off → verify pass-through"
    - docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md adds note on enablement + rollback
  notes: |
    FOLLOW-UP from INFRA-1488 (Marcus M-C shipped 2026-05-21). Without this wiring, M-C is dead code-on-disk. Risk: low — agent is opt-in, fallback is current behavior.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2320
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1658
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: audit + fix printf|grep -q pipefail race across scripts/"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Yesterday's keystone unblocker fix in scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit-obs-budget.sh was a printf|grep -q pipefail race: under set -o pipefail, grep -q closes stdin early on first match, printf gets SIGPIPE → exit non-zero → pipeline reports failure even when the match was found. Spent 6 hours chasing false-negative obs-budget hits before locating it. Pattern likely repeats across scripts/.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - grep -rn 'printf.*
    - .*grep' scripts/ — produce candidate list
    - "For each match: assess (1) is set -o pipefail in effect, (2) does grep -q early-close cause the race, (3) is the script in a hot-path (called per-PR or per-cycle)"
    - Fix race-prone sites via tempfile materialization (the INFRA-755 fix pattern in pre-commit-obs-budget.sh as the model)
    - Add scripts/ci/test-pipefail-race-sweep.sh that re-greps and fails if new printf
    - grep -q in marked hot-path scripts
    - "Update docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md with the anti-pattern: under pipefail, never 'printf X "
    - " grep -q Y'; instead 'echo X > tmp; grep -q Y tmp'"
  notes: |
    FOLLOW-UP from INFRA-755 fix 2026-05-20. The original race was in pre-commit-obs-budget.sh; INFRA-1658 sweeps for sibling occurrences. Hot-path candidates: any script in scripts/coord/, scripts/dispatch/, scripts/git-hooks/. xs-effort: grep, audit, fix ~3-5 sites.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2322
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

