- id: INFRA-1662
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: reap orphan claude subprocesses spawned by cron-loop firings"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Cron-loop 6249a56f ran for ~60h firing every ~12min; each firing spawned a fresh Claude Code subprocess (binary at ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude-code/2.1.138/claude.app/Contents/MacOS/claude) that never got reaped. By 2026-05-22 morning: 354 wedged claude processes pinning 8.5GB RAM, load average 262. SIGTERM didn't reach them (wedged); SIGKILL required. Cleanup was manual via ps + xargs kill -9.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Investigate Claude Code harness side: does it intend to leave claude-binary subprocesses running between cron firings? If yes, why?"
    - If unintended (harness bug), file upstream report with reproduction (cron-loop fires every 12m → claude binary count grows linearly)
    - "If intended (subscription-OAUTH session reuse), add Chump-side launchd-watchdog: every 1h, find claude-binary processes with same --plugin-dir signature older than 1h not in active session chain, SIGKILL"
    - Emit ambient kind=orphan_subprocess_reaped with count + age stats on each sweep
    - Register the kind in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    - "Hard cap: never kill processes whose ppid chain leads to the foreground Claude.app (PID 15517 pattern)"
    - "CI test: stub ps output with synthetic claude processes (1 fresh, 5 old), verify reaper kills exactly the 5 olds"
  notes: |
    DISCOVERED 2026-05-22 during mac-slowness diagnosis. Cron 6249a56f cancelled 2026-05-21; this gap is preventive for future autonomous loops (which will absolutely run again). Pairs with INFRA-NEW-stale-process-watchdog (below). Tier-1 risk: future autonomous runs lock the operator's machine within 24h without this guard.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2323
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1663
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: stale-process watchdog (rustc/chump health/any worker exceeding expected lifetime)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    2026-05-22 cleanup found 5 leaked rustc compilations alive for 1.5+ days (parent worker died, child kept running consuming CPU) and 2 leaked 'chump health --slo-check' invocations alive 11+ hours (should complete in seconds). Both classes are easy to detect by ps + etime comparison against an expected-lifetime table.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Define expected_lifetime table: rustc=10m, cargo=15m, chump health=2m, worker.sh=4h, bot-merge.sh=20m, run-fleet.sh=24h, others=1h default"
    - Daily launchd cron sweeps ps -Ao pid,etime,comm,user; flags any matching the table whose etime exceeds expected
    - SIGTERM with 30s grace, then SIGKILL
    - Emit ambient kind=stale_process_reaped per kill with comm/etime/expected/pid
    - Register kind in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    - "Bypass env: CHUMP_STALE_PROC_WATCHDOG=0 disables (operator override during legitimate long runs)"
    - "CI test: synthetic ps output with 2 stale + 1 fresh row, verify watchdog kills only the 2 stale"
    - Document in docs/process/SELF_HOSTED_RUNNERS.md operational section
  notes: |
    DISCOVERED 2026-05-22. Generalizes INFRA-1662 (which targets only claude-binary leaks). Cheap insurance: ~50 LOC bash + plist. P2 because INFRA-1662 covers the highest-frequency leak; this catches the long tail.
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2326
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

