- id: INFRA-1666
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: SessionStart hook misreports curator/state JSON in .chump-locks/ as leases — filter glob by session_id presence"
  status: superseded
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Bug: scripts/coord/ambient-context-inject.sh treats every .chump-locks/*.json file as a lease in the SessionStart digest. Reality (2026-05-22): the directory has 44 curator-filed-balance_restock_*.json audit files + 3 state JSON files (drift-alert-state, fleet-state, gap-priority) and 0 actual leases — the hook reports 47 phantom leases with session=? expires=? and a duplicated 'INFRA-1149' listing 41 times (the curator audit files carry gap_id=INFRA-1149 as their dedup match). Related: INFRA-1494 (zombie-lease reaper at fleet startup) addresses stale REAL leases; this gap addresses non-lease JSON files being misclassified. Fix shape: in scripts/coord/ambient-context-inject.sh Python digest (lines ~265-275), add 'if not data.get("session_id"): continue' before appending to leases list. Two-line change in Python plus one CI test fixture.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - ambient-context-inject.sh Python digest filters lock_dir.glob('*.json') to only files whose parsed JSON has a non-empty 'session_id' field; non-lease files (curator-filed-*, fleet-state.json, gap-priority.json, drift-alert-state.json) are excluded from 'active leases' count and 'Active sibling leases' render block
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-ambient-context-inject-non-lease-files.sh creates a fixture .chump-locks/ with one real lease + 3 curator-filed-style JSON + 2 state-style JSON and asserts the rendered context contains 'active leases: 1' (not 6)"
    - "fresh SessionStart hook fire (after fix) shows correct count: 0 leases when none claimed, n leases when n live claims exist"
    - no regression to existing tests scripts/ci/test-session-start-emit.sh + scripts/ci/test-ambient-glance.sh
  notes: |
    duplicate of INFRA-1664 (already fixed in PR #2307, merged 2026-05-22 09:53). Local main was 9 commits behind origin/main when I filed this; the stale SessionStart hook showed 47 phantom leases because the fix had not been pulled yet. Lesson: pre-flight fetch was incomplete during diagnosis; should have inspected origin/main before filing. Cross-ref: INFRA-1664 + INFRA-1661 (lessons doc PR #2306 already documented this).
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1667
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: opus-curator daemon real-run exit_code 5 every 10min — dry-run exits 0, post-decision phase fails under set -euo pipefail"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Symptom: every 10min, daemon_tick for task=opus-curator shows exit_code=5 (5+ consecutive failures observed 2026-05-22 17:08-17:48Z). Dry-run mode (manual invoke) exits 0 cleanly with 'Decision X: already filed today, skipping' for all four pillars. Script has 'set -euo pipefail' so a single unset var / non-zero subshell after the decision-print phase will exit with that command's code. The real-run code path beyond dry-run guards must contain the failing call — most likely a chump gap mutation (gap reserve / gap set / decompose) or a fleet-state.json batch write that returns 5. Mitigates noise in daemon_tick stream AND restores curator's ability to file balance-restock gaps when a pillar is genuinely starved (currently INFRA-1382 reports zero-pickable for all pillars but curator can't act). Fix: add 'or echo + curator_error event + true' around the suspect call in scripts/coord/opus-curator.sh; or unwrap set -e for the mutation block.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - root-cause identified for non-dry-run failure post 'CURATOR DECISIONS' phase (likely a chump gap mutation or fleet-state write call failing under set -euo pipefail)
    - opus-curator.sh either tolerates the failure with explicit handling OR emits structured curator_error event AND fails-soft to exit 0 so the daemon_tick stream stops showing exit_code=5 noise
    - after fix, 5 consecutive daemon_tick events for opus-curator show exit_code=0 (verified via tail .chump-locks/ambient.jsonl)
    - smoke test scripts/ci/test-opus-curator-real-run.sh that runs the script without CHUMP_CURATOR_DRY_RUN=1 against a fresh fixture state.db and asserts exit 0
  closed_date: '2026-05-22'
  closed_pr: 2312
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1668
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: oauth-token-critical.json missing — every critical-lane GitHub call emits github_app_fallback, no fallback path exercised"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Symptom: every critical-lane GitHub API call from queue-driver.sh emits 'github_app_fallback criticality=critical reason=lane_token_missing expected_file=/Users/jeffadkins/.chump/oauth-token-critical.json'. Confirmed by ls ~/.chump/ — only oauth-token.json exists, not oauth-token-critical.json. Likely INFRA-1080's call-criticality system (CLAUDE.md) is configured to use a separate token for critical operations but the token-refresh path was never wired. Net effect: critical calls silently fall back to the standard lane (functional) but the noise floods ambient.jsonl. Fix shape: pick one — (a) update fleet-bootstrap to provision the critical token file, or (b) treat fallback as the default and emit only on transition (per-process sentinel). Option (b) is xs effort.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Verified 2026-05-22: per-process sentinel _CHUMP_GH_FALLBACK_NOTICED in scripts/coord/lib/github.sh:451 already limits to one emit per process; ambient noise = N short-lived cron-tick scripts × 1 emit each (queue-driver.sh, pr-rescue.sh, bot-merge.sh fire as separate processes)"
    - "Fix shape A (preferred): day-level sentinel file at .chump-locks/gh-fallback-acked-<YYYY-MM-DD> — skip emit when file exists, touch it on first emit of the day. Limits ambient noise to 1 event per machine per day rather than 1 per process"
    - "Fix shape B: gate emit on CHUMP_GH_LEGACY_AUTH_OK=1 env so operators on legacy path silence the notice via env, not code change"
    - CI test scripts/ci/test-github-fallback-noise-budget.sh runs 5 distinct fleet scripts in a row and asserts at most 1 github_app_fallback emit total (vs. current 5+)
    - "docs/process/OPERATOR_RUNBOOK.md adds a paragraph: 'the fallback notice is informational; provision lane tokens (Steps 1-6) only when seeing graphql_exhausted under sustained load — proven by PR #2310 merging cleanly on legacy path 2026-05-22'"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

