- id: INFRA-1687
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: decompose src/main.rs (6k LOC) via inventory-style subcommand self-registration — kill hot-file shared-edit class"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Strategic followup from 2026-05-22 collision-scaling conversation. Today
    src/main.rs holds every CLI subcommand dispatch (~6000 LOC); every PR that
    adds a command must edit this one file. Observed concretely 2026-05-22:
    3+ agents holding main.rs leases concurrently (INFRA-1484/1682/1685). The
    lease model rations a scarce resource; deleting the scarcity is cheaper
    than scheduling around it. Same playbook applies to EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    (second hot-file in the fleet) after main.rs lands.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Subcommand self-registration via inventory or linkme crate: each subcommand owns src/cmd/<name>.rs and submits Subcommand{name, run, help} at link time; no edits to main.rs to add a new subcommand"
    - src/main.rs reduces from ~6000 LOC to <500 LOC (router-only) — the leftover is arg-parse + global dispatch
    - "Pilot migration: chump fanout (INFRA-1484) + chump fleet plan/apply/spec-status (INFRA-1483) ported to the new pattern first; proves the registration ergonomics"
    - ci.yml gate scripts/ci/test-main-rs-loc.sh asserts main.rs LOC <500 — advisory during pilot, blocking after full migration
    - "EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml decomposition: docs/events/<kind>.yaml glob-loaded via build.rs; same playbook applied to the second hot-file"
    - Migration plan doc at docs/refactor/MAIN_RS_DECOMPOSITION.md names every subcommand and assigns a /s follow-up gap per owner
    - "Backward-compat: zero CLI surface changes; all existing chump <subcommand> invocations work identically (smoke: scripts/ci/test-cli-surface-baseline.sh)"
    - "Telemetry: emit kind=hot_file_lease_collision when claim --paths detects an overlap on main.rs or EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml in the post-decomposition window; expectation is zero events after pilot lands"
  notes: |
    Manage-by-elimination of fleet contention. Pillar EFFECTIVE — reduces
    agent-velocity tax from collision rebases. Pairs with INFRA-1688
    (lease-as-advisory) and INFRA-1689 (AST-region claims, contingent).
    Top pick by ROI from 2026-05-22 architectural review with operator.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1688
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: lease-as-advisory + auto-conflict-resolver on every merge — leap-frog the lease-wall model"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Strategic followup from 2026-05-22 collision-scaling conversation. The
    current claim/lease model rations file access; at 10+ workers it crushes
    velocity. Alternative: leases become advisory (warn, don't block),
    INFRA-1488 conflict-resolver-agent runs automatically on every conflicting
    push, humans see only escalations. Today's model assumes conflicts are
    exceptions; this model assumes they are routine and budgets for them.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "CHUMP_CLAIM_MODE env var (default=blocking; opt-in=advisory): in advisory mode, chump claim emits warning on path overlap but allows the claim — no exit-1"
    - bot-merge.sh auto-invokes INFRA-1488 conflict-resolver-agent on merge-conflict detection (no --opt-in flag required); resolver runs unattended for textual/AST scenarios it has a confidence pattern for
    - "Test suite scripts/ci/test-conflict-resolver-scenarios.sh: 10+ synthetic conflict scenarios with known-correct resolutions (rust func-add, yaml row-add, ci.yml step-insert, EVENT_REGISTRY kind-add, etc.); each scenario asserts the resolver produces the expected merged file"
    - "Telemetry: emit kind=conflict_auto_resolved {pr, files, scenario_match, confidence} on success; kind=conflict_escalated_to_operator {pr, reason} when below confidence threshold or no scenario match"
    - "Rollout gate: default-flip from blocking → advisory after 100 consecutive auto-resolutions without operator-reported regression; auto-revert to blocking on any operator-reported bad resolution within 24h"
    - "PWA surface: auto-resolution rate per 24h on /pwa/cockpit; escalation queue with one-click approve / revert / edit per resolution"
    - "Backward-compat: bare chump claim under default CHUMP_CLAIM_MODE=blocking keeps current semantics; existing sibling-lease alerts unchanged"
    - "Honest-failure mode: if 3+ operator-rejected resolutions land in a 7d window, kind=conflict_resolver_trust_breach emits and the default flips back to blocking automatically"
  notes: |
    Leap-frog play from 2026-05-22 architectural review. Right north star
    at 10+ worker scale. Pairs with INFRA-1687 (deletes the most common
    contention class first) and INFRA-1689 (sub-file claims as hedge).
    Pillar RESILIENT — embraces concurrent edits as a budgeted failure
    class rather than rationing the resource.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1689
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: AST-region claims via tree-sitter — sub-file lease granularity (contingent on hot-file decomposition outcome)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: l
  description: |
    Strategic followup from 2026-05-22 collision-scaling conversation. Hedge
    play. If INFRA-1687 (hot-file decomposition) drops the collision rate to
    near-zero, this gap stays at P2. If post-decomposition metrics still show
    >1 file-level collision/day across the fleet, promote to P1 and pick up.
    Instead of file-level leases, declare AST regions: agents claim
    'src/main.rs::dispatch::fanout' not 'src/main.rs'. Two agents editing
    different functions in the same file don't collide.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump claim --region <file>::<function|impl|struct> declares a region-level lease parsed via tree-sitter for the file's language"
    - "Region-overlap detector: two claims on the same file but disjoint AST regions don't trigger sibling-lease alerts; same-region overlap blocks as today"
    - "v1 languages: Rust, TypeScript, Python — covers >95% of repo by LOC; other languages fall through to file-level claim with a one-line stderr note"
    - "Lease file format extension: .chump-locks/<session>.json paths array entries become 'file' (current) or 'file::region' (new); backward compatible with existing readers"
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-region-claim.sh: two synthetic claims on same file different functions both succeed; same function, second claim blocks; cross-language fall-through path covered"
    - "Telemetry: kind=region_lease_acquired {file, region, lang} on grant; kind=region_lease_collision_avoided {file, regions} when two agents safely share a file — proves the feature pays off"
    - "Bypass / additive: --paths CSV still works for cross-file claims; --region is additive (a claim may specify both); operator can opt out per-claim with --no-region"
    - "Sunset condition: gap can be closed without shipping if INFRA-1687 lands and 30-day post-decomposition window shows <0.1 collisions/day fleet-wide"
  notes: |
    Hedge tier from 2026-05-22 architectural review. Real engineering
    (~1 week per language parser) — do NOT pick up until INFRA-1687
    metrics are in. Pillar EFFECTIVE.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

