    repo and add value" demo (Week 4 deliverable) runs against. This
    decision gates every Week 2 design choice — per-language detector
    quality bar, artifact shape, tooling surfaces, failure-mode coverage.
    
    Operator constraint: "many repos." Selection rubric (6 criteria):
    language mix (3+ of supported), size (2-15k LOC), age (3-12 months
    active), push access, demo-watchability (30s pitch), familiarity
    inverted (operator should NOT have touched in last 7 days, ideally
    30+).
    
    Method: META-069 — Sonnet does the per-repo data gather + scoring,
    Opus does synthesis + the final pick.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - docs/strategy/COLUMN_A_DEMO_TARGET_2026-05-23.md exists, names exactly ONE primary repo, scores it 0-3 against each of the 6 criteria
    - Doc includes a top-5 scoring matrix from the data-gather pass (Sonnet's output)
    - Doc includes an explicit fallback ladder (at least 3 alternatives in priority order) with the criterion-by-criterion reason each is below the primary
    - Doc names the 'what this gates' implications for Week 2 design (per-language detector priority, artifact shape, tooling surfaces, failure-mode coverage)
    - Doc names a pre-flight gate (INFRA-1778 chump ingest pre-flight) that must pass before the demo is committed; if pre-flight blocks, walk the fallback ladder and re-record
    - Process-notes section attributes the data-gather vs synthesis split per META-069 discipline
    - Doc is committed in a single docs-only PR; CI is docs-path-filtered, no fast-checks/cargo-test required
  notes: |
