- id: INFRA-1798
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: cron-loop autopilot prompt reads opus-message inbox at iter start — 'Glance' phase addendum (INFRA-1796 dogfood)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Receive-and-act-by-default, loop-discipline half (sibling of CREDIBLE-114, the PreToolUse hard-enforcement half). Per A2A_MASTER_PLAN_2026-06-03 Tier-0 step 0.3: 'chump-inbox.sh read' must be the MANDATORY first step of every curator/worker/autopilot cycle, and the agent must ACT on what it finds (ack handoffs, vote on open proposals) — not read-only. This is the 'demand side' the whole A2A layer was missing: agents broadcast 57 proposals over 24d but never read/voted, so consensus_result stayed 0 (the closing bug is fixed in CREDIBLE-122). Success is the OUTCOME metric, not a green check: inbox_advance > 0 and consensus_result firing organically.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Every curator/worker/autopilot loop (scripts/coord/*-loop.sh + the work-your-lane / SUBAGENT prompt) runs scripts/coord/chump-inbox.sh read as the FIRST step of each cycle, before picking new work (A2A_MASTER_PLAN Tier-0 0.3).
    - "After draining, the agent ACTS on each item: ack HANDOFF/STUCK via broadcast.sh --to <sender> DONE, and cast chump vote <corr_id> +1|-1|0 --reason on every open FEEDBACK kind=proposal it has not yet voted on. Read-without-act does NOT satisfy this."
    - Each drained cycle emits kind=inbox_advance with the count of items processed, so the outcome is measurable (the master-plan load-bearing gate is inbox_advance > 0 fleet-wide).
    - "OUTCOME verification (not signal): over a soak window with >=1 open proposal and >=2 live agents, consensus_result events fire and at least one proposal reaches quorum (>1 distinct voter). consensus_result count must climb from its current floor."
    - "Smoke test: a single loop cycle with 1 unread proposal in the inbox results in (a) the proposal read, (b) a chump vote emitted for it, (c) an inbox_advance event — asserted by a scripts/ci/test-*.sh that drives the real loop, not a hand-written fixture."
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1799
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE: chump gap set acceptance-criteria escapes pipe chars in AC values (today's INFRA-1796 yaml break + earlier Rust-generic AC breaks)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    chump gap set --acceptance-criteria treats the pipe character as the AC delimiter, but provides no escape mechanism. When an AC value legitimately contains '|' (Rust generic bounds like Type1|Type2, regex alternation like <a|b|c>, shell pipes in code snippets), the parser splits the value mid-bullet and produces malformed yaml. Today (2026-05-23) this bug broke 3 separate AC writes: (1) my own attempts to file Rust HandoffContract gaps with generic syntax, (2) the INFRA-1796 (opus-message v0) author writing '<gap-id|session-id|all-opus>' for the --to recipient resolution, (3) similar issues in subsequent ACs. The INFRA-1796 case cascaded through gaps-integrity check on 5 PRs (#2391, #2392, #2393, #2394, plus advisory). The fix is small CLI-parser change: either accept --acceptance-criteria multiple times (one bullet per flag) or treat backslash-pipe as escaped. Pillar ZERO-WASTE — high-frequency CI failure source that costs both time-to-fix and operator-time-routing.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "src/main.rs or wherever chump gap set lives: parser for --acceptance-criteria gains a documented escape mechanism. Two options to evaluate (operator picks during implementation): (a) treat backslash-pipe (escape) as literal pipe within an AC bullet, (b) accept --acceptance-criteria multiple times where each invocation is one bullet (no delimiter needed), preferred because no escape syntax to teach"
    - chump gap set --help documents the chosen mechanism with an example showing a pipe-containing AC value
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/behavior_gap_set_pipe_escape.sh: invoke chump gap set on a synthetic gap with an AC value containing a literal pipe, assert the resulting yaml parses cleanly via python yaml.safe_load + assert the AC bullet contains the literal pipe character"
    - "Backward compatible: existing AC values without pipes work identically; only the new escape-or-multi-flag path is a feature add"
    - "Optional: if implementation goes the multi-flag route, the old delimiter syntax stays supported with a deprecation warning to ambient kind=chump_gap_set_legacy_delim used so the curator can migrate scripts gradually"
  closed_date: '2026-05-24'
  closed_pr: 2411
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

