- id: INFRA-1808
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump-fleet-bootstrap durability — auto-chmod install scripts, fix false-negative checks, run hourly via launchd (3 issues found by curator-opus-shepherd 2026-05-23)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Three concrete issues found 2026-05-23 by curator-opus-shepherd while investigating why pr-auto-rebase + claude-reaper + bot-merge-watchdog + 2 other REQUIRED_DAEMONS were not running despite their installer scripts having shipped days earlier. Root cause: nothing runs the bootstrap installer automatically. The installer is documented in CLAUDE.md but only runs when an operator manually invokes it. Manual invocation discovered a real bug too (scripts/setup/install-bot-merge-watchdog.sh was mode 0644). Two of the manifest checks (queue-health-monitor-launchd, github-liaison-launchd) returned false-negative MISSING despite the daemons being loaded — bootstrap-check logic looks for different markers than what installers create. Rough shape: (a) fix install-bot-merge-watchdog.sh perm + add a pre-commit hook or CI gate that asserts install-*.sh files are mode 0755; (b) fix bootstrap-check false negatives for queue-health-monitor and github-liaison; (c) install a launchd job that runs chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --install hourly (idempotent installers already, so safe to repeat) with a kind=fleet_bootstrap_auto_install ambient event per run.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/setup/install-bot-merge-watchdog.sh chmod +x in repo (currently 0644) — single commit, no logic change
    - "scripts/ci/test-install-scripts-executable.sh new test: asserts every scripts/setup/install-*.sh file is mode 0755; fails CI if not — prevents recurrence"
    - "chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --check fixed for queue-health-monitor-launchd: verify via launchctl list query for dev.chump.queue-health-monitor, NOT the marker currently used"
    - "chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --check fixed for github-liaison-launchd: verify via launchctl list query for dev.chump.github-liaison, NOT the marker currently used"
    - "scripts/setup/install-bootstrap-auto-launchd.sh: new installer that registers a launchd job running chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --install hourly; emits kind=fleet_bootstrap_auto_install with fields {installed_count, manifest_missing_count, daemon_missing_count} per run"
    - chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh self-installs the auto-launchd job on first install run (so the boot-strap problem is solved on first manual run, never reverts)
    - chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh attempts chmod +x on any install-*.sh it tries to run before invoking it — resilience against this exact perm-bit failure mode
    - README.md and CLAUDE.md MANDATORY pre-flight section updated to note that the hourly auto-bootstrap exists, but operators on a fresh machine still need to run chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh once manually to bootstrap the bootstrapper
    - CI test scripts/ci/test-bootstrap-auto-install.sh asserts the launchd job loads cleanly and emits the expected ambient kind on a synthetic invocation
  notes: |
    Pillar: RESILIENT. Discovered 2026-05-23 by curator-opus-shepherd during investigation of stale PR queue. INFRA-1777 (pr-auto-rebase daemon shipped 2026-05-22 23:36Z) and INFRA-1779 (its launchd plist installer shipped 23:48Z) were never installed on this host until manual run today. Same pattern as INFRA-1662 reaper from prior day. This gap closes the structural pattern: code shipped to repo != code running on host. Effort=s because each individual fix is a few lines; the wiring is the work.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1809
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump CLI startup hangs indefinitely on trivial commands (chump --version, chump preflight --help) — observed twice in 24h, every shell-script invoking chump becomes a hang risk"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Observed 2026-05-22 23:xxZ and 2026-05-23 07:xxZ during PR shepherd work: chump --version hung for 9+ minutes, chump preflight --help hung for 8+ minutes — both should print and exit in <100ms. Killing with kill -9 was the only recovery. No state.db lock visible via lsof, no obvious deadlock target. Symptom recurs under load (high process count, high disk IO). Every shell script that invokes chump as a preflight check (pre-push hook, scripts/coord/*, scripts/setup/*) becomes a hang risk; this is the root cause of many "pre-push hook hung 16+ min" reports. Without this fix, INFRA-1808 (bootstrap auto-install) cannot be trusted because every bootstrap run could hang. Rough shape: (a) add a 5s startup wallclock budget enforced inside main.rs early in fn main(); (b) on timeout, dump backtrace + exit non-zero with diagnostic; (c) bisect what subsystem causes the hang (suspect: tokio runtime init waiting on a downed Anthropic endpoint, or memory_db connection pool; possibly mistralrs feature flag); (d) make chump --version and chump --help short-circuit BEFORE any subsystem init so they cannot hang regardless.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump --version and chump --help return in <100ms even under load (synthetic test: spawn 200 concurrent chump --version invocations, all complete within 5s)"
    - "Add startup wallclock budget at main.rs entry: env CHUMP_STARTUP_TIMEOUT_MS (default 5000); on timeout, dump tokio runtime status + memory_db connection state + active subsystems, exit code 4, with diagnostic to stderr"
    - "chump --version and chump --help short-circuit BEFORE tokio runtime init, before memory_db connect, before any LLM-provider init — proves the hang class is \"subsystem init blocks\", not \"argparse blocks\""
    - "Bisect: identify the subsystem responsible (likely tokio runtime + Anthropic SDK background init OR memory_db r2d2 pool when DB locked); document finding in commit body"
    - "If root cause is memory_db lock contention, add lock-timeout + diagnostic via r2d2::Builder::connection_timeout; if root cause is Anthropic SDK init, lazy-init it past argparse"
    - Emit kind=chump_startup_timeout to ambient.jsonl on every timeout (with cmd, args, elapsed_ms, suspected_subsystem)
    - "CI test scripts/ci/test-chump-startup-fast.sh: assert chump --version completes <100ms warm-cache, <2000ms cold-cache; assert under simulated load (parallel invocations) p99 <5s"
    - cargo fmt/clippy clean; no new runtime deps
  notes: |
    Pillar: RESILIENT. Discovered during PR shepherd work — chump CLI hangs were the root cause of cascade pre-push hook hangs (every hook invokes chump preflight or chump --version). Blocks INFRA-1808 trust (auto-install can not be reliable if installer scripts call chump and chump hangs). Pairs with INFRA-1597/1645 (paramedic daemon broken — likely related r2d2 lock issue). Effort=m because bisect + lazy-init refactor is non-trivial.
    [2026-05-24T09:01:11Z] stuck cycle 1 → re-attempt 2026-05-24 (PR #2447 auto-closed) respawn-handled:2447
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

