- id: INFRA-1861
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CI/QA: every required check accurate, no flakes, zero false-positive failures, 100% catch rate on local-vs-CI parity (META-074 child A)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Child A of META-074. Operator priority #1: "CI/QA to be 100%."
    
    Today's pain (concrete, 2026-05-23 session):
      - 3 PRs (#2398/#2399/#2416) all failed cargo-test + ACP smoke +
        chump-first-contract on one root-cause syntax error in
        src/preflight.rs from a bad rebase. The 8-12 min CI cycle ran
        all 3 in parallel; each consumed full runner time before
        surfacing the same error. Local preflight would have caught
        it in <60s.
      - PR #2418's pr-hygiene check failed on a regex that didn't
        recognize PR-body mentions of deleted files (only "Revert"
        commits). False positive.
      - Multiple "audit-required" cascade failures because the
        EVENT_REGISTRY orphan-allowlist drifts faster than PRs can
        rebase against it.
      - Pre-push hook hangs forced --no-verify usage across the night.
    
    What "100%" means concretely:
      a) Every CI failure represents a real defect (no flakes, no
         heuristics-false-positives)
      b) Every defect surfaces locally before push (chump preflight
         catches what CI would catch, in <60s warm)
      c) When CI fails, the cause is immediately legible to the
         operator (no spelunking through cascade-cancellations)
      d) Audit-allowlist drift is auto-detected + auto-fixed (no
         manual orphan-batch PRs)
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Flake-rerun catalog (docs/process/KNOWN_FLAKES.yaml) audit: 100% of catalogued flakes have a root-cause-fix gap filed; un-catalogued flakes block merge until catalogued OR root-caused"
    - "chump preflight --scope all gains coverage parity with CI: any check that CI runs MUST have a preflight equivalent OR be explicitly exempted in docs/process/CI_GATES_INVENTORY.md with a reason"
    - "Audit-allowlist auto-pruner: kind=audit_orphan_landed event fires when a new orphan appears on main; auto-rescue daemon (extends INFRA-1714) opens a batch-allowlist PR within 5 minutes"
    - "False-positive heuristic-check audit: every check that produces FAIL must have a 'how to bypass cleanly' line in its output. pr-hygiene's PR-body-mention check must recognize markdown link to filename, plain mention, AND Revert commit"
    - "Cascade-cancellation visibility: when a required check cancels other jobs, the cancelled-jobs list is surfaced in PR status not buried in workflow run logs"
    - "Pre-push hook hard timeout: cap each phase at 30s; total 90s; abort + emit kind=prepush_timeout if exceeded. Today's hang-induced --no-verify usage = audit signal of CI/QA debt"
    - "Local-vs-CI parity smoke: scripts/ci/test-preflight-parity.sh runs chump preflight + parses the CI workflow YAML + asserts every required-check has a preflight match (or explicit exempt)"
    - "Telemetry: emit kind=ci_qa_score {window_h:24, accurate_failures:N, false_positives:N, missed_locally:N, flake_count:N} hourly; score = (accurate / (accurate + false_positive + missed_locally + flake)) × 100. Target ≥95% by Week 4, 100% by Week 8"
  notes: |
    P1 RESILIENT/CREDIBLE crossover. Child A of META-074. Ship before
    child B (A2A) because: A2A coordination needs trustworthy CI signal
    to know whether peer agents succeeded. False CI = false coordination.
    Suggested owner role: curator-opus-ci-audit (already exists per
    today's session).
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1862
  domain: INFRA
  title: "A2A WORLD-CLASS: extend INFRA-1115 broadcast/inbox into a real coordination mesh with delivery guarantees + role-typed routing (META-074 child B)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Child B of META-074. Operator priority #2: "A2A world class."
    
    Today's pain (concrete):
      - My STUCK broadcast at 18:54Z used reason=unspecified (broadcast.sh
        positional-arg confusion) — orchestrator had to ask for the
        actual reason. Delivery worked; semantic correctness didn't.
      - When the daily-driver-session closed 3 of my PRs at 21:29Z while
        my fixes were in flight, no advance signal. The closure was an
        automated action with no broadcast.
      - curator-opus-ci-audit dispatched INFRA-1834 to me at 21:33Z —
        cross-curator routing worked, but there's no role-based
        capability discovery (it could have routed to curator-opus-handoff
        instead and I'd never know).
      - No delivery guarantees: I check my inbox manually each turn.
        At 50 workers, every agent polling every turn = wasted compute.
    
    What "world class" means concretely:
      a) Typed events with strict schemas (today's broadcast.sh accepts
         INTENT/HANDOFF/STUCK/DONE/WARN/ALERT but the field shapes drift)
      b) Role-based capability discovery (Opus instances publish their
         role-skills; routers dispatch to best-fit owner not to whoever
         claimed first)
      c) Delivery guarantees (push notifications via NATS — already partly
         in INFRA-1118 A2A Layer 1a — replace polling inboxes)
      d) Atomic claim-handoff (handing off a gap mid-stream shouldn't
         require the receiver to re-claim; current pattern leaves a 10-30s
         hand-over gap)
      e) Audit trail: every send/receive logged for post-hoc analysis
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Schema validation: scripts/coord/broadcast.sh rejects malformed events with a clear error pointing at the expected shape (today's --to-recipient + STUCK reason field defaulted to 'unspecified' on positional-arg misuse)"
    - "Capability manifest: each curator session publishes role + skills (e.g. role=curator, skills=[rust,docs,sql,a2a]) to a known KV; routers query by skill match BEFORE dispatching"
    - "Delivery guarantees Tier 1: NATS-backed delivery (extends INFRA-1118 Layer 1a) for high-priority events (STUCK, ALERT, dispatch). Tier 2: file inbox as fallback for low-priority"
    - "Push notifications: agents subscribe to their session's inbox via NATS push (not poll). Reduces polling overhead by 100×"
    - "Atomic handoff: chump gap handoff <gap> --to <session> atomically transfers the lease + claim record + worktree pointer in a single transaction; receiver auto-resumes without manual re-claim"
    - "Audit trail: every broadcast logged to ambient.jsonl with sender/recipient/event/correlation_id; nightly digest summarises mesh health (delivery rate, response latency, dead-letter count)"
    - "Backward-compat: existing broadcast.sh callers continue to work; new typed-schema is opt-in via --strict flag; flip to default after 7-day clean window"
    - "Smoke: scripts/ci/test-a2a-mesh.sh spawns 3 ephemeral sessions, exchanges messages across all 6 pair-directions, asserts 100% delivery + <100ms median latency"
  notes: |
    DECOMPOSED 2026-05-24T17:42Z by wizard (owning the offline decompose-curator task per operator 17:31Z directive). 5 sub-slices filed:
      - INFRA-1944 slice A: broadcast.sh delivery-confirmation receipts (P1/s)
      - INFRA-1945 slice B: role-typed routing via fleet-registry.jsonl (P1/s)
      - INFRA-1946 slice C: dead-letter queue + operator-recall page (P1/s)
      - INFRA-1947 slice D: opt-in NATS transport with file-fallback (P2/m)
      - INFRA-1948 slice E: schema validation + 4 ambient kinds (P1/xs, ships last)
    Recommended ship order: E (gates) → A → B → C → D. Slices A-C usable independently for single-machine fleet; D enables Pi-mesh.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1863
  domain: INFRA
  title: "OWNER-BY-SCOPE: replace file-leases with role/skill-typed claims; agents own modules/concerns, conflict-resolver handles overlap (META-074 child C)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    Child C of META-074. Operator priority #3: "owner by scope and role
    type/skill etc."
    
    Today's pain (concrete):
      - INFRA-1853 holds scripts/coord/chump-commit.sh for ~4h. I needed
        a 5-line edit there for INFRA-1834. Blocked.
      - META-071 holds docs/process, docs/gaps, scripts/ci as a SINGLE
        broad lease. Any docs/gaps work collides with it.
      - INFRA-1792 + INFRA-1831 both held event-registry-reserved.txt
        (append-only metadata file) earlier in the night. Lease
        semantics on an append-only file = double-counting.
      - I want to add a 1-line allowlist entry; another agent is rewriting
        the file's structure. Today's leases can't express the difference
        between 'append a row' and 'rewrite the schema.'
    
    What "owner by scope and role/skill" means concretely:
      a) Agents claim by ROLE (curator, fleet-worker, paramedic, etc.)
         and SCOPE (a module, a concern, a feature-area) — NOT a file
         path
      b) Specific files become outputs of role-scoped work; multiple
         agents touching the same file is the NORM, not the exception
      c) Conflict-resolver (INFRA-1488, shipped) auto-resolves textual
         conflicts; advisory-lease (INFRA-1688, filed) warns instead
         of blocks
      d) Append-only metadata files (event-registry-reserved.txt,
         env-vars-internal.txt, EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml) are explicitly
         EXEMPT from lease semantics — the append-only merge driver
         already handles them
      e) Broad-scope leases (>1 dir) require explicit --broad --reason
         flag at claim time
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump claim --role <role> --scope <module-or-concern> [--paths CSV] — paths now optional and advisory. Default behaviour: warn on overlap, do not block"
    - "Append-only file exemption: scripts/ci/event-registry-reserved.txt, scripts/ci/env-vars-internal.txt, docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml are NEVER leased — chump claim ignores them in the paths CSV"
    - "Broad-scope guard: claims with >1 directory in --paths require --broad flag + --reason '<text>' OR get auto-narrowed to the most-specific common parent"
    - "Role registry: docs/process/AGENT_ROLES.yaml enumerates roles (curator, fleet-worker, paramedic, ci-audit, handoff, target, decompose, shepherd) with skill profiles; chump claim --role must match a registered role"
    - "Conflict-resolver wired into bot-merge.sh: auto-invoke on every push that conflicts; emit kind=conflict_auto_resolved/escalated for audit"
    - "Migration: existing path-based claims continue to work; new role-based claims are opt-in via --role flag; flip claims to advisory-by-default after Week-2 clean window + ≥100 successful auto-resolutions"
    - "Telemetry: emit kind=claim_collision_avoided when role-scoped claim would have collided under old file-lease semantics; metric becomes the migration-success signal"
    - "Smoke: scripts/ci/test-role-scoped-claims.sh exercises 5 scenarios — same-role same-scope (block), same-role different-scope (allow), different-role same-file (allow + warn), broad-scope without flag (reject), append-only file in paths (exempt)"
  notes: |
    P1 EFFECTIVE/RESILIENT crossover. Child C of META-074. SHIP LAST
    of the three children — depends on child A (CI/QA accurate enough
    to trust conflict-resolver outputs) AND child B (A2A spine to
    coordinate the conflict-resolver across agents). Suggested owner
    role: curator-opus-fleet (new role).
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

