- id: INFRA-1890
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: detector escalation tier — when same ambient signature fires N times in M hours without resolution, auto-file ONE follow-up gap (dedup via title hash + respect META-063 redundancy gate); turns silent detectors into actionable gaps"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. New module crates/chump-coord/src/escalation.rs (or wherever detector daemons live) defines EscalationRule { signature_kind: String, threshold_count: u32, window_hours: u32, resolution_check: fn(event) -> bool, gap_title_template: String, gap_priority: Priority, gap_effort: Effort }"
    - "2. Initial rule set seeded with 4 signatures derived from 2026-05-23 triage scan — (a) kind=gap_failed same gap_id >=10x in 24h AND chump gap show <id> returns status=open AND no commit on branch since first event → file gap titled 'RESILIENT: <gap-id> stuck — N gap_failed events without recovery'; (b) kind=pr_auto_rebase_failed same PR >=3x in 24h AND PR mergeStateStatus still DIRTY → file gap; (c) kind=dirty_pr_unresolvable same conflict_files across >=3 distinct PRs in 24h → file gap titled 'RESILIENT: hot-file <path> blocking N PRs — rebase contention pattern'; (d) any novel kind (no rule yet) → emit kind=escalation_uncategorized + log to .chump/triage/uncategorized.jsonl for operator review only"
    - "3. Dedup gate: generate title hash via SHA256(normalize(title)); before filing query chump gap list --status open --grep <keyword>; if any open gap matches → emit kind=escalation_dedup_hit with matched_gap_id, do NOT file"
    - "4. Respect META-063 redundancy gate: run chump gap consolidate --threshold 0.7 against candidate title; if any duplicate suggestion → skip and emit kind=escalation_meta063_blocked"
    - 5. Scheduled hourly via launchd plist scripts/launchd/com.chump.escalation.plist OR added to existing daemon cycle
    - 6. Each filing emits kind=escalation_fired with signature, match_count, gap_id_filed, dedup_checks_passed
    - "7. Unit test scripts/ci/test-escalation-tier.sh: seed ambient.jsonl with synthetic 10x same signature spanning 12h, run escalation, assert exactly one gap filed; run again, assert second-run sees dedup_hit not a second filing"
    - "8. Operator override: chump fleet escalation --suppress-rule <id> writes a suppression entry to .chump/escalation-suppressions.json (e.g. to silence a known-noisy signature during a maintenance window)"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

