- id: INFRA-1902
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: chump-commit.sh auto-lease side-effect materializes stale-TODO-AC YAMLs that mismatch state.db — companion to INFRA-1893 (same step's spurious 401); sub-agent INFRA-1743 had to chump gap set mid-ship to fix stale ACs"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Reproduce: in a worktree whose state.db has gap X with full ACs but disk has no docs/gaps/X.yaml, invoke scripts/coord/chump-commit.sh <some-other-file> -m 'message mentioning X-NNN'; expect: either NO YAML is materialized for X OR the materialized YAML matches state.db's content (description + ACs + notes); baseline 2026-05-23: sub-agent INFRA-1743 found stale TODO-AC YAML in state.db that broke bot-merge re-claim until chump gap set was invoked; sub-agent INFRA-1888 batch saw INFRA-1896 materialized with TODO ACs while state.db had real ones"
    - "2. Trace the code path: chump-commit.sh lines around 480-512 (the auto-lease block per existing code grep) calls chump claim <gap-id> for each gap-ID in the commit message; identify whether chump claim OR a downstream hook is the source of the TODO-AC YAML stub"
    - "3. Fix: replace the stub-template materialization with chump gap dump --per-file --gap <ID> (or equivalent state.db-canonical render); if that command does not exist, add it OR skip materialization entirely and let the existing yaml-drift daemon reconcile"
