- id: INFRA-1911
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: docs/gaps/*.yaml closed_pr field can reference CLOSED-not-MERGED PRs leaving gaps falsely-shipped — 4 instances on 2026-05-24 (INFRA-1412/1458/1597/1598); reaper INFRA-1909 doesn't catch these (it checks merged state)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Reproduce: docs/gaps/<ID>.yaml has 'closed_pr: NNNN' set; gh pr view NNNN shows state=CLOSED but merged=null/no (PR was closed without merging — superseded, abandoned, or rejected). Gap reads as falsely-shipped to anyone parsing the YAML"
    - "2. Detection logic: scripts/dev/audit-stale-closed-pr-refs.sh — walk docs/gaps/*.yaml; for each gap with closed_pr set AND status:open, run gh pr view <N> --json mergedAt; if mergedAt is null, emit kind=stale_closed_pr_ref with {gap_id, pr_number, pr_state}"
    - "3. Remediation choice (operator decision per gap): (a) clear the closed_pr field and re-queue for fresh work, OR (b) update closed_pr to the actual merged-PR (if work landed via different PR), OR (c) mark status:wontfix if work abandoned"
    - "4. Smoke test scripts/ci/test-audit-stale-closed-pr.sh: seed two gap yamls (one with merged closed_pr, one with closed-but-not-merged closed_pr); invoke audit; assert exactly one stale_closed_pr_ref event emitted"
    - "5. Bypass: CHUMP_AUDIT_STALE_CLOSED_PR=0 disables; emit kind=stale_closed_pr_audit_disabled"
    - "6. Cadence: weekly cron OR run-on-demand from chump health; not blocking"
    - "7. Baseline 2026-05-24 evidence: 4 instances detected in single session — INFRA-1412 closed_pr=2283, INFRA-1458 closed_pr=2292, INFRA-1597 closed_pr=2268, INFRA-1598 closed_pr=2276 — all 4 PRs are CLOSED not MERGED"
    - 8. Pairs with INFRA-1909 (ghost-gap reaper for the merged case); this gap handles the NOT-merged closed_pr drift class (different remediation path)
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

