  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Reproduce: every push that fires the pre-push hook (which already invokes chump preflight per INFRA-1670/1671) emits a kind=preflight_ci_agreement event to ambient with {gap_id, branch, preflight_pass:bool, preflight_secs:int, sha:str} AFTER the local preflight completes"
    - "2. After CI completes on the resulting PR (success/failure/skipped), a follow-up event kind=preflight_ci_agreement_resolved {gap_id, sha, ci_pass:bool, ci_required_pass:bool, mismatch:bool} is emitted — likely via scripts/ops/github-liaison.sh on workflow_run.completed webhook"
    - "3. Weekly rollup script scripts/dev/preflight-ci-agreement-report.sh: queries ambient.jsonl for the last 7 days, joins by sha, reports {total_pushes, both_pass_count, both_fail_count, local_pass_ci_fail_count, local_fail_ci_pass_count, agreement_pct}"
    - "4. Target: agreement_pct ≥ 95% (anything below means preflight needs adjustment to match CI gates more closely)"
    - "5. Bypass: CHUMP_PREFLIGHT_CI_AGREEMENT=0 disables emit (debug-only)"
    - "6. Smoke test scripts/ci/test-preflight-ci-agreement.sh: stub a synthetic push event + a synthetic workflow_run.completed + invoke the rollup; assert mismatch counted correctly when local-pass + ci-fail"
    - 7. Register the 2 new event kinds in scripts/ci/event-registry-reserved.txt (python-direct emit, not grep-scannable)
    - "8. Baseline 2026-05-24: 0 visibility into local↔CI agreement; pre-push hook is honored (0 bypass events in 24h) but we cannot tell if the 0.18s docs-only preflight + sub-min Rust preflight actually catches what the 10-12min CI catches"
