    - "Concrete first slice — pick ONE high-throughput, platform-agnostic job (suggest: 'audit' or 'fast-checks') and add a parallel job 'audit-self-hosted' that runs on chump-fleet runners. Gate the required-check on either passing (workflow-call required: false). Validates the pattern before broadcasting it across N workflows"
    - "Measure — after the first-slice ships, measure queue drain rate (merges per hour over a 4h window) vs pre-change baseline. Target: 2x improvement when GH-hosted queue is saturated"
    - Pairs with — INFRA-1543 (Pi mesh Linux ARM64 runners) which is the longer-arc fix for actually mirroring ubuntu workflows. INFRA-1937 is the Phase 1 workaround using existing macOS runners. INFRA-1544 (fleet doctor runner liveness) catches the inverse failure mode
    - Done definition — at least 1 production workflow has a self-hosted parallel job that exercises the same gate; queue drain rate measurably improves when GH-hosted is saturated
  notes: |
