- id: INFRA-1953
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md ship-or-die gate — sonnet dispatch MUST verify PR exists before return; current epilogue allows 'idle-waiting' as completion (observed 2026-05-24 in INFRA-1893 + INFRA-1935)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "docs/process/SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md shipping epilogue updated: add a 'PRE-EXIT VERIFICATION' block after the manual-recovery path that says 'BEFORE you return your final report, run: gh pr list --head <your-branch> --state open --json number "
    - " jq length; if result is 0 your work has not shipped — execute the manual-recovery push+create+arm path NOW, do NOT return with status=completed'"
    - Pre-exit verification is the LAST executable instruction in the epilogue (after shipping epilogue, after manual recovery, before final report format)
    - New scripts/dispatch/subagent-pre-exit-check.sh helper that takes a branch name + asserts (a) branch exists on origin, (b) PR exists for branch, (c) PR has auto-merge armed; exits 0 on all-pass, non-zero with diagnostic otherwise
    - Update existing dispatcher prompt templates (target-loop.sh when shipped, plus any manual dispatch scripts) to pass --verify-ship to the subagent's epilogue
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-subagent-pre-exit-check.sh: synthetic 'subagent' shell that commits + pushes + returns without creating PR; assert the check script catches it (exits 1 with 'no PR for branch')"
    - Add ambient kind=subagent_idle_without_pr emit when the check detects the pattern; debounced per session-id so we can track adoption + remaining instances
  notes: |
    Filed by curator-opus-target-2026-05-23 after observing 2 of last 3 Sonnet dispatches today (INFRA-1893 #2489 + INFRA-1935 #2536) committed + pushed but didn't create PR; manual recovery took ~30s each time. The SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md epilogue HAS the manual recovery path but subagents are reading 'report PR number OR BLOCKED' and treating 'I'm waiting for monitor' as a valid completion. Pre-exit verification is the gate that catches this class of half-ship. Pairs with INFRA-1941 (SessionStart nag) + INFRA-1942 (Monitor restart) — all three are ops-glue gaps that the 2026-05-24 day exposed.
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  closed_pr: 2551
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1954
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: gap-reserve re-uses shipped gap IDs removed from docs/gaps/ — INFRA-018 guard only checks live registry, not git history"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    During the 2026-05-25 Cold Water cycle, chump gap reserve assigned IDs
    META-103, INFRA-1953, INFRA-1955, and INFRA-1957 — all of which had already
    been shipped and removed from docs/gaps/ (their YAML files were deleted after
    gap-ship, not moved to docs/gaps/closed/). The INFRA-018 duplicate-ID guard
    checks docs/gaps/*.yaml and state.db — it does not check git history.
    
    Evidence (observed during Issue #13 audit):
    - chump gap reserve → INFRA-1953 assigned; git log --grep=INFRA-1953 → PR #2551 already shipped
    - chump gap reserve → META-103 assigned; git log --grep=META-103 → PR #2544 already shipped
    - chump gap reserve → INFRA-1955 assigned; git log --grep=INFRA-1955 → PR #2548 already shipped
    - chump gap reserve → INFRA-1957 assigned; git log --grep=INFRA-1957 → PR #2561 already shipped
    Four re-used IDs in a single Cold Water session.
    
    The guard works for gaps still in the live registry. It is blind to gaps that
    shipped and whose YAML files were deleted (not closed/). Any agent reading a
    commit message with a re-used ID will be confused about which gap the work
    refers to.
    
    Falsifying condition: chump gap reserve has a pre-check that runs
    `git log --all --grep=<proposed-id>` and fails if the ID appears.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump gap reserve checks git log (--all, --grep=<proposed-id>) before assigning — fails with DUPLICATE if any commit references the proposed ID
    - "OR: gap-ship moves YAML to docs/gaps/closed/ instead of deleting — INFRA-018 guard already checks closed/"
    - "Regression test: scripts/ci/test-gap-reserve-no-reuse.sh creates a dummy gap, ships it (moving YAML to closed/), then attempts reserve with same ID and asserts failure"
    - "Fix verified by running the Cold Water evidence sequence: four IDs (META-103, INFRA-1953, INFRA-1955, INFRA-1957) attempted reserve with chump gap reserve → all four rejected"
  opened_date: '2026-05-25'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

