- id: INFRA-1987
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: pile-up cluster detector — when N>=3 open PRs fail IDENTICAL check-set within 30min, emit kind=ci_failure_cluster + auto-HOLD fleet shipping until trunk-fix lands"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    See docs/strategy/THE_FLOOR.md §2. THE primary structural fix to
    the pile-up pattern. Today's autopilot retries individual PRs when
    CI is red. When 3+ PRs fail with the same red checks, that's a
    TRUNK or SHARED LAYER bug — retrying individuals burns CI minutes
    against a wall.
    
    Rough shape: (a) launchd daemon at 2min cadence; (b) gh pr list
    --json + failing-check rollup (cache-first); (c) bucket BLOCKED
    PRs by sorted-tuple-of-failing-checks; (d) when any bucket has
    ≥3 entries within trailing 30min, fire; (e) cluster_id is
    sha256(sorted_checks); (f) META gap auto-file via chump gap
    reserve (with --force-duplicate to bypass similarity check on
    repeated cluster fires).
    
    Phase 1 ships detection only (no fleet-hold). Phase 2 extends to
    auto-HOLD once we trust the detection.
    
    THIS GAP IS THE LYNCHPIN. Floor-temp (INFRA-1992) counts these
    events. Recovery queue (INFRA-1993) gates by cluster_id. Wedge
    state machine (INFRA-1994) treats persistent clusters as wedges.
    Ship this first.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - New scanner scripts/coord/cluster-detector.sh runs every 2 min via launchd; queries gh pr list (cache-first per INFRA-1081) for BLOCKED PRs + their failing check names
    - "When N≥3 OPEN PRs share the IDENTICAL set of failing checks within a 30min window, emit ambient event kind=ci_failure_cluster with fields: cluster_id (hash of check-set), pr_numbers (CSV), failing_checks (CSV), detected_at"
    - "Phase 2 extension: auto-HOLD fleet shipping by writing .chump-locks/fleet-hold.txt with the cluster_id + reason; workers read this file before claim and skip shipping work in favor of triage/docs"
    - "Auto-file a META-NNN cluster RCA gap titled 'CLUSTER RCA: <N> PRs blocked on <failing_checks>' with the PR numbers, suspect check-set, and instruction to dispatch blame-bot (INFRA-1989) when available"
    - "Idempotent: re-detection of same cluster_id within 60min does not re-file the META gap; updates the existing one with latest PR list"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-cluster-detector.sh: stub gh pr list with 3 PRs sharing failing checks, assert ambient event fires + META gap created + idempotent on second run"
    - "Cluster resolution: when cluster_id stops appearing (PRs merged or checks turn green), emit kind=ci_failure_cluster_resolved + remove fleet-hold.txt"
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  closed_pr: 2587
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1988
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: hook silent-no-op alarm — when pre-push (or any git hook) exits 0 without entering its main ref loop on a non-trivial push, emit kind=hook_silent_passthrough"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    See docs/strategy/THE_FLOOR.md §3. The 3-day pre-push regression
    (INFRA-1986) existed because the hook exited 0 silently — no test,
    no log, no alarm. This gap converts that invisible failure into
    a visible ambient event.
    
    Rough shape: (a) every hook gets ~5 LOC: counter var + sentinel
    at top of main loop + on-exit trap that checks the counter; (b)
    ambient emit via the existing scripts/dev/ambient-emit.sh helper;
    (c) smoke test with empty stdin to validate the alarm fires.
    
    XS effort because the actual fix is ~30 LOC × 4 hooks. Smoke
    test is the bulk of it.
    
    Pairs with INFRA-1996 (silent-failure tax) — this catches RUNTIME
    silent passthroughs; the tax catches STATIC silent-failure
    surfaces in source code.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Every git hook in scripts/git-hooks/* gets a sentinel: at the top of its main work loop, increment a counter in shell-local variable; on hook exit, if counter==0 AND push was non-trivial (≥1 ref, not all-zero SHAs), emit ambient event kind=hook_silent_passthrough with hook_name + reason='loop did not execute'"
    - "Non-trivial heuristic: stdin had ≥1 line of 'local_ref local_sha remote_ref remote_sha' format; ZERO_SHA-only pushes (deletions, etc.) are trivial and exempt"
    - Reason field captures WHY the loop didn't execute (stdin empty, early-return before loop, exception, etc.) — use $LINENO + last-executed marker
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-hook-silent-noop.sh: run pre-push with empty stdin → assert ambient event fires; run with real stdin → assert no event"
    - "Doc update: docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md gets 'Silent hook detection' entry referencing the 3-day pre-push regression (INFRA-1986) that motivated this"
    - "Telemetry: aggregate kind=hook_silent_passthrough events over 24h window; if any hook fires >2x, file follow-up gap (this is the floor-temp WARM signal)"
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  closed_pr: 2595
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-1989
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE: regression-attribution bot — when a CI test goes from green to red with no test-file change, git-blame the related production paths since last green run and post the suspect commit to the cluster gap"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    See docs/strategy/THE_FLOOR.md §4. Today's RCA workflow when a
    test goes red: I (Opus) bash -x trace it (15-50 min). Blame bot
    automates the green-to-red attribution to <5 min.
    
    Rough shape: (a) consumer of ci_failure_cluster events; (b) gh
    api for last-green run discovery on main; (c) git log + git diff
    to identify test-vs-prod changes; (d) prod-path resolver from
    test source (simple grep for 'use crate::' Rust imports, source/
    in bash); (e) cluster gap comment via gh pr comment OR ambient
    event; (f) ambient telemetry on attribution success/failure
    rates.
    
    Pairs with INFRA-1987 (cluster detector emits the trigger event)
    and INFRA-1991 (auto-rollback consumes the suspect commit).
    
    Sequencing: depends on INFRA-1987 because the cluster gap is
    where the blame-bot posts its findings.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - New script scripts/coord/blame-bot.sh triggered by kind=ci_failure_cluster events (from INFRA-1987) and standalone test-fail events
    - For each newly-failing test, find the last green CI run on main; diff the test file itself between green-sha and now → if unchanged, the test isn't the cause; the suspect is in PROD code that the test exercises
    - "Resolve prod paths via test-to-prod mapping: parse test file for imports/sources/CHUMP_REPO-relative paths it references"
    - Run git log --oneline green_sha..HEAD -- <prod_paths> to surface the suspect commits
    - "Post comment on cluster RCA gap (or open a follow-up gap) with: 'Suspect commits for test <name>: <commit1, commit2, commit3>. Inspect: gh pr view <pr_for_commit1>'"
    - "Emit ambient event kind=regression_attributed with: failing_test, suspect_commits (CSV), prod_paths_checked"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-blame-bot.sh: synthetic git history with green→red transition + isolated prod-file change; assert correct suspect commit identified"
    - "Failure-class: if no suspect commit can be identified (test went red without prod-code or test-code changes — likely flake or env), emit kind=regression_inattributable with reason"
  depends_on: [INFRA-1987]
