- id: INFRA-1996
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: silent-failure tax — CI audit counts 2>/dev/null||true + .unwrap_or_default + hook-can-exit-0-without-loop surfaces; budget+require # Silent-OK-Reason annotation on new ones"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    See docs/strategy/THE_FLOOR.md §3. The pre-push hook regression
    (INFRA-1986) existed because `exit 0` is too easy. Anywhere code
    silently does nothing when it should do something, we have a
    silent-failure surface. They exist, they will always exist, but
    they should be AUDITABLE — not invisible.
    
    Rough shape: (a) audit script that greps for the patterns above
    + AST-walks shell hooks for early-return-without-loop; (b)
    bootstrap pass: every existing surface gets an annotation comment
    or a removal commit; (c) CI gate fails on un-annotated growth; (d)
    bypass env + trailer; (e) ambient telemetry on annotations.
    
    KEY DESIGN: this is a BUDGET, not a BAN. Silent failures are
    necessary (graceful degradation, fail-open on read-only ops). The
    tax converts "silently shipping silent failures" into "explicitly
    shipping silent failures with stated reasons" — same code paths,
    different visibility.
    
    Pairs with INFRA-1988 (silent-no-op alarm runs at runtime; this is
    the static-analysis sibling) and INFRA-1990 (hook stdin gate is
    one specific pattern; this is the general pattern).
    
    Depends on those two because they establish the
    `# Silent-OK-Reason:` annotation convention; this gap generalizes
    it across the codebase.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "New CI gate scripts/ci/test-silent-failure-tax.sh: greps for silent-failure patterns in src/**/*.rs + scripts/**/*.sh; reports total count + delta-since-main"
    - "Patterns counted: '2>/dev/null \\|\\| true', 'unwrap_or_default()', 'unwrap_or(0)', 'unwrap_or(false)', '.ok()', '|| return 0', '|| exit 0' in shell context, hooks with `read` loop that can exit normally without entering the loop"
    - "Budget: today's count is the budget; new PRs that increase count without `# Silent-OK-Reason: <one sentence>` annotation FAIL CI"
    - "Annotation format: `// Silent-OK-Reason: ...` for Rust, `# Silent-OK-Reason: ...` for shell, on the line ABOVE the silent-failure pattern"
    - Annotated surfaces still counted but exempt from the budget gate; ambient emit kind=silent_failure_surface_added with reason field on each new annotated surface (so we can audit reasons over time)
    - "Bootstrap: one-time mass annotation pass through existing surfaces (this is the bulk of the m-effort) — every existing surface gets either an annotation or a removal"
    - "Bypass: CHUMP_SILENT_FAILURE_TAX_BYPASS=1 + commit body trailer `Silent-Failure-Tax-Bypass: <reason>` — same pattern as preflight bypass"
    - "Doc update: docs/process/CLAUDE_GOTCHAS.md gets 'Silent failure tax' section listing the patterns and annotation rules"
  depends_on: [INFRA-1988, INFRA-1990]
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  closed_pr: 2598
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

