- id: INFRA-2002
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE: chump-worker + chump-fleet binaries Phase 1 — port scripts/dispatch/worker.sh + run-fleet.sh to typed Rust (META-107 sub-gap #6 of 6 — the final one)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: l
  description: |
    Final Phase 1 sub-gap of the META-107 Rust-First Migration Blueprint
    series (#6 of 6). Sibling ships: INFRA-1997 chump-git-hooks (#2605),
    INFRA-1998 chump-messaging (#2611), INFRA-1999 chump-github-cache
    (#2633), INFRA-2000 chump-gap-store::maintenance (#2637), INFRA-2001
    chump-ship Phase 2 (#2641). Same recipe — smallest viable carve-out,
    ONE concrete impl, smoke test for parity, backward-compat shims, NO
    new event kinds.
    
    Replaces TWO bash files (Phase 1 = parallel-run via feature flags;
    decommissioning the bash bodies is a follow-up sub-gap):
      - scripts/dispatch/worker.sh    (~1908 LOC, per-worker fleet loop)
      - scripts/dispatch/run-fleet.sh (~750  LOC, fleet launcher)
    
    Module surface inside existing chump-coord crate (not a new crate —
    chump-coord is the natural home for fleet-coordination primitives
    next to capability.rs / work_board.rs / help_request.rs):
    
    (a) crates/chump-coord/src/worker/capability.rs — WorkerCapability
        adapter mapping env (WORKER_SKILLS / WORKER_MACHINE /
        WORKER_BACKEND) into a picker-filter struct. Distinct from
        the wire-format CapabilityManifest in src/capability.rs
        (INFRA-1760, chump-capability-v1 schema published into NATS
        KV). The runtime worker only needs the picker view; KV publish
        is deferred to a follow-up sub-gap.
    
    (b) crates/chump-coord/src/worker/loop_body.rs — single-iteration
        run_one_cycle(&CycleEnv) -> CycleOutcome. The CycleOutcome
        enum classifies 7 terminal states (Shipped, ChildFailed,
        ChildTimeout, NoPickableGap, StateError, LostClaimRace,
        WorktreeError). Emits worker_exit on every child-exit path
        and worker_stuck on every no-progress path; both are existing
        registered kinds. ZERO new kinds.
    
    (c) crates/chump-coord/src/worker/worktree.rs — create_worktree /
        remove_worktree subprocess to `git worktree add -B <branch>
        <path> origin/main` and `git worktree remove --force`. Scope
        doc favored git2::Worktree for env-immunity; Phase 1 ships
        subprocess to keep the dep tree small (60s preflight target).
        Migrating to git2 is a follow-up gap once another caller in
        chump-coord needs the crate.
    
    (d) crates/chump-coord/src/bin/chump-worker.rs — CLI entry. Args:
        --once (single iteration for tests/CI), --idle-sleep-s SECS,
        --session-id ID. Env honors WORKER_SKILLS / WORKER_MACHINE /
        WORKER_BACKEND / FLEET_TIMEOUT_S / CHUMP_GAP_CLAIM_TTL_SECS /
        CHUMP_WORKER_EXEC_OVERRIDE (test seam). NATS PUSH path is
        STUBBED — if CHUMP_NATS_URL is set, the worker emits a debug
        line and falls through to PULL. Actual subscribe lives in
        FLEET-034 follow-up sub-gaps.
    
    (e) crates/chump-coord/src/bin/chump-fleet.rs — supervisor. Spawns
        N tokio tasks each running `chump-worker` as a subprocess.
        On worker exit, restarts with linear 5s backoff (exponential
        deferred). SIGTERM / SIGINT trigger graceful shutdown via a
        watch::channel. Per-worker session_id is
        `chump-fleet-<pid>-<i>`. CHUMP_WORKER_BIN env honored to
        override the path to chump-worker.
    
    (f) Backward-compat shims:
        - scripts/dispatch/worker.sh   — ~25 LOC feature-flag block at
          top: if CHUMP_WORKER_RUST=1, exec chump-worker "$@"; legacy
          1908 LOC bash body preserved unchanged below.
        - scripts/dispatch/run-fleet.sh — same pattern; legacy 750
          LOC bash body preserved unchanged below. Translates
          FLEET_SIZE=N env to --size N when no flags given.
    
    (g) Smoke test scripts/ci/test-chump-worker-rust.sh: builds both
        binaries; asserts --help banners; runs single-iteration
        chump-worker against a synth state.db (sqlite3 schema bootstrap
        matching gap-store v6 columns); asserts the test gap got
        claimed (lease row written) with CHUMP_WORKER_EXEC_OVERRIDE=
        /usr/bin/true mocking the child; asserts capability filter
        (python worker MUST NOT claim rust-tagged gap; rust worker
        DOES); asserts 2-worker fleet against 5 pickable gaps with 0
        lease collisions. CHUMP_REPO and CHUMP_REPO_ROOT both set to
        the fake repo so ambient emits don't leak to the real
        repo's ambient.jsonl.
    
    Phase 1 NON-goals (explicitly deferred):
      - Decommissioning the bash bodies (follow-up after parallel-run window)
      - NATS PUSH subscribe implementation (FLEET-034)
      - KV CapabilityManifest publish (INFRA-1760 follow-up)
      - Speculative `replicas: N` envelopes (INFRA-311)
      - Worker_heartbeat / worker_restarted ambient kinds (would require
        EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml edits — forbidden by Phase 1 hygiene; deferred
        to a sub-gap that explicitly carries the registry edit)
      - git2::Worktree migration (defer until a second caller justifies the dep)
    
    Closes the META-107 Rust-First Migration Blueprint umbrella (6 of 6
    sub-gaps shipped or in-flight: INFRA-1997 / INFRA-1998 / INFRA-1999 /
    INFRA-2000 / INFRA-2001 + this one).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Existing chump-coord crate gains pub mod worker with submodules capability / loop_body / worktree
    - "capability module: WorkerCapability struct + from_env(WORKER_SKILLS/MACHINE/BACKEND) + matches(&GapRow) picker filter + to_manifest() adapter to INFRA-1760 CapabilityManifest"
    - "loop_body module: run_one_cycle(&CycleEnv) -> CycleOutcome — PULL-mode happy path against state.db; pick_eligible_gap; spawn `chump --execute-gap` as tokio::process::Child with FLEET_TIMEOUT_S budget"
