- id: INFRA-2006
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: A2A inbox-routing bug — --to <lease-session-id> writes to wrong inbox file; receivers read from worktree-derived session not lease-id"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Catalyst: 2026-05-25 wizard session sent 8 A2A messages to lease-IDs.
    All landed in inbox/<lease-id>.jsonl but receivers read from
    inbox/chump-Chump-NNN.jsonl. Messages 'delivered' but never 'seen'.
    
    Root cause: lease.session_id (an arbitrary daemon-spawned token) is
    NOT the session_id the worker uses when calling chump-inbox.sh read.
    Workers without explicit CHUMP_SESSION_ID derive a worktree-based ID.
    
    Two readers can also collide on the same generic inbox file (e.g.
    multiple agents in main checkout all read .chump-locks/inbox/chump-Chump-NNN.jsonl).
    Mail-bag collision is the next bug class once this lands.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - When broadcast.sh --to <recipient-id> matches an active lease.session_id, ALSO write to the inbox file the recipient actually reads from (the worktree-derived or env-set CHUMP_SESSION_ID of the agent that holds the lease)
    - "Resolution: scan .chump-locks/inbox/ for the most-recently-updated inbox file owned by the same gap (heuristic 1) OR maintain .chump-locks/session-alias-map.json that ties lease.session_id → reader.session_id when the worker first writes its inbox cursor (heuristic 2)"
    - "Preserve back-compat: still write to .chump-locks/inbox/<lease-id>.jsonl AND to the resolved reader inbox (dual-write so old readers don't break)"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-broadcast-to-lease-id.sh: stub lease at $TMP/.chump-locks/claim-X.json + reader inbox cursor; broadcast --to lease.session_id; assert message landed in BOTH inboxes"
    - "Doc update: docs/process/OPUS_MESSAGE_PROTOCOL.md — note the dual-write behavior so senders understand --to <lease-id> is an alias for the reader-session"
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2817
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

