- id: INFRA-2014
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P0: live inbox injector — daemon watches inbox files + tmux send-keys interrupts to running fleet-worker sessions when new urgency:CRIT message arrives; converts A2A from dead-letter to live signal"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - New daemon scripts/coord/live-inbox-injector.sh (or chump-inbox-injector binary) — uses fswatch (macOS) / inotifywait (Linux) to watch .chump-locks/inbox/*.jsonl files for appended lines; detection latency <1s p95
    - "On new line append: parse JSON, extract urgency + to (recipient session-id) + body fields; if urgency == \"CRIT\" AND a tmux pane matches the recipient session-id (via tmux list-panes -F pattern matching), send Ctrl-C + the message text via tmux send-keys to interrupt the worker"
    - "Recipient identification: parse pane name pattern fleet-worker-N / curator-opus-* / wizard-* etc. to map session-id → tmux target. Documented mapping table in scripts/coord/live-inbox-injector-routes.yaml. Fallback: when no tmux pane matches, fall back to writing an interrupt-flag file at .chump-locks/inbox/<session-id>.interrupt that the recipient session polls (existing pattern)"
    - "Events emitted: kind=live_inbox_inject_attempted (fields: recipient_session, message_id, urgency, target_pane_found bool) on each detection; kind=live_inbox_inject_succeeded on successful send-keys; kind=live_inbox_inject_failed (fields: reason — pane_not_found / send_keys_error / parse_error) on failure"
    - "Cost tracking: per-invocation logs duration_ms + pane_lookup_count to .chump-locks/live-inbox-injector-metrics.jsonl; chump waste-tally consumes via existing log-tailing pattern; cost target <50ms per inject (CPU-cheap; only fswatch + tmux send-keys roundtrip)"
    - "Failure-class taxonomy: TRANSIENT — tmux send-keys returns non-zero (auto-retry once after 200ms); PERMANENT — no tmux pane matches recipient AND no fallback file write possible (emit live_inbox_inject_failed reason=pane_not_found and DO NOT retry); MALFORMED — JSON parse fails on inbox line (log + skip; do not retry; emit live_inbox_inject_failed reason=parse_error)"
    - launchd plist scripts/launchd/com.chump.live-inbox-injector.plist — KeepAlive=true (daemon, not interval-triggered); ProgramArguments + Description keys per INFRA-2046 audit class; installs via scripts/setup/chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-live-inbox-injector.sh: (a) write a urgency:CRIT message to a fake inbox file; assert kind=live_inbox_inject_attempted within 2s; (b) with no matching tmux pane, assert fallback file written at .chump-locks/inbox/<session>.interrupt; (c) malformed JSON line, assert skipped + emit kind=live_inbox_inject_failed reason=parse_error"
    - EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml entries kind=live_inbox_inject_attempted + live_inbox_inject_succeeded + live_inbox_inject_failed; allowlist entries in scripts/ci/event-registry-reserved.txt
  notes: |
    [2026-05-27T19:43:20Z] AC backfilled 2026-05-27 by curator-opus-shepherd (was TODO placeholder; violates operator no-TODO rule). Implementation shape: fswatch-based daemon, urgency:CRIT filter, tmux send-keys primary path + interrupt-flag-file fallback. Pairs with INFRA-1932 (A2A roll-out doc) and INFRA-2006 (A2A inbox-routing bug — must be fixed before injector is reliable).
  closed_date: '2026-05-29'
  closed_pr: 2609
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2015
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P1: A2A typed urgency levels — broadcast.sh adds --urgency INFO|WARN|CRIT|EMERGENCY routing"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Today (pre-INFRA-2015): broadcast.sh accepts an event-type
    (INTENT|HANDOFF|STUCK|DONE|WARN|ALERT|FEEDBACK) but those describe
    INTENT not URGENCY. Caller might WARN about something low-priority
    or ALERT about something already-resolved — receiver has no way to
    triage.
    
    With urgency: sender declares "this needs response in <window>"
    independently from event-type. Routing layer matches urgency to
    delivery mechanism.
