- id: INFRA-2051
  domain: INFRA
  title: "wizard-daemon Step 4 has NO dispatch-outcome detection: re-picks the same gap forever if chump --execute-gap exits without shipping (wheel-spin)"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    wizard-daemon Phase 2 Step 4 (pickable-gap dispatch) is fire-and-forget: it spawns chump --execute-gap <ID> & via subshell, records PID in dispatch-state.json, and walks away. There is NO detection of whether the dispatched process actually shipped the gap. Confirmed 2026-05-27T14:32-14:36Z: wizard dispatched CREDIBLE-069 TWICE (PIDs 16739 + 54221). Both processes exited within minutes WITHOUT creating a worktree, opening a PR, or changing gap status. Wizard's next tick saw gap still status:open → re-picked it → infinite wheel-spin. Without this fix, the autonomous loop is theatre — wizard fires dispatches that go nowhere, consumes API budget, and never advances the queue. Phase B critical for any claim of 'running on auto'. The chump --execute-gap process itself works (it's a multi-tool-call mini-agent that needs ~5-15min to actually ship), but wizard's supervision of it is missing.\n\nROOT CAUSE: Step 4's dispatch state tracks PID only. PID-died != dispatch-shipped. Need outcome-tracking: did gap status flip to 'done'? Did a PR get opened with this gap ID in the title? Did the dispatch process exit non-zero?
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "wizard-daemon Step 4 tracks dispatch outcome: SHIPPED (gap status:done) | PR_OPENED (gh pr list found PR with gap ID) | FAILED (process exited, no PR, no status change after lookback window)"
    - "Per-gap attempt counter persisted in dispatch-state.json — after CHUMP_WIZARD_MAX_DISPATCH_ATTEMPTS (default 3) failures, gap is marked wizard_skip:true automatically (with reason annotation in gap notes)"
    - After N consecutive failed dispatches on the SAME gap, emit kind=wizard_dispatch_giveup ambient event so operator sees the pattern
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-wizard-daemon-dispatch-outcome.sh: 4 fixture scenarios — happy-path-ship, dispatch-exits-no-pr, dispatch-creates-pr-not-merged, dispatch-3-fails-mark-skip"
    - "Wheel-spin protection: same gap cannot be dispatched twice within DISPATCH_GAP_COOLDOWN_S (default 1800 = 30min) regardless of attempt counter"
    - "Update INFRA-2049's dead-PID pruner: prune NOT JUST dead PIDs but also entries where dispatch outcome was FAILED >cooldown ago"
  closed_date: '2026-05-27'
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2052
  domain: INFRA
  title: "CREDIBLE P2: operator_recovery_requested event schema mismatch — recovery-queue-emit.sh emits prs=CSV+cluster_gap_id+authorizing_session whereas chump ambient emit naturally emits pr=N+source+session; recovery-queue-service.sh may consume only the INFRA-1993 shape, dropping direct ambient emits; document canonical schema + add schema-aware consumer"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Document the canonical schema for kind=operator_recovery_requested events in a new section of docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml (or wherever per-kind schemas are formally specified). REQUIRED fields ts kind authorizing_session reason. OPTIONAL fields prs (CSV string) or pr (single int) or both. OPTIONAL cluster_gap_id. The schema must explicitly tolerate BOTH (a) one-event-per-PR with pr=N (chump ambient emit shape) and (b) one-event-per-cluster with prs=CSV (INFRA-1993 recovery-queue-emit.sh shape)
    - "recovery-queue-service.sh consumer is schema-aware: when an event has prs=CSV it processes each PR in the CSV; when an event has pr=N (single) it processes just that PR; when both present prs wins. Today (2026-05-27) the daemon may consume only the INFRA-1993 prs+cluster_gap_id+authorizing_session shape and silently drop events with the chump-ambient-emit pr+source+session shape — verify this assumption via grep + fix"
    - "Field-name reconciliation: today's two shapes are inconsistent. Specifically (1) recovery-queue-emit.sh emits authorizing_session whereas chump ambient emit emits session; (2) recovery-queue-emit.sh emits source=recovery_queue_emit literal whereas chump ambient emit emits source from --source flag (e.g. curator-opus-shepherd-2026-05-23). The daemon should accept BOTH forms; the canonical schema doc must list both as valid"
    - "Real-world trigger today 2026-05-27 14:03Z: shepherd inline-emitted operator_recovery_requested via chump ambient emit operator_recovery_requested --source curator-opus-shepherd-2026-05-23 --field pr=2633 --field reason=... ; PR #2633 did land at 14:30Z but it may have been wizard's manual admin-merge after seeing shepherd's 14:10Z A2A DONE, not auto-recovery-queue-service consumption. Investigation: was the chump-ambient-emit-shape event consumed by the daemon at all, or did it sit unconsumed?"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-operator-recovery-schema.sh: emit one event in each shape (chump ambient emit form + recovery-queue-emit.sh form); start a recovery-queue-service.sh in mock-mode (no actual admin-merge); assert BOTH events get processed (i.e. each one results in the mock executing-cycle log entry). Currently expected to fail until reconciliation lands"
    - Pairs with INFRA-1993 (the emit producer) and recovery-queue-service.sh (the consumer); this gap is the contract / schema reconciliation between them
    - "Documentation: docs/process/RECOVERY_QUEUE_PROTOCOL.md if it exists OR add to docs/process/THE_FLOOR_PRIMITIVES.md describing the dual-shape acceptance rule; cross-link from chump ambient emit --help"
