  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Bidirectional YAML <-> state.db sync. Three modes: sync --pull (YAML
    files in docs/gaps/ become source-of-truth; state.db rows updated to
    match); sync --push (state.db rows become source-of-truth; YAML files
    updated to match); sync --check (compare both; exit non-zero on any
    drift; no mutations). Closes the failure mode that bit the shepherd
    6+ times today: had to direct-sqlite UPDATE state.db because
    `chump gap reserve` writes TODO ACs that `chump gap set` then can't
