- id: INFRA-2055
  domain: INFRA
  title: chump --execute-gap MUST emit kind=gap_shipped|gap_blocked|gap_deferred before exit — eliminates silent-exit wheel-spin class that bit wizard-daemon today
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    chump --execute-gap is a multi-tool-call mini-agent that can exit silently without emitting a structured outcome. This is exactly what bit wizard-daemon today (2026-05-27T14:32-14:36Z): the wizard dispatched CREDIBLE-069 twice, both processes exited within ~3min without creating a PR or changing gap status, wizard had no signal to detect failure → wheel-spin. INFRA-2051 (in flight) adds heuristic outcome detection (PID-dead + no-PR + gap-still-open + >timeout = FAILED). But the AUTHORITATIVE fix is to make chump --execute-gap itself ALWAYS emit one of three terminal kinds before exit. Then wizard reads the explicit kind, not heuristic. Eliminates the silent-exit class entirely.\n\nFIX: wrap the chump --execute-gap exit path so EVERY path (success, error, timeout, ctrl-c, panic) emits exactly one of:\n  kind=gap_shipped {gap_id, pr_number, commit_sha}\n  kind=gap_blocked {gap_id, reason, recoverable_by}\n  kind=gap_deferred {gap_id, reason, defer_until_event}
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump --execute-gap exit handler installs trap (Rust: Drop impl or process::exit wrapper) that always emits one of gap_shipped/gap_blocked/gap_deferred to ambient.jsonl"
    - On panic or ctrl-c, emit kind=gap_blocked with reason=panic_or_signal and exit non-zero
    - Register the 3 new kinds in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml plus event-registry-reserved.txt single-commit lease pattern
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-execute-gap-always-emits.sh covers: (a) happy-path-emits-gap_shipped, (b) silent-exit-emits-gap_blocked, (c) explicit-defer-emits-gap_deferred, (d) ctrl-c-emits-gap_blocked-with-signal-reason"
    - "wizard-daemon Step 4 outcome detection (INFRA-2051) gains a PREFERRED path: read gap_shipped/blocked/deferred events from ambient before falling back to PID-dead heuristic. Heuristic stays as defense-in-depth for legacy chump --execute-gap that didn't emit."
  closed_date: '2026-05-27'
  closed_pr: 2639
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2056
  domain: INFRA
  title: chump --execute-gap emits kind=subagent_heartbeat every 60s during execution — wizard-daemon can detect silent-death within 2min instead of inferring from PID checks
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    chump --execute-gap is a multi-minute mini-agent. Today's wizard-daemon trial showed 'process alive' is a weak signal — process can be ALIVE but stuck (network call hung), or recently dead (we don't know when it died). Strengthen with active heartbeat: every 60s, emit kind=subagent_heartbeat with fields {gap_id, pid, last_action, iter_count}. Wizard-daemon Step 4 outcome detection (INFRA-2051) gains: if heartbeat >120s stale → infer agent is dying/dead, escalate sooner than the 15min FAILED timeout. Pairs with INFRA-2055 (mandatory outcome emit on exit) — heartbeat handles the 'agent stuck but didn't crash' case, outcome-emit handles 'agent exited cleanly'.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump --execute-gap emits kind=subagent_heartbeat every 60s during execution with fields gap_id, pid, last_action (e.g. last tool name), iter_count (tool call count)
    - Register kind in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml + event-registry-reserved.txt
    - "wizard-daemon Step 4 (INFRA-2051) gains heartbeat-staleness check: if last subagent_heartbeat for active dispatch is >120s old, infer agent dying, record outcome=STUCK + remove from active"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-execute-gap-heartbeat.sh: synth a long-running execute-gap, assert heartbeats every ~60s in ambient.jsonl"
  closed_date: '2026-05-27'
  closed_pr: 2648
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2057
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P1: chump cron subcommand — declarative cron expr to launchd plist (macOS) / systemd timer (Linux) generator; idempotent install + uninstall; never depends on Claude Code or any specific agent session being alive"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "New chump cron subcommand with at least install + uninstall + status actions. Surface: chump cron install --name NAME --schedule CRON_EXPR --exec COMMAND [--description TEXT] [--working-dir PATH] [--env KEY=VAL] [--stdout-log PATH] [--stderr-log PATH]"
    - "Backend selection by platform: macOS uses launchd plist generation under ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.chump.NAME.plist OR /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.chump.NAME.plist (chump cron install --scope user|system selects); Linux uses systemd user-unit at ~/.config/systemd/user/chump-NAME.timer + chump-NAME.service. Auto-detected via uname; explicit override via env CHUMP_CRON_BACKEND=launchd|systemd"
    - Cron expression supports full 5-field cron syntax (M H DoM Mon DoW) PLUS launchd-native StartInterval seconds shorthand via --interval Ns (translates to StartInterval on launchd, OnUnitActiveSec on systemd). EVERY plist generated MUST have either StartCalendarInterval entries OR StartInterval — never both omitted (INFRA-1929 prune-worktrees plist class)
    - "Idempotent: chump cron install on an existing name with identical config is a no-op + exit 0. With changed config, stops + reloads atomically. chump cron uninstall --name NAME removes from disk + bootout from launchd (or stop+disable from systemd). chump cron uninstall on non-existent is a no-op + exit 0 (not error)"
    - All Chump-managed plists are tagged with a sentinel comment + a Label prefix com.chump. so chump cron list (sibling INFRA-2046) can distinguish them from operator-owned plists. Refuse to manage plists outside the com.chump.* label space
    - "On install, emits ambient kind=chump_cron_installed with fields name, schedule, exec, backend, scope. On uninstall emits kind=chump_cron_uninstalled. PER WIZARD 2026-05-27 13:27Z: use the INFRA-2003/2020 lease pattern — single-commit add to scripts/ci/event-registry-reserved.txt allowlist (with reason 'INFRA-2045 chump cron lifecycle, emitted by crates/chump-cron/src/lib.rs'), hold off docs/observability/EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml entry until the first runtime fire reveals the actual emit shape"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-chump-cron-install.sh: install a synthetic schedule, assert plist exists + launchctl list shows it loaded; wait one fire-window, assert exec ran (via stdout-log presence); uninstall, assert plist removed + launchctl no longer lists it. Linux variant tested via container or skipped on non-Linux runners with appropriate marker"
    - "Backward-compat: ALL existing scripts/setup/install-NAME-launchd.sh scripts continue to work; chump cron is a NEW surface, not a replacement. Migration of existing 20+ launchd installers to chump-cron management is a SEPARATE follow-up sub-gap"
    - "Capability lives in NEW Rust crate crates/chump-cron/ per META-064 Rust-first criteria (mutates canonical state under ~/Library/LaunchAgents or /Library/LaunchDaemons; durable beyond 3mo; will exceed 200 LOC at first commit). NOT bash. Wizard-confirmed 2026-05-27 13:27Z. chump cron CLI is the harness-neutral surface per OPERATOR_PLAYBOOK Section 5"
    - "Documentation: chump cron --help shows full CLI; docs/process/SCHEDULING_LAYERS.md (DOC-058 sibling) references chump cron as the durable layer; CLAUDE.md adds a Scheduling discipline section linking to it"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

