- id: INFRA-2100
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: self-hosted runner cargo-registry corruption for tauri-2.11.2 (bundle.global.js missing) — needs runner-side cargo clean -p tauri or actions cache invalidation"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Diagnosis: `cargo build` on any PR touching src/ that triggers chump-desktop recompile fails with `tauri::generate_context!() proc macro panicked` + `failed to read plugin global API script .../tauri-2.11.2/scripts/bundle.global.js: No such file or directory`. Observed PR #2692 (EFFECTIVE-025) 2026-05-28T13:21Z. Class: cargo registry corruption sibling of INFRA-2082 silent-build-failure.\n2. Reproduce on each self-hosted runner: `ls ~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-*/tauri-2.11.2/scripts/bundle.global.js` returns non-existent file. Full tauri-2.11.2 contents are partially extracted.\n3. Fix (operator-side, ~5 min): on each self-hosted Mac runner (chump-runner{,-2,-3,-4}), run `rm -rf ~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-*/tauri-2.11.2/` then trigger a re-fetch via any cargo invocation that depends on tauri.\n4. Prevention: add `Swatinem/rust-cache@v2` with `cache-key-suffix: tauri-2.11.2-rev2` bump to force a fresh registry pull, OR add a pre-build step that verifies `tauri/scripts/bundle.global.js` exists and re-fetches if missing.\n5. Future detection: INFRA-2098 (chump_cargo_build wrapper) already detects the `proc macro panicked` class with `kind=cargo_registry_corruption` ambient emit. Wire that wrapper into the cargo-test step (or a preflight step) to convert the silent panic into a structured failure pointing at the fix."
  notes: |
    2026-05-28T17:00Z: TRIAGE applied — `cargo fetch` from a worktree extracted tauri-2.11.2 to ~/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-*/tauri-2.11.2/ (the missing dir). bundle.global.js now present. Runner shares ~/.cargo (same user), so the next CI run picks it up.
    
    ROOT CAUSE: NOT corrupted tarball (tarball is healthy — 142 files, includes scripts/bundle.global.js). The bug is the EXTRACTED registry/src/ directory being missing or partial when tauri-build's proc-macro runs.
    
    WHY IT RECURS: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2 post-step deletes ~/.cargo/registry/src/ before saving the cache (per its docs: src/ is regenerated by cargo on first build). On restore + parallel cargo invocations, extraction can race or partially complete — proc-macro reads bundle.global.js before extraction finishes.
    
    DURABLE FIXES (operator-pick):
      A) Add `cargo fetch --locked` step BEFORE cargo test/clippy in ci.yml (forces sequential extraction; ~10-30s warm cost)
      B) Bump Swatinem `prefix-key` to invalidate stale caches across all jobs (~10-20min warm cost on first run)
      C) Disable Swatinem `cache-target-dir` for jobs that build tauri (keeps src/ around)
    
    RECOMMENDATION: Fix A is the cheapest + most surgical. File as INFRA-2101 sub-gap if INFRA-2100 stays open for the runner-side hygiene.
    
    NEXT: PR #2693 INFRA-2098 CI is rerunning right now (no failures yet) — should clear with the one-time tauri-2.11.2 extraction in place.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

