- id: INFRA-2106
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump gen broken on Mac default config — local provider expects gpt-5-mini (not on PATH), cloud cascade returns tool-use that doesn't parse"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "- Repro: cd /tmp/some-non-rust-project && chump gen \"create file foo.txt with content bar\" --work-dir /tmp/some-non-rust-project\n- Symptom A (default cascade): \"Local API error 404 Not Found: model 'gpt-5-mini' not found\". Hardcoded local model = gpt-5-mini, local provider URL = http://localhost:8000/v1 (vllm-mlx) or http://localhost:8001/v1, neither running by default on dev Mac.\n- Symptom B (CHUMP_GEN_PROVIDER=anthropic): cloud route returns tool-call syntax like `<function/run_cli>{\"command\": \"echo ok\"}` but chump gen parses only `===FILE===` blocks. Result: \"LLM response contained no parseable file edits\". Tool-use trained models (Claude, GPT) can't be steered to file-block output without explicit prompt tuning.\n- Symptom C (--local + OPENAI_API_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1 → ollama): chump fails with \"model HTTP unreachable (daemon down)\" even though `curl http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags` succeeds. Likely connection-handling bug or timeout mismatch in chump's local-LLM HTTP client.\n- Fix one of: (a) update default local model to one that actually runs on dev Mac (qwen3:14b or similar from ollama), (b) auto-fallback model resolution: probe local endpoints, pick a model that exists, (c) update cloud cascade prompt to force ===FILE=== block output for tool-use models OR teach chump gen to accept tool-call responses by mapping them to file ops.\n- Verify: `chump gen \"create test.txt with hello\" --work-dir /tmp/scratch` succeeds with cloud or local provider, produces a git commit.\n- Discovered: 2026-05-28 trying to demo chump gen on ehippy/derelict (external TypeScript repo). Coord primitives (claim, work-board, emit) worked perfectly; chump gen was the only broken link."
  closed_date: '2026-05-29'
  closed_pr: 2698
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2107
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: chump-coord work-board complete needs Open→Claimed→Complete; auto-claim on direct complete OR clearer error"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "- Repro:\n    $ chump-coord work-board post some-gap class \"title\"\n    SUBTASK-abc12345\n    $ chump-coord work-board complete SUBTASK-abc12345\n    [chump-coord] cannot complete SUBTASK-abc12345: subtask is in state Open, not the expected state\n- Root cause: the work-board state machine requires Open → Claimed → Complete. `complete` rejects subtasks in `Open` because it expects them to have been claimed first. Discovered while closing the derelict demo loop on 2026-05-28.\n- Why this hurts: a single-agent flow (or operator running the demo solo) wants to mark \"I did the work\" without first claiming. The current message names the *state* but not the *missing transition*, so the next thing the user tries is usually `claim` then re-`complete` after squinting.\n- Fix options (pick one):\n    (a) Allow `work-board complete` from `Open` directly when there's no other claimant; emit a one-line note that the implicit claim was performed.\n    (b) Improve the error message to be remedy-shaped: `cannot complete SUBTASK-abc12345 from state Open: run \\`chump-coord work-board claim SUBTASK-abc12345\\` first`.\n- Verify: after fix, the demo loop (post → complete on a single agent) works without a manual claim step. Or, the error message names the exact next command to run.\n- Cross-references: discovered during INFRA-2102 Phase 2 / derelict end-to-end demo. See docs/strategy/NATS_A2A_DEMO_2026-05-28.md."
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

