  title: "RESILIENT P0: disk-pressure structural fix — chump-runner/cargo-target grows unbounded (43G debug, 109M release); cargo-target-reaper INFRA-2125 doesn't cover ~/.cache/chump-runner path; will crash at scale"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Reproduce: du -sh ~/.cache/chump-runner/cargo-target → expect >10GB; the dir is populated by `cargo install --path ... --bin chump --force` which uses CARGO_TARGET_DIR=$HOME/.cache/chump-runner/cargo-target. INFRA-2125 cargo-target-reaper does NOT scan this path; it only covers target/, /tmp/chump-*, and ~/.cache/chump-fleet-target (different dir)"
    - "Fix A (minimum): extend scripts/ops/cargo-target-reaper.sh reaping list to include ~/.cache/chump-runner/cargo-target/{debug,release} with mtime-based pruning (default 7d, same as fleet-target). Add safety guard: skip if any chump-* binary in that path has been touched < 24h ago (likely active install in progress)"
    - "Fix B (structural): the chump-runner cache exists because chump install uses a separate CARGO_TARGET_DIR for predictable upgrade behavior. Audit whether we still need a SEPARATE target dir or can point install at the workspace target. If we keep separate: add `cargo install --keep-going false --offline` semantics where possible"
    - "Fix C (cap-based): add CHUMP_DISK_CRITICAL_GB env (default 20) — when df reports less than this on /System/Volumes/Data, trigger aggressive reap (drop --fingerprint-age to 1d, drop --fleet-age to 2d). Wire into the chump-disk-health-monitor daemon emit kind=disk_critical → reaper aggressive-mode handler"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-cargo-target-reaper-runner-scope.sh: synth a fake ~/.cache/chump-runner/cargo-target/debug populated with old fingerprints; run reaper; assert files pruned + disk-free recovered amount logged"
    - "Trigger validation: install the updated reaper plist + run `launchctl start dev.chump.cargo-target-reaper`; capture df-before / df-after in /tmp/chump-cargo-target-reaper.out.log; assert at least 5GB reclaimed when starting from <20GB free state"
  notes: |
    Filed 2026-05-29 by curator-opus-shepherd. Observed: disk_critical alerts fired all day; manual cleanup reclaimed 22GB by removing target/release + stale worktrees. ~/.cache/chump-runner/cargo-target/debug=43G is the next big chunk but cargo install is actively using it. Without the structural fix this will recur every few days. Sibling: INFRA-2125 cargo-target-reaper (shipped today) + INFRA-1170 worktree-orphan-target reaper (older).
  closed_date: '2026-06-05'
  closed_pr: 2963
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

