- id: INFRA-2202
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: AGENTS.md communication policy — NATS broadcast vs inbox DM channel boundaries"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Operator observation: agents have been reaching for the inbox file (.chump-locks/inbox/<session-id>.jsonl) when the right channel is NATS broadcast (chump.events.>) — e.g. design-feedback requests, status FYIs, fanout asks. The inbox is for ADDRESSED DMs that need acknowledgment; broadcasts are for now-ish fanout. Mixing them slows responses (inbox is per-recipient loop tick; NATS is PreToolUse digest minutes-ish) AND clutters inboxes peers actually need to scan. Codify the channel boundaries in AGENTS.md so every harness follows them. Add it between the GraphQL exhaustion section and the docs index.
