    - AGENTS.md gets a new section 'Communication channels — what goes where' between the GraphQL exhaustion section and 'Where to find docs'
    - Section names the four channels (NATS broadcast / inbox DM / ambient.jsonl emit / heartbeat-lease) and the kind of message each carries
    - "Section calls out the anti-patterns: using inbox for design fanout, polling ambient.jsonl in a busy loop, manufacturing liveness signals, addressing 5 curators individually when one broadcast would do"
    - "Section provides a quick decision table: 'I want a design vote / FYI / proposal' to broadcast; 'I need specific session X to do Y' to inbox; 'I made an observable change' to ambient emit; 'Am I alive' to heartbeat"
    - Cross-references OPUS_MESSAGE_PROTOCOL.md for inbox format and broadcast.sh for NATS format
    - No code or daemon changes; doc-only
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2745
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2203
