  description: |
    chump-fleet-recorder inserts events with NULL gap_id/session_id/subject even though the schema declares all three as TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''. Currently 14000+ rows in .chump/fleet_events.db are NULL. The server's row_to_event was patched in INFRA-2189 to tolerate this via Option-aware reads, but the contract is still broken: the segmenter's SQL also has to special-case, and any downstream consumer hits the same hazard. Fix at the source: recorder INSERT path coerces None to '' before binding. Backfill the existing rows in a one-shot migration.
