- id: INFRA-2209
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P0: AGENTS.md — enforce consensus-over-operator-pinging discipline; team uses NATS A2A FEEDBACK consensus for decisions when operator not present"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Per operator directive 2026-05-29T23:55Z: Claude Code agents (Opus orchestrator + curator-opus-* + Sonnet sub-agents) often bounce questions to the operator. Operator is not always present to answer. The team must self-resolve via NATS A2A consensus instead. This needs to land in AGENTS.md as enforced discipline, not advisory hint.\n\n## Doctrine to land in AGENTS.md\n\nNew section (suggested placement: after current \"Coordination\" or \"Mission\" section, before \"Hard rules\"):\n\n### Decision protocol — consensus over operator-pinging\n\nWhen you reach a decision point that has more than one reasonable answer (architecture choice, naming, sequencing, scope split, tradeoff), DO NOT bounce the question to the operator. Use the team consensus protocol:\n\n1. **Ask via NATS FEEDBACK**: `scripts/coord/broadcast.sh FEEDBACK proposal \"<your question + 2-3 options with tradeoffs>\"`. Dual-publishes to ambient.jsonl + NATS subject chump.events.feedback so every curator-opus-* subscriber sees it.\n\n2. **Target specific curators with --to <name>** for lane-specific weigh-in (e.g. handoff for typed-contract questions, ci-audit for flake decisions, harvester for prior-art checks, observability for telemetry decisions).\n\n3. **For real-time consensus**: orchestrator dispatches each curator as Agent sub-agent with focused brief. Sub-agent reads its inbox, evaluates question through its lane, replies via broadcast.sh FEEDBACK. Aggregator (orchestrator OR future chump-consensus-aggregator-daemon per META-125) tallies + decides at quorum-or-timeout.\n\n4. **Operator escalation gate**: only ping operator when (a) consensus genuinely deadlocks at quorum, OR (b) decision requires operator personal authority (license/legal/spend/identity/permissions on external systems). Default = consensus.\n\n5. **Recording**: every consensus decision emits ambient kind=consensus_decision_emitted with the question, votes, rationale, decision. Audit trail for later replay.\n\n6. **Today's working pattern** (manual, until META-125 productizes): orchestrator dispatches N curators via Agent tool in single message (parallel). Curators reply within 5 min. Decision aggregated by orchestrator, broadcast back. This works TODAY without waiting for META-125 daemons. See session 2026-05-29 for repeated successful uses (META-124 review, META-125 review, sequence-alignment).\n\n## Concrete deliverables\n\n1. Edit AGENTS.md to insert the above section (or its tightened version) in a sensible spot.\n2. Update CLAUDE.md to cross-reference the new AGENTS.md section under §Hard rules OR §Mission section.\n3. Update SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md to remind dispatched Sonnets to use consensus, not operator pings.\n4. (Stretch) Add a CI check that scans claude session logs for \"should I\" / \"would you like me to\" questions to operator — log them as ambient kind=operator_ping_anti_pattern for audit.\n5. Voice-lint clean.\n\n## Cross-references\n\n- META-125 (consensus pipeline umbrella — productizes this discipline)\n- META-127 (curator suite — this discipline is part of the standardized role template)\n- INFRA-2185 (ring-the-bell — adjacent live-substrate piece)\n- Today's repeated successful manual-consensus uses (META-124 review, sequence-alignment)"
  closed_pr: 2757
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

