  title: "EFFECTIVE: fleet-scrubber lane sort — most-recently-active first (Marcus-grade UX polish)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Live observation on http://localhost:7070/scrubber/ — the per-session lanes render in whatever order they fall out of the API response (effectively sqlite ORDER BY session_id ASC). Result: my chump-Chump-* session sits randomly mid-list, sub-Sonnets are scattered, curators clump together. For Marcus-grade demo + my own daily use, the most-recently-active session should be at the top, with stale/idle sessions sinking to the bottom. Sort key: MAX(events.ts_ms) per session_id, DESC. Implementation: server-side in /api/segments response (return lanes already sorted) OR client-side in the scrubber render (after fetchData, sort allSegments groups by max ts). Server-side is cheaper to render but a frontend sort is simpler and doesn't require an API contract change.
