  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    crates/chump-fleet-recorder/src/main.rs test 'ambient_tail_ingests_new_lines' uses tokio::time::timeout(800ms) wrapped around the infinite ambient_tail_loop, which polls every 250ms (AMBIENT_POLL_INTERVAL_MS). On CI with shared runners + cargo-test parallelism, 800ms may not allow even one poll cycle to land the row before the timeout. Flake observed during INFRA-2203 ship (operator-reported 2026-05-30T01:50Z). Pre-existing; not from INFRA-2203. Fix: replace the fixed-budget timeout with a poll-until-success loop bounded at 5s ceiling so the test passes deterministically when the ingestion lands, and fails fast (with a clear assertion) when it doesn't.
