    - crates/chump-curator-supervisor/ Rust daemon, StartInterval 300s, iterates the 6 productized curators (shepherd/target/handoff/ci-audit/decompose/md-links); four checks per role — error-pattern (regex 'unknown subcommand
    - Traceback
    - panic
    - "fatal:"
    - exit 1' >2× in last 50 log lines), silent-stall (no heartbeat ambient event >10min), crash-loop (log file growing only with error-class lines), productivity-drop (zero state.db mutations attributed to session_id in 1h)
    - Fingerprint (role + error_pattern_hash); dedupe via sentinel .chump-locks/curator-supervisor/seen/<fp>.sentinel with 24h TTL; novel failures get chump gap reserve + chump gap set with last 20 log lines as evidence; P0 multi-curator outage, P1 single
    - "Remediation: DEFAULT AGGRESSIVE (operator-chosen 2026-05-30). Supervisor files gap AND spawns Sonnet inline via claude -p with the SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md epilogue + the gap-id as task. Env override CHUMP_CURATOR_SUPERVISOR_MODE=conservative falls back to file-only"
    - "Auto-restart: DEFAULT ON (operator-chosen 2026-05-30). Supervisor tmux respawn-pane t chump-curators:<role> with the fleet-autopilot canonical command after filing. Verifies new pane heartbeats within 60s via ambient.jsonl tail; if no heartbeat, emits kind=curator_respawn_failed and escalates to operator via NATS WARN. Env override CHUMP_CURATOR_SUPERVISOR_AUTORESTART=0 disables"
    - Emit ambient kind=curator_failure_paged on filing AND kind=curator_respawned on successful respawn; both registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml per INFRA-754
    - launchd plist scripts/setup/launchd/com.chump.curator-supervisor.plist installed by chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh; bootstrap --check exits 0 with supervisor running
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-curator-supervisor.sh: synth a broken-curator log + heartbeat history → supervisor detects + files + (in test mode) emits would-spawn-Sonnet event + would-respawn-pane event; second tick respects sentinel dedupe"
