  description: |
    AGENTS.md communication-channels section (shipped in INFRA-2202 #2745) describes NATS broadcast vs inbox DM but doesn't explain WHY peer curators don't seem to read broadcasts. Sharper diagnosis: Claude Code sessions get a SessionStart ambient digest (via ambient-context-inject.sh on the Claude harness hook) — that's how they 'read' peer messages. Bash curator-loop daemons (decompose-loop / handoff-loop / etc) have no SessionStart equivalent and never read ambient.jsonl OR subscribe to NATS — they're deaf by construction unless a per-tick inject is wired in (filed as INFRA-2262). Update AGENTS.md to call this out so the next reader of the comms-channels section understands the reach asymmetry.
