    - Section explicitly names the 6 productized bash loops + their current deafness status
    - "Includes a worked example: 'I broadcast FEEDBACK on NATS at 12:00 — wizard sees it at 12:05 SessionStart digest; decompose-loop never sees it'"
    - Cross-references INFRA-2262 (quick-win inject)
    - Section also notes that broadcasts go to BOTH NATS jetstream AND ambient.jsonl (dual-publish in broadcast.sh emit_to_nats) so a NATS outage doesn't break fanout — the file-based channel is the durable one
    - No code change; doc-only
    - chump preflight green
