- id: INFRA-2294
  domain: INFRA
  title: PWA cockpit + scrubber unification — best-in-class HITL fleet UX consensus (3 options A/B/C + role-grouping sub-question)
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    STRATEGIC: best-in-class HITL fleet visualization. Operator directive 2026-05-30T16:00Z: "Does the PWA need to be the end-all be-all? Are there two tools? We need the team's consensus on this, not mine."
    
    Routed via FEEDBACK kind=proposal subject=cockpit-scrubber-unification (broadcast 2026-05-30T16:01Z). Quorum target: 5 of {ci-audit, target, decompose, handoff, harvester, infra-watcher, observability, external-collab}.
    
    EXISTING ARTIFACTS:
      - PWA cockpit at localhost:3737/v2/?view=cockpit (PRODUCT-122)
        5-zone grid: attention queue | inbox | daily-brief | fleet-roster | ambient-tail | quick-actions
        Backed by /api/fleet-status (31 sessions) + /api/ambient/stream SSE
        Components: cockpit.js (54KB), fleet-sidebar.js, operator-attention.js, cost-meter.js, ...
      - Standalone fleet-scrubber at localhost:7070/scrubber/ (INFRA-2164)
        D3 gantt timeline of segments (235 in last 1h across 93 unique sessions)
        Backed by chump-fleet-server (separate from PWA server)
        Strength: forensic replay; Weakness: flat session-id soup, no role-grouping
    
    THREE OPTIONS (vote A/B/C via FEEDBACK kind=vote):
      A. ONE TOOL UNIFIED: kill standalone scrubber URL; embed gantt as drill-down in cockpit's ambient-tail; share components. Pro: single URL, consistent UX. Con: cockpit page weight; gantt load on every visit.
      B. TWO TOOLS CROSS-LINKED: keep both; cockpit=operational, scrubber=forensic. Pro: clear separation, perf-optimized per use case. Con: two URLs, divergent components.
      C. ONE ARTIFACT TWO PRESENTATIONS: single PWA codebase; view=cockpit and view=scrubber-fullscreen as query params. Pro: shared code, deep linking. Con: harder routing, design discipline burden.
    
    SUB-QUESTION (yes/no via FEEDBACK kind=vote, separate corr_id):
      Should fleet-roster render 4-tier role hierarchy (curators / sub-agents nested under spawning curator / claim-* short-lived sessions / 1 operator session) vs current flat session_id list?
    
    DATA-SHAPE BLOCKERS (already-known follow-ups, filed even if vote is C):
      - segments table needs: role (derived from session_id), parent_session (sub-agent → curator nesting), gap_id (currently 0 of 235 carry it)
      - /api/health-summary endpoint (≈ PR #2777 INFRA-1883 dashboard.rs, currently DIRTY)
      - HUD metric tiles to replace daily-brief prose: TRUNK / SHIP-RATE / WORKERS / ATTENTION / COST / TICKS / YOU
    
    Decisive factors per curator vote: (1) single-URL operator desire, (2) forensic-vs-operational perf, (3) component dup cost, (4) BEAST-MODE integration path.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Consensus tallied: \\`scripts/coord/feedback-report.sh --corr-id cockpit-scrubber-unification\\` shows vote distribution A/B/C; deliberator emits kind=consensus_resolved with winning option\n2. Winning option's design doc written under docs/design/COCKPIT_SCRUBBER_UNIFIED.md including: chosen architecture, deprecation/migration plan for the losing artifact, data-shape changes required (role, parent_session, gap_id), routing/URL strategy\n3. Three sub-gaps filed:\n   (a) fleet-sidebar role-grouping (4-tier hierarchy, if sub-question carried)\n   (b) HUD metric strip (7 tiles per design)\n   (c) recorder segments enrichment (role + parent_session + gap_id columns)\n4. Decision doc reviewed by external-collab curator for Marcus-facing impact\n5. Operator sign-off on the design doc before any code lands"
  notes: |
    [2026-05-30T16:04Z] Amendment broadcast cockpit-mission-lens-amendment sent. Mission-layer framing surfaced: my original A/B/C asked the wrong question first. Should be: vote M/G/S on primary organizing lens (Mission / Gap / Session) BEFORE voting A/B/C on tool unification. Reasoning: if Mission lens wins, scrubber becomes a drill-down tool under Mission-first cockpit (favors A or C); if Gap or Session lens wins, scrubber's flat-gantt becomes a peer (favors B). INFRA-2247 (Mission types) + CREDIBLE-071 (Mission Yield digest) added as blockers — design doc cannot lock in until Mission becomes a queryable primitive, not just a title-prefix convention.
  skills_required: "external_repo:repairman29/BEAST-MODE"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

