  title: "fix(INFRA-2130 installer): plist template has invalid XML comments + path substitution uses fallback not found binary"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Two bugs in chump-integrator-daemon installer (shipped in PR #2868) discovered 2026-05-30 during operator-on-behalf install:
    
    BUG 1: Invalid XML comments in .chump/launchd/com.chump.integrator-daemon.plist
      - XML comments cannot contain '--' anywhere except the closing delimiter
      - The plist comments include '--uninstall', '--live', '--status', '--check' (from the docstring listing flag invocations)
      - python3 plistlib.load() fails with: xml.parsers.expat.ExpatError: not well-formed (invalid token): line 14, column 58
      - Effect: install script bombs at plist parse step
      - Workaround used: stripped all comments from installed plist via sed
    
    BUG 2: scripts/setup/install-integrator-daemon.sh substitutes __CARGO_BIN__/chump-integrator with $CARGO_BIN/chump-integrator (defaulting to ~/.cargo/bin/) instead of with the binary path it just found via _find_integrator()
      - Effect: installed plist points to ~/.cargo/bin/chump-integrator which doesn't exist
      - Daemon fails with: /bin/bash: /Users/jeffadkins/.cargo/bin/chump-integrator: No such file or directory
      - Workaround used: sed-fixed the installed plist directly
    
    Both bugs were masked locally because the Sonnet's tests focused on shell logic, not actual launchctl bootstrap + first-run.
