  title: "RESILIENT: sccache + cargo incremental reaper — Mozilla.sccache (20G) + target/debug/incremental (14G) untouched by existing reapers"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    During the 2026-05-30 disk_critical investigation (two ALERTs at 16:45:47Z and
    16:50:18Z, disk at 95-98%), top consumers were:
    
      1. /Users/jeffadkins/Projects/Chump/target = 44G  (active build, correctly protected)
         - debug/deps         = 21G  (don't touch — destroys 30+ min compile state)
         - debug/incremental  = 14G  (SAFE to delete; cargo regenerates lazily)
         - release            = 7.0G (rebuilds on next --release)
      2. ~/Library/Caches/Mozilla.sccache    = 20G  (NO reaper covers this)
      3. /Users/jeffadkins/Projects/Chump/.claude/worktrees = 8.3G  (6 entries)
      4. /private/tmp/chump-meta-181 = 3.1G  (active lease, correctly protected)
    
    Existing reapers (disk-pressure-reaper.sh tier 1-4, cargo-target-reaper.sh,
    target-dir-reaper.sh, stale-worktree-reaper.sh) DO NOT touch:
      - Mozilla.sccache (any tier)
      - target/debug/incremental as a separable subset (only reaps full target/)
    
    SCCACHE_CACHE_SIZE env var is unset; no ~/.config/sccache/config exists.
    sccache default is 10GB cap but local dir is 20G — cap unenforced or stale.
    
    META-128 covers PRE-action disk planning (chump-disk-inventory-daemon, plan/budget
    subcommands). INFRA-2188 covers chump-runner/cargo-target growth. Neither covers
    Mozilla.sccache LRU or incremental-only subset reap. This gap fills the missing
    POST-action retroactive cleanup for these two specific caches.
    
    Why this matters: combined 34G recoverable without touching active build state.
    At tier 3 (5-10GB free), the current reaper freed only 6.6GB by reaping target/
    dirs in tmp worktrees — but sccache+incremental would free 5x that.
