- id: INFRA-2471
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: productize NATS mesh wiring — installer must SET CHUMP_NATS_URL (not just print) + code default-to-localhost so the push-tier can't silently go dark"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - install-nats-server-launchd.sh SETS CHUMP_NATS_URL via launchctl setenv + installs a com.chump.fleet-setenv LaunchAgent (RunAtLoad, reboot-persistent) + appends export to the shell rc — replaces the current advisory-only printf that left the mesh dark for 2 days
    - a checked-in com.chump.fleet-setenv.plist template under scripts/setup/ so reboot-persistence is reproducible on any install
    - "chump-worker.rs + jetstream_consumer.rs default to nats://127.0.0.1:4222 and fall back to pull only on actual connect failure, instead of gating on whether CHUMP_NATS_URL happens to be set (root cause: server up 2 days, push-tier never connected because the env var was unset)"
    - chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --check verifies the broker is reachable via chump-coord ping and warns kind=nats_mesh_dark when the server is up but no client traffic is flowing
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2472
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: lease files are filesystem-local — NATS mesh era needs cross-machine lease registry to prevent invisible collisions"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "[\"Trigger: 2026-06-02 ~00:10Z operator confirmed NATS is ON and BASH_CALL events streaming mesh-wide; but local find .chump-locks/ shows 0 active leases despite Sonnets N/O/P having claimed (their lease files exist only on their machine)\",\"Audit: src/atomic_claim.rs lease creation writes to local .chump-locks/ only — no NATS publish\",\"Real fix: claim either (a) publishes lease assertion via chump-coord to a NATS KV subject like chump.leases.<gap-id> with TTL, OR (b) writes to a shared SQLite/postgres registry that all machines consult\",\"All pre-push hooks + atomic_claim path-overlap checks (INFRA-2434 in flight) MUST consult the shared registry, not just local .chump-locks/\",\"Smoke test scripts/ci/test-multi-machine-lease.sh: simulate 2 sessions on different machines claiming same gap; second one refuses; first ones lease visible to second\",\"Companion to INFRA-2446 (lease-selection by branch) — that gap fixes the local-pick logic; this gap fixes the visibility scope\"]"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

