- id: INFRA-2475
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT: INFRA-NEW-MAIN-RED-emi: preflight gate failure on origin/main (fp=1b092007e862)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    main-preflight-watchdog (INFRA-2397) detected one or more preflight gates failing on origin/main.
    
      - Failing gates: emi,—
      - Fingerprint: 1b092007e862
      - Head SHA: 6b0667fda9907101a793d80126a3c25d6b49ec2d
      - Tick ID: tick-1780445358-70686
    
    This gap was auto-filed by scripts/coord/main-preflight-watchdog-daemon.sh. The fingerprint is sha256(sorted failing-gate names) so a second tick with the same failure set will NOT re-file. A new failing gate will file a new gap.
    
    CONTEXT: The trunk-sentinel daemon watches ci.yml conclusion on main — it does NOT catch preflight/audit-class gates that fail on PR validation but not on main's own post-merge CI. This daemon fills that gap by running chump preflight against origin/main locally.
    
    Recommended workflow:
      1. Run locally: chump preflight  (should reproduce the failure)
      2. Identify the failing gate from: emi,—
      3. Fix the gate or the underlying code issue
      4. When origin/main passes preflight, this daemon will emit main_preflight_recovered and close this gap automatically.
    
    This is a fleet-halt-class wedge: the next PR opened against main will inherit this failure. Fix before picking new work.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "DIAGNOSIS (2026-06-03): NOT a real main-code breakage — core ci.yml is GREEN on origin/main. The watchdog REDs because chump preflight on a clean origin/main (auto-scope skips cargo, no rust changes) runs SCRIPT-scope gates that fail for non-code reasons: (1) pr-hygiene — a PR-context gate (src/preflight.rs:963 INFRA-1854) that false-fails when there is no PR; (2) path-filter-coverage — a real dist allowlist drift (release.yml cargo-dist path not in ci.yml code: filter)."
    - "FIX (belongs in INFRA-2422 domain — src/preflight.rs + scripts/lib/chump-preflight.sh, do NOT stomp): main-health preflight (watchdog/--scope) must EXCLUDE PR-context gates (pr-hygiene, pr-scope) — they are meaningless for \"is origin/main healthy\". Separately add the dist path to ci.yml code: allowlist (parity-gated edit)."
    - "After fix: main-preflight-watchdog re-enable (INFRA-2520) writes GREEN on a healthy main (verified via a REAL tick, not DRY_RUN). Until then watchdog stays disabled (safe; claims fail-open on stale GREEN)."
  depends_on: [INFRA-2422]
  notes: |
    [2026-06-04T00:06:14Z] confirmed merged on origin/main (fix/feat commit); registry hygiene
  closed_pr: 2980
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

