- id: INFRA-2515
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P1: activate A2A consensus layer — CHUMP_FLEET_RECV_SIDE_V0 is unset fleet-wide so vote/tally works but every proposal returns NO_QUORUM (only proposer votes)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - CHUMP_FLEET_RECV_SIDE_V0=1 set fleet-wide (launchctl setenv + a checked-in setenv LaunchAgent + bootstrap), mirroring the CHUMP_NATS_URL wiring
    - curator loops cast FEEDBACK kind=preference/vote on open proposals (verify a test proposal collects >=quorum votes from >1 distinct curator)
    - deliberator emits a non-NO_QUORUM consensus_result for that test proposal
    - "evidence captured 2026-06-03: broadcast+vote+tally all functioned end-to-end over the mesh but verdict=NO_QUORUM because the flag is off so only the proposer (Opus) could vote"
  depends_on: [RESILIENT-061, RESILIENT-062]
  notes: |
    [2026-06-06T00:11:13Z] Shipped 2026-06-05 (operator mandate: always-run + always-in-use + force/mandate + farmer-keeps-optimal): durable flags (bootstrap setenv + deliberator plist uncomment + live launchctl setenv); fleet-doctor check_a2a_consensus FAILS on dormancy (run by self-doctor); deliberator re-surfaces starved NO_QUORUM proposals to inboxes (rate-limited nudge) + exit-fix; CLAUDE.md+AGENTS.md doctrine (curators MUST vote each cycle); test-a2a-always-on.sh 7/7. Verified live. Follow-ups: wire test into CI+preflight; demand-side EFFECTIVE-039 Contract-Net.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

