- id: INFRA-2523
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: one canonical ship path — collapse bot-merge.sh (4000 LOC) + batched integrator-queue + manual-PR into a single path; delete the other two"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - bot-merge Mode A (batched integrator) is selected ONLY when the integrator is verified healthy — chump-integrator binary present at the daemon plist's ProgramArguments path AND the com.chump.integrator-daemon launchctl last-exit==0; otherwise bot-merge fails-open to Mode B (per-PR auto-merge) and emits kind=bot_merge_mode_failopen with a reason
    - no gap is ever silently routed to a dead/missing integrator queue — kills the INFRA-2455 limbo + INFRA-1120/2188 ghost class
    - the integrator-health check is bounded (<=2s, no hang) and computed once per run
    - a normal 'bot-merge --gap X --auto-merge' opens+arms a PR whenever Mode A is unavailable, so a routine ship no longer needs CHUMP_BYPASS_BOT_MERGE
    - scripts/ci/test-bot-merge-mode-failopen.sh asserts integrator-unhealthy->Mode B + integrator-healthy->Mode A + bounded check, via a mockable health probe
    - bot_merge_mode_failopen registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml with scanner-anchor
    - "follow-ups noted: reconcile stale ready_to_ship ghosts (INFRA-2460), docs (CLAUDE.md + INTEGRATION_CYCLE), eventual full single-path consolidation"
  notes: |
    [2026-06-04T00:06:14Z] confirmed merged on origin/main (fix/feat commit); registry hygiene
  closed_pr: 2991
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2524
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: fail-OPEN every fleet-blocking daemon — watchdog/integrator/main-health must warn+degrade, never halt all claims (today they fail CLOSED, violating A2A_ROADMAP principle 7)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump claim main-health check fails OPEN: a stale/garbled/missing health signal degrades to a warning, never blocks claims fleet-wide (2026-06-03: one watchdog em-dash parse halted ALL claims 5h+)"
    - the integrator daemon missing/dead does not silently swallow ship requests (INFRA-2459)
    - each fleet-blocking daemon has a liveness+sanity self-check that disables itself (fail-open) rather than emitting fleet-halting false signals
    - conforms to A2A_ROADMAP.md principle 7 fail-open-over-deadlock
  notes: |
    [2026-06-03T23:58:34Z] confirmed on origin/main (merged fix commit); mission-loop registry hygiene
  closed_pr: 2987
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2525
  domain: INFRA
  title: "ZERO-WASTE P1: cull bypass env vars — 113 distinct CHUMP_*_(BYPASS|SKIP|IGNORE) escape hatches down to <=3; rule: a gate that needs a routine bypass is fixed or deleted"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - 131 distinct CHUMP_*_(BYPASS
    - SKIP
    - "IGNORE) vars enumerated 2026-06-03 (bigger than the 113 estimate). TRIAGE each into 4 buckets, then cull: GENUINE = real T1-T4 or canonical-path-broken (e.g. CHUMP_BYPASS_BOT_MERGE until INFRA-2523 lands) — keep, target <=3 survivors"
    - CARGO-CULT = gate already fails-open so the bypass is never needed (e.g. CHUMP_OFF_RAILS_CHECK per INFRA-2533) — fix docs + delete the usage
    - SOFTENED = gate is now warn-only (CHUMP_OBS_BUDGET_BYPASS/INFRA-2425, CHUMP_RUST_FIRST after INFRA-2522) — delete the now-inert bypass
    - DEAD = referenced only at its def-site or for a removed gate — delete
    - "RULE: never delete a bypass while its gate still hard-blocks (breaks legit work); soften/remove the gate first, confirm the var is unused via grep, then delete from code + bypass-env-var-allowlist.txt"
    - this is a dedicated effort, NOT a marathon-tail rush — decompose per-bucket at claim time
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

