- id: INFRA-2533
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: off-rails path-scope fails-OPEN when claim.paths is undeclared — stop blocking every commit that didn't pass --paths (the #2 friction this session); enforce only when paths explicitly declared"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - the pre-commit off-rails (RESILIENT-026) path-scope check WARNS (does not block) when the claim lease has an empty/unset paths array — path-scoping is opt-in, enforced only when paths were explicitly declared via chump claim --paths
    - a normal 'chump claim <id>' (no --paths) no longer requires CHUMP_OFF_RAILS_CHECK=0 to commit in-scope work
    - when paths ARE declared, an out-of-scope staged file still blocks (protection preserved)
    - the commit-subject gap-id check (RESILIENT-025) is unchanged
    - tested
  closed_date: '2026-06-05'
  closed_pr: 2990
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2534
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P0: test-cross-pr-contract.sh calls chump contract-scan THREE times — collapse to single call (3× O(N×M) → 1× O(N×M), audit-step time reduced from 20+ min)"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "test-cross-pr-contract.sh lines 162-180 currently call chump contract-scan --in-flight 3 times: once for progress stderr-to-terminal, once captured (but discarded), once captured for real (used)"
    - "Each call walks 948 writers (32 python + 150 Rust + 766 ambient) — triples the audit-step wall-clock to ~20+ min, causing operator-cancellations and 4 substrate PRs (#2981/#2982/#2983/#2985) wedged in BLOCKED state"
    - "Fix: collapse to single call. Run contract-scan once, capture both stdout and stderr to tempfile, print progress live via tee"
    - Document allowlist usage in scripts/ci/cross-pr-allowlist.txt header — entries are matched per writer/reader pair AFTER scan completes, allowlist does NOT speed scanning
    - "Regression test scripts/ci/test-cross-pr-contract-triple-call-guard.sh: count chump contract-scan invocations in the script; assert exactly 1"
  closed_date: '2026-06-05'
  closed_pr: 2989
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

