- id: INFRA-2672
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P1: pin rustfmt version for preflight↔CI parity — drift caused #3003 fast-checks fail today"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Today 2026-06-03 PR #3003 RESILIENT-059 passed local cargo fmt --check rc=0 against rustc 1.96.0 stable-aarch64-apple-darwin (rustup toolchain), but CI cargo fmt --check failed with 3-line diff (the .prepare( wrapping in src/commands/durable_execution_journal.rs)."
    - "Root: no pinned rustfmt version means local vs CI can drift on minor rustfmt patches. Each drift = one CI iteration burn."
    - "Fix: add rust-toolchain.toml at repo root pinning a specific stable channel (e.g. 1.96.0). preflight reads rust-toolchain.toml or uses the same channel via rustup show. Audit.yml + ci.yml read the same."
    - "Verify: scripts/ci/test-rustfmt-parity.sh asserts (a) rust-toolchain.toml exists, (b) preflight reads the pinned channel, (c) a sample cargo fmt run locally matches the toolchain selection workflows would use."
    - "Operator escape hatch: rustup override allows manual toolchain choice for diagnosis, but is not the default."
  notes: |
    [2026-06-03T23:58:32Z] confirmed on origin/main (merged fix commit); mission-loop registry hygiene
  closed_pr: 3012
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2673
  domain: INFRA
  title: "EFFECTIVE P1: bot-merge.sh --progress-file flag — stream phase markers so background callers can tail"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "[\n\"Today 2026-06-03 orchestrator-opus invoked bot-merge.sh in background (run_in_background=true), output stayed at 0 bytes for 11+ min while internal cargo build + gh polling proceeded silently. Operator could not tell whether the script was hung or just slow.\",\n\"Fix: add --progress-file PATH option to scripts/coord/bot-merge.sh. When set, each phase boundary (init, fetch, push, gh-merge-arm, wait, post-merge) writes a single timestamped line to the file. Caller can tail -f the file to see incremental progress.\",\n\"Phases to mark: phase=init, phase=fetch_main, phase=preflight, phase=push, phase=arm_auto_merge, phase=wait_for_ci, phase=post_merge_clean, phase=done, phase=aborted_*.\",\n\"Verify: scripts/ci/test-bot-merge-progress-file.sh — invoke bot-merge.sh --dry-run --progress-file /tmp/test.log, assert lines appear in order with monotonic timestamps and the expected phase= prefix.\",\n\"Backwards-compat: when --progress-file is absent, behavior unchanged (no file writes).\"\n]"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-2674
  domain: INFRA
  title: "RESILIENT P0: _chump_gh_maybe_emit_exhausted empty-string→0 coercion — INFRA-2484 missed this, cascade still firing 31 false alarms / 30 min"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "[\n\"Today 2026-06-03 16-18Z: live GraphQL is 4266/5000 healthy, but ambient still emits 31 graphql_exhausted events / 30 min. Each event has threshold_seen:0 resets_at:unknown source:gh. Each event causes bot-merge.sh to exit 144 (wedge guard) — blocked my DOC-065 ship + 2 others.\",\n\"Root cause: scripts/coord/lib/github.sh:124 local gql_rem=${1:-0} — when _chump_gh_rate_remaining returns a malformed/empty string, the read in chump_gh_record leaves gql_rem as empty string. Calling _chump_gh_maybe_emit_exhausted with empty $1 coerces to 0 via the default. Then 0 =~ ^[0-9]+$ matches, 0 -le 100 fires.\",\n\"INFRA-2484 added the -ge 0 check thinking it would catch negatives but missed that empty-string default → 0 → fires.\",\n\"Fix: replace local gql_rem=${1:-0} with [[ -n ${1:-} && ${1} =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] "
    - ""
    - " return 0; local gql_rem=$1; — reject empty AND require explicit digits BEFORE allowing any threshold comparison.\",\n\"Also: _chump_gh_rate_remaining should validate output shape — if it does not match INT INT INT, return the sentinel -1 -1 0. Today it accepts gh api rate_limit failure output verbatim (e.g. { from a JSON error message) leading to the malformed downstream parse.\",\n\"Regression test scripts/ci/test-graphql-exhausted-empty-coercion-guard.sh: call _chump_gh_maybe_emit_exhausted with empty $1, assert no graphql_exhausted line written to test ambient file.\"\n]"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

