  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    `cargo install --path . --bin chump --force` fails with:
      error[E0599]: no method named `signing_key` found for reference `&Box<ml_dsa::SigningKey<MlDsa44>>`
    The `superboring` crate calls `.signing_key()` on `ml_dsa::SigningKey` which no longer
    exists in the current ml_dsa API. This blocks `chump` binary rebuild from HEAD.
    Fix: pin superboring or ml_dsa to a compatible version in Cargo.toml, or patch the
    superboring call site to use the new API.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - cargo install --path . --bin chump --force completes successfully
    - chump --version reports a binary built from a post-fix commit
    - cargo clippy passes on main
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-816
  domain: INFRA
  title: "release-plz: missing glib-2.0 system dependency causes CI failure"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    release-plz.yml CI workflow consistently fails because it runs `cargo test` 
    without installing system dependencies needed by glib-sys crate (glib-2.0). 
    The main CI (ci.yml) has `sudo apt-get install libglib2.0-dev` in its setup 
    steps, but release-plz.yml lacks this. Error:
    
      pkg-config failed: Package glib-2.0 was not found in the pkg-config search path.
      The system library glib-2.0 required by crate glib-sys was not found.
    
    The release-plz workflow handles crate publishing (crates.io). With this 
    failure, the release pipeline is broken for any PR that touches a crate 
    with glib-sys as a transitive dependency.
    
    Fix: add `sudo apt-get install -y libglib2.0-dev` to the release-plz.yml 
    setup steps, matching the pattern used in ci.yml.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - ""
    - " release-plz.yml CI run passes on a PR with crate changes that transitively depend on glib-sys "
    - " yes "
    - "\n"
    - " apt-get install libglib2.0-dev step added to release-plz.yml setup "
    - " yes "
    - ""
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: INFRA-817
  domain: INFRA
  title: e2e-pwa flake persists — PWA-shell-loads-home test fails intermittently, zero green CI runs on main in last 100
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    The e2e-pwa Playwright test "PWA-shell-loads-home-and-shows-message-composer" 
    fails intermittently in CI with `element(s) not found` for the message composer 
    input. It is retried 3 times and all attempts fail. This single flaky test is 
    the primary cause of zero successful main-branch CI runs in the last 100 
    executions (all either cancelled by merge queue or failed on this flake).
    
    Previous attempts:
    - PRODUCT-070 (PR #1379, closed): enabled CHUMP_LIGHT_CONTEXT for web_slim — did not fix
    - PRODUCT-074 (PR #1381, closed): investigation of DOM element timeouts — closed as done but flake persists  
    - INFRA-764 (PR #1366, closed): added flake auto-rerun harness — safety net only
    - PRODUCT-076 (open, P2/m): update tests to use v2-native selectors — may help but low priority
    
    The core issue is likely a race condition in the PWA v2 web UI rendering 
    pipeline — the message composer DOM element isn't consistently available 
    by the time Playwright checks for it. This could be a missing loading 
    indicator, a hydration timing issue, or a CSS selector mismatch after v2 
    migration.
    
    Fix options:
    1. Add Playwright waitForSelector with longer timeout / retry logic
    2. Fix the root rendering race in web_server.rs or PWA v2 frontend
    3. Remove or skip the flaky test until v2 migration is complete
  acceptance_criteria:
    - ""
    - " e2e-pwa CI runs pass consistently (10 consecutive green runs on main) "
    - " yes "
    - "\n"
    - " Root cause of the PWA-shell-loads-home flake identified and documented "
    - " yes "
    - "\n"
    - " Either: rendering race fixed, or test hardened, or test skipped with tracking gap "
    - " yes "
    - ""
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

