  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    As of 2026-05-11, at least 3 gaps have code merged to main but YAML still shows status:open:
    - INFRA-816: fixed in PR #1437 (fix(infra-816): add system deps to release-plz.yml) — gap still open
    - CREDIBLE-013: shipped in PR #1431 (CREDIBLE-013: CI failure triage) — gap still open
    - INFRA-817: fixed in PR #1442 (fix(e2e): update PWA v2 test selectors) — gap still open
    
    In addition, INFRA-796/797/798 have pr: 1421 set but status: open, indicating partial ship.
    
    The CLAUDE.md ship pipeline says to run `chump gap ship <ID> --update-yaml` after merge.
    Bot-merge.sh does not call this automatically. When the agent that shipped moves on to the
    next gap, the prior gap stays open forever unless someone manually closes it.
    
    This is pure waste: false signal in the open queue, incorrect pillar counts, and audit tools
    reporting on "open with closed_pr" pattern will eventually mis-report metrics.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - bot-merge.sh calls chump gap ship <GAP-ID> --update-yaml after successful gh pr merge
    - Gap ID extracted from branch name (pattern chump/<GAP-ID>-*) or PR title prefix
    - "chump gap audit-priorities \"open with closed_pr\" count = 0"
    - INFRA-816, CREDIBLE-013, INFRA-817 closed (or manually confirmed still incomplete)
    - scripts/ci/test-bot-merge-auto-close.sh verifies the new behavior on a fixture gap
