- id: META-115
  domain: META
  title: "RESILIENT: per-session source-freshness preamble Phase 1 — classify local state FRESH/STALE/CRITICAL_STALE + gate MUTATE ops (META-114 freshness cluster sub-gap)"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Sub-gap of META-114 freshness discipline cluster. Phase 1 of three.
    
    Failure mode this closes: every "stale-tree false-positive" gap (e.g.
    shepherd's 2026-05-27 recovery-queue-emit.sh phantom-missing) starts
    with a MUTATE operation against a stale local view. Operator's local
    main is 48-63 commits behind origin/main; a file that exists on
    origin/main appears missing locally; operator/curator files a "file
    missing" gap or runs a destructive op against a phantom state.
    
    Phase 1 SHIPS THE SCRIPTS but is intentionally NON-INVASIVE: no hook
    wiring, no chump fleet-bootstrap --check integration, no EVENT_REGISTRY
    addition (uses event-registry-reserved.txt allowlist). Integration is
    a separate sub-gap so Phase 1 is reviewable + ship-able as additive.
    
    Real-world precedent (2026-05-27 shepherd session):
      - recovery-queue-emit.sh phantom-missing (worst) — shepherd filed
        an almost-gap for a file that existed on origin/main
      - fleet-hold-check.sh false-missing earlier same session
      - chump --temp returning multi-line instead of enum
    
    All three would have been caught by running freshness-preamble.sh at
    session-start; CRITICAL_STALE classification would have prompted a
    rebase + binary reinstall before the operator went chasing ghosts.
    
    Related: META-114 (parent umbrella), INFRA-2053 (chump gap sync —
    bidirectional state.db <-> YAML drift; today's session shipped that
    as the OTHER half of the freshness layer), META-110/INFRA-2046
    (chump cron health subcommand; this script fail-softs if not present),
    META-066 (chump-fleet-bootstrap --check; this script fail-softs).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - NEW scripts/coord/freshness-preamble.sh classifies session-start state into FRESH/STALE/CRITICAL_STALE based on (a) git commits-behind via fetch+rev-list, (b) binary-age via stat-mtime $(which chump), (c) chump cron health (fail-soft to unavailable), (d) chump fleet-bootstrap --check exit code (fail-soft); emits single-line stdout summary + exits 0/1/2 reflecting state; --json variant for programmatic use
    - "Env-tunable thresholds: CHUMP_FRESHNESS_COMMITS_THRESHOLD (default 50 = CRITICAL_STALE above), CHUMP_FRESHNESS_BINARY_AGE_S (default 14400 = 4h CRITICAL_STALE above), CHUMP_FRESHNESS_STALE_COMMITS (default 15 = STALE above), CHUMP_FRESHNESS_STALE_BINARY_AGE_S (default 3600 = 1h STALE above), CHUMP_FRESHNESS_DISABLE_FETCH (skip fetch for offline tests)"
    - "NEW scripts/coord/freshness-gate.sh is a thin wrapper: calls freshness-preamble.sh, refuses chained op on CRITICAL_STALE (exit 2) unless CHUMP_ACCEPT_STALE=1; on bypass emits kind=freshness_critical_stale_bypassed to ambient with commits_behind, binary_age_s fields"
