- id: META-152
  domain: META
  title: chump fleet lane-recommend — current-state-aware curator-lane bottleneck picker (replaces ad-hoc AskUserQuestion at onboard time)
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Demonstrated 2026-05-30: ci-audit-onboarding session sent AskUserQuestion "which lane should I onboard into?" — operator answered "no preference" — which means the FLEET should have decided. The data exists: 4 curator sessions DARK (target/external-collab/infra-watcher/observability never emitted from the 2026-05-28 cohort), 5 alive (ci-audit/handoff/decompose/shepherd/md-links). All 4 dark lanes were coverage gaps; ci-audit was alive-but-idle (silent_agent SLO root cause). A data-driven picker would have ranked ci-audit (alive-but-not-acting > dark on impact) or target (highest user-facing pillar gap) without operator input. Pairs with META-132 fresh-eyes (which audits AFTER lane-pick) — this acts BEFORE.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump fleet lane-recommend CLI exists; outputs ranked lanes with one-line why; supports --json and human table
    - "Scoring inputs (combined): (a) lane darkness (0 heartbeats in last 4h = highest), (b) alive-but-idle ratio (heartbeats > 0 AND sub_agent_dispatched/DONE = 0 over 4 ticks), (c) pickable queue depth per lane skill_required tag, (d) shipped-PR rate last 24h per lane (low = starved), (e) roadmap-bottleneck-pillar alignment from docs/ROADMAP.md, (f) age of oldest stuck item in lane"
    - "Lane coverage: target / ci-audit / handoff / shepherd / decompose / observability / external-collab / md-links / infra-watcher / fresh-eyes (when META-132 lands). Add new lanes via docs/agents/<role>.md presence"
    - "Cold-start fallback: when no ambient data (< 10 events in 24h), rank by roadmap-bottleneck-pillar alignment only"
    - "Auto-surface: SessionStart hook calls lane-recommend and folds top recommendation into the session digest (one line, behind a hint); /onboard slash command runs it"
    - Emit kind=lane_recommended {top_lane, score, runner_up, reason} to ambient on each invocation; register in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    - "Score explainability: --explain flag shows per-lane breakdown of the 6 inputs"
    - scripts/ci/test-fleet-lane-recommend.sh exercises a synthetic state (dark target, idle ci-audit, busy shepherd) and asserts target ranks highest
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-153
  domain: META
  title: chump preflight --vs origin/main — diff-scoped failure attribution (pre-existing vs new), filter pre-existing fails from local CI
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Demonstrated 2026-05-30: chump preflight FAILed on (a) pr-hygiene (scripts/ci/check-pr-hygiene.sh referenced by preflight.rs:950 not in this worktree) and (b) event-registry-coverage (10 pre-existing emit-without-register violations including bad/good/skip/consensus_resolved/operator_escalation/preference/test_event/sccache_r2_token_*). My diff added zero new emit kinds. I spent 4min diagnosing both before bypassing with Preflight-Skip-Reason. This is the single biggest local-vs-CI friction class: preflight FAILs treat pre-existing baseline failures as if they were caused by my change. Need: "what failed that wasnt already failing on origin/main HEAD" mode.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump preflight --vs origin/main flag exists; runs preflight against current HEAD AND against origin/main; emits only gates that pass on origin/main and fail on HEAD as actionable failures
    - origin/main preflight result cached at .chump/preflight-baseline.json with TTL=1h; cache key = main HEAD SHA; invalidate on SHA change
    - "Output sections: \"NEW (your diff)\" — hard fail; \"PRE-EXISTING (not yours)\" — listed with originating-commit SHA + author + age, do NOT block"
    - When --vs origin/main is set and baseline is unavailable (offline, SHA fetch fails), gracefully fall back to current behavior with a warning banner — never block the user
    - Default scope behavior unchanged when --vs origin/main NOT passed; this is opt-in until proven, then promote to default in follow-up
    - "chump preflight --vs origin/main --json emits structured {new_failures: [...], preexisting_failures: [...], baseline_sha: ..., baseline_age_seconds: ...} for tooling"
    - Emit kind=preflight_baseline_diff {new_fail_count, preexisting_fail_count, baseline_sha} to ambient on each run; register in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    - "scripts/ci/test-preflight-vs-origin-main.sh fixture: synthetic 3-gate preflight (1 pre-existing fail, 1 new fail, 1 pass) — assert only the new fail is in NEW section"
    - "Pre-commit hook integration: when --vs origin/main NEW section is non-empty, hook blocks; when only PRE-EXISTING, hook warns and proceeds"
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2828
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-154
  domain: META
  title: chump sibling-status — per-active-lease progress matrix (progressing/in-flight/heartbeat-only/stalled/silent), beats 'lease exists'
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Demonstrated 2026-05-30: SessionStart digest showed me 3 active sibling leases (INFRA-2238, INFRA-2239, INFRA-2240) with their session_ids + expiry. That told me nothing about whether each was making progress, idle, or stalled. I had to manually grep ambient by session_id to find out (and found INFRA-2240 was actively editing files while INFRA-2238 had only emitted heartbeats). Beats "lease exists" by adding the actually-doing-what dimension. Pairs with META-152 (lane-recommend uses this signal) and META-132 (fresh-eyes uses this signal as comparator #3 input).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump sibling-status CLI exists; one row per active claim-*.json in .chump-locks/; output human table + --json
    - "Per-lease columns: gap_id, session_id, age, last_commit_ts (vs git), last_file_edit_ts (vs ambient kind=file_edit), last_broadcast_ts (vs ambient broadcast events), last_heartbeat_ts, status_classification"
    - "Status classifications: progressing (commit in last 30min), in-flight (file_edit but no commit in last 30min), heartbeat-only (heartbeat in last 30min but no edit/commit/broadcast — silent_agent candidate), stalled (lease age > 2h AND no activity in last 30min), silent (no heartbeat in last hour), expired (lease past expires_at)"
    - "Auto-surface: SessionStart digest folds sibling-status one-line summary (\"3 leases: 1 progressing, 1 in-flight, 1 heartbeat-only\") replacing the existing \"Active sibling leases\" raw list"
    - "--watch mode: refreshes every 30s, terminal screen redraw, exits on Ctrl-C"
    - Emit kind=sibling_status_polled {progressing, in_flight, heartbeat_only, stalled, silent, expired} to ambient on each non-watch invocation; register in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml
    - "scripts/ci/test-sibling-status.sh fixture: 5 synthetic claim files + 5 synthetic ambient event patterns — assert each lease classified correctly"
    - Reads from .chump-locks/ambient.jsonl directly (not gh) — must work offline and respond <500ms even with 10k ambient lines
  notes: META-154 work in flight; PR opening shortly
  closed_pr: 2823
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-155
  domain: META
  title: "META: fleet wire reader-side — peer curators subscribe to chump.events.> + react (NOT just emit)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Operator observation 2026-05-30T04:35Z: surveyed 24h of NATS chump.events.> traffic + ambient.jsonl mirror. Result: peer curators emit heartbeats and per-tick state, but ZERO addressed curator-to-curator messages, ZERO FEEDBACK responses to broadcasted proposals (META-129, INFRA-2206, INFRA-2208, INFRA-2239). The 6 productized curator-loop scripts (shepherd / target / handoff / ci-audit / decompose / md-links) do their narrow domain work + emit heartbeat — they have NO code path that subscribes to peers' broadcasts and reacts. The fleet wire is broadcast-only in practice; the new comms policy (INFRA-2202 #2745) describes the channel but no consumer side exists. Naming locked 2026-05-30: this layer is 'fleet wire' (operator pick). HOLD this gap until design lands — three sub-questions to settle on NATS FEEDBACK before claim: (a) which subjects each role subscribes to (narrow domain filters vs everything), (b) what counts as 'react' (file gap / dispatch sub-agent / dedupe-then-emit / no-op), (c) dedupe + cooldown rules so curators don't reaction-loop on each other's emissions.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Design doc docs/design/FLEET_WIRE_READER.md covers the three sub-questions with concrete defaults per role (which subjects shepherd / target / handoff / ci-audit / decompose / md-links subscribes to)
    - "For each productized curator role: a reaction table — incoming kind → reaction class (file gap / dispatch sub-agent / dedupe-emit / no-op) with rationale"
    - "Dedupe + cooldown spec: fingerprint scheme to avoid reaction loops; sentinel TTL per reaction class (e.g. 'don't dispatch another Sonnet on the same kind+subject within 1h')"
    - "Mechanism: each loop script gets a chump-coord subscribe wrapper OR a shared scripts/coord/wire-subscriber.sh that the loops invoke per tick to drain new events since last cursor"
    - At least 5 NATS FEEDBACK responses from peer curators (or operator decisions) recorded in the design doc before AC are locked
    - Cross-references INFRA-2202 (comms policy), INFRA-2239 (curator-supervisor — both consume + emit on the wire), META-129 (scrubber panel info architecture)
    - "Marcus loop: external-collab curator validates that the reader side surfaces something Marcus would care about (not just internal fleet meta)"
  depends_on: [INFRA-2202, INFRA-2239]
  notes: |
    2026-05-30T05:25Z sharper diagnosis: NATS+broadcast.sh both work (dual-publish to ambient.jsonl + NATS JetStream). Real bug: bash curator-loop daemons never read ambient OR subscribe to NATS. Claude Code sessions read via SessionStart ambient-context-inject; bash daemons have no equivalent. Quick win filed as INFRA-2262 (per-tick ambient inject); AGENTS.md doc update filed as INFRA-2263. META-155 remains the umbrella reaction-table design — even with the deafness fix, we still need to settle which subjects each role subscribes to / what counts as 'react' / dedupe rules.
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-156
  domain: META
  title: bot-merge.sh init step hangs silently with no operator-visible signal — relies on 600s SIGTERM budget; logs land in worktree-local file curator can't easily find
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Demonstrated 2026-05-30T04:16-04:26Z: bot-merge.sh launched as background bash for CREDIBLE-079; foreground bash exited immediately with 0-byte output. The real log went to /private/tmp/chump-credible-079/.chump-locks/bot-merge-1462.log (worktree-local, no operator hint). Bot-merge ran preflight OK then tried chump claim which failed with "worktree path already exists" (re-claim from the outer claim wasn-t expected); it then hung 10min at "init" step until budget SIGTERM killed it at 04:26Z. Caller (this Opus session) had no idea bot-merge was dead until 25min later when I checked. The lease vanished, no PR opened, no branch pushed. Operator had to manually recover with CHUMP_OPERATOR_RECOVERY=1 git push, gh pr create, gh pr merge --auto. Real failure rate per session: high (saw it once today; SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md already calls out the 15min budget as a stall pattern). Pairs with META-154 sibling-status (would have showed bot-merge session as silent within 5min) and META-152 lane-recommend (would not have re-recommended this lane while bot-merge silently dead).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - bot-merge.sh emits kind=bot_merge_step_started + kind=bot_merge_step_done to ambient.jsonl for each named step (init, preflight, claim, push, pr_create, pr_merge_arm, pr_wait_merge, post_ship). Step-done includes duration_ms and rc
    - bot-merge.sh re-claim failure (worktree exists) auto-retries with --force-recover when the outer caller is the same session_id (read from CHUMP_SESSION_ID env if set); otherwise fails fast with operator-visible reason
    - GraphQL 401 / graphql_exhausted is hard-fail-fast in bot-merge init step (don-t retry-loop until budget kills you) — emit kind=bot_merge_aborted_no_auth and exit 1 within 30s
    - "bot-merge.sh log path advertised to operator: when launched as background, append .log path to a session-visible file (.chump-locks/bot-merge-active-<session_id>.path) so operator/curator can tail -F immediately"
    - Foreground bot-merge.sh prints log path to stdout in first second of execution (not deferred to log file) so IDE callers see where output is going
    - Budget enforcement (currently 600s default, CHUMP_SUBAGENT_BOT_MERGE_BUDGET_S=900 per SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md) emits intermediate alerts at 50% / 75% / 90% as kind=bot_merge_budget_warn — currently the FIRST signal operator sees is the 100% SIGTERM
    - Step-done emits roll up into ambient kind=bot_merge_completed {gap_id, pr_number, duration_ms, terminal_state} on graceful exit; this is what META-154 sibling-status and downstream consumers should match against
    - "scripts/ci/test-bot-merge-step-emits.sh smoke: stub out gh + git, run bot-merge --gap FIXTURE-001 against a tmp worktree, assert all 8 step-started/step-done events emitted in order"
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2826
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-157
  domain: META
  title: "[UMBRELLA] Fleet recv-side v0 — close the broadcast loop using shipped foundations (INFRA-1759/1760/1761), fanout-to-inbox + vote + consensus-tally + per-loop drain + deliberator"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: l
  description: |
    Demonstrated 2026-05-30 onboarding: I broadcast 3 FEEDBACK proposals (META-132, META-152/153/154, cadence-vote) and got ZERO replies. Root cause was a 3-step compound failure (1) broadcast.sh emit_to_inbox() requires --to flag; without it returns 0 silently with no inbox write — every fan-out FEEDBACK proposal lands in ambient+NATS but NEVER reaches any per-session inbox file. All ~100 inbox files in .chump-locks/inbox/ are 0 bytes despite hundreds of broadcasts. (2) 5 of 7 curator loop scripts (decompose, external-collab, infra-watcher, md-links, observability) have ZERO inbox/feedback handling code — they would not have seen the broadcasts even if delivered. (3) no vote primitive (chump vote does not exist) and no consensus mechanism (no deliberator role, no consensus-tally) — even if a curator wanted to reply, the reply mechanism does not exist. NATS broker IS deployed (nats://127.0.0.1:4222 OK), broadcast.sh DOES dual-publish to NATS chump.events.> for FEEDBACK, INFRA-1759 RPC + INFRA-1760 CapabilityManifest + INFRA-1761 NATS KV chump_scratch foundations ARE shipped. The recv-side primitives just dont USE them. v0 ships 6 slices in parallel via META-069 Sonnet fleet dispatch, ending with end-to-end test: broadcast → 5 curator inbox drains → 3 votes → 1 consensus_result event.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - docs/strategy/FLEET_RECV_SIDE_2026-05-30.md design doc lands first; cites INFRA-1759/1760/1761 by name; lists 6 slices with explicit no-conflict file paths; operator sign-off recorded in PR body
    - "Slice 1 (broadcast.sh fan-out-to-inbox): when --to is unset AND event=FEEDBACK AND kind in (proposal,preference,defect,retro), emit_to_inbox expands to all live curator session_ids by globbing .chump-locks/.curator-opus-*.lock; new --no-fanout flag opts out for backwards compat; smoke test in scripts/ci/test-broadcast-feedback-fanout.sh"
    - "Slice 2 (chump vote + consensus-tally CLI): chump vote <corr_id> <+1|-1|0> --reason <text> emits FEEDBACK kind=vote to ambient + NATS; chump consensus-tally [--corr-id X|--all] aggregates votes per corr_id from last 24h, prints rolling result + verdict; new test scripts/ci/test-chump-vote.sh + test-chump-consensus-tally.sh"
    - "Slice 3 (decompose loop drain): scripts/coord/decompose-loop.sh gains Phase 0 _drain_inbox + _peek_pending_feedback functions matching the ci-audit pattern; tick subcommand exits 0 when actionable proposals found; test-decompose-loop.sh extended"
    - "Slice 4 (external-collab + infra-watcher + md-links + observability loops drain): same Phase 0 pattern applied to the other 4 loops missing recv code; one slice per loop or bundled; each loop tick exits 0 on actionable proposals"
    - "Slice 5 (curator-opus-deliberator role): .claude/agents/deliberator.md role doc + scripts/coord/deliberator-loop.sh CLI; runs every 30min via launchd plist; reads FEEDBACK kind=proposal events from ambient, computes vote tally, emits kind=consensus_result {corr_id, verdict in (passed/failed/no_quorum/extended), vote_counts, voters} after deadline; escalates to operator via OPERATOR_RECALL when no_quorum AND deadline+24h passed"
    - "Slice 6 (capability registration): each curator loop on startup publishes manifest to NATS KV chump_scratch bucket key=fleet.<role>.capabilities (matches INFRA-1760/1761 contract); deliberator queries this to compute quorum count (active voters); test-capability-registration.sh covers"
    - "End-to-end ship test: scripts/ci/test-fleet-recv-side-e2e.sh starts a tmp NATS, dispatches 1 broadcaster sending FEEDBACK kind=proposal, dispatches 5 mock curator loops each running drain+vote, runs deliberator tick, asserts kind=consensus_result emitted with correct verdict"
    - Slices ship in parallel via META-069 Sonnet sub-agent dispatch; Opus PM (this session) babysits + surgical-rescues; final integration PR bundles all 6 slices behind a single CHUMP_FLEET_RECV_SIDE_V0 feature flag (default OFF until E2E proves green, then ON in a follow-up flip-PR)
    - "Operator sign-off broadcast: after design doc lands, broadcast FEEDBACK kind=proposal with this UMBRELLA as subject + 6-slice list + flag-default-OFF rollout plan; this is the FIRST broadcast that tests fan-out-to-inbox post-Slice-1 (meta-recursive proof)"
  closed_date: '2026-06-05'
  closed_pr: 2805
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: META-158
  domain: META
  title: "META-157-a: broadcast.sh fan-out-to-inbox — when --to unset AND event=FEEDBACK AND kind in (proposal/preference/defect/retro), expand recipient via .curator-opus-*.lock glob"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Sub-slice A of META-157. Fixes emit_to_inbox silent no-op for fan-out FEEDBACK. See docs/strategy/FLEET_RECV_SIDE_2026-05-30.md §3 Slice 1. Read META-157 description for compound-failure context.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "scripts/coord/broadcast.sh emit_to_inbox: when recipient unset AND event=FEEDBACK AND kind in (proposal,preference,defect,retro), expand recipient list by globbing .chump-locks/.curator-opus-*.lock and stripping the leading dot + .lock suffix to get session_ids"
    - "New --no-fanout flag opts out: when set, fan-out is suppressed and emit_to_inbox falls back to current single-recipient behavior"
