    - " HumanEscalate)\n- MissionExecutor, ObjectiveResult\n- ExecutionRecord, ExecutionLog\n- FallbackMode { SafeShutdown, ReturnToBase, QueryAuthority, ContinueLastTask, SkipAndContinue }\n\n**Adaptations for agent fleet (vs original physical-fleet context):**\n- resource_cost = token_budget (per-gap cost cap; INFRA-2090 alignment)\n- target = HITL approval gate (already wired via INFRA-1813)\n- location/geo affinity = path-domain scope (file-prefix lease affinity)\n- mesh distribution = chump-coord broadcast + lease primitives (already operational)\n- ExecutionRecord = ambient stream + PR commit log (already in place)\n\n**Sub-tracks (decompose at claim):**\n\n(a) **INFRA-2247 (keystone prerequisite): lift Mission types into crates/chump-coord/src/mission/** — public-interface only, derived from internal prior-art shapes; agent-fleet-adapted (resource_cost vs energy_cost, path scope vs geo)\n(b) Curator capability registry — each role declares supported ObjectiveKind (in INFRA-1120 capability.rs)\n(c) MissionExecutor daemon — dispatches via chump-coord broadcasts + lease primitives\n(d) Mission-aware picker — curators prefer assigned Objective over generic next-best (depends_on as hard ordering)\n(e) chump mission CLI (new / status / complete / abort)\n(f) Replanner: AbortOnFailure + RetryWithBackoff + DegradeToSimpler + HumanEscalate\n(g) Ambient events: mission_created, objective_started, objective_completed, mission_replanned, mission_completed (extend EVENT_REGISTRY)\n(h) Rainbow-6 viz: fleet-scrubber gains mission lane (timeline + role assignments)\n(i) Canary: declare Marcus M-B (INFRA-1813/1605/2141/2200) as a post-hoc Mission for validation\n(j) PWA Mission panel — chump-cockpit mission status view\n\n**Operator value:** today's manual multi-sub-agent dispatch + manual lease arbitration + manual admin-merge cycles → one CLI call. Mission lands → done. Replan on collision automatic.\n\nDecompose via chump gap decompose at claim time. INFRA-2247 is the unblocker for everything else."
