- id: META-180
  domain: META
  title: "[UMBRELLA] relentless PR-shepherd daemon — 100% coverage of open PRs every N seconds, classifies + acts (consensus vote / rebase / rerun / escalate); replaces operator manual admin-merge as the fleet's PR-management engine"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: l
  description: |
    OPERATOR PAIN SIGNAL 2026-05-30T16:30Z: 'I need RELENTLESS TENACIOUS PR management for 100% of what's in that queue all the time... We need a systemic PR admin merge consensus voting option for the fleet or something.. you can't keep making me do this manually'
    
    CURRENT STATE OF SUBSTRATE (relevant pieces, all in flight or filed):
      PR #2841 (INFRA-2274) — ConsensusCoordinator into bot-merge as pre-merge gate; shadow-mode default, 7-day before enforce flip; replaces ~105 admin-merge-bypass landings from 2026-05-30. THE GATE. Currently BLOCKED behind trunk-red queue.
      PR #2831 (INFRA-2247) — Mission types vendored from proprietary; 869 LOC; BLOCKED behind same trunk-red.
      PR #2858 (RESILIENT-041, mine) — comprehensive trunk-red rescue; landing this cascade-unblocks #2841 + #2831 + 27 others.
      RESILIENT-050 — stale-pr-reaper destroyed 28 legitimate PRs at 15:46Z during trunk-red; needs a 'no reap when trunk-red' guard.
      scripts/coord/pr-watch.sh, pr-rescue.sh, pr-watch-shepherd.sh, opus-shepherd-triage.sh — passive/single-PR tools, NOT 100%-coverage daemons.
      scripts/coord/queue-driver.sh — pulls open gaps into workers; gap layer not PR layer.
      scripts/dispatch/operator-recall.sh — pages operator on halt-class conditions; reactive not proactive.
    
    WHAT'S MISSING (the 'relentless 100% coverage' delta):
      A daemon — call it 'chump-pr-shepherd-daemon' or 'pr-relentless-loop' — that runs every N seconds (default 60s, env: CHUMP_PR_SHEPHERD_INTERVAL_S) and walks ALL 30+ open PRs. For each, classifies state and dispatches action:
        BEHIND          → auto-rebase via update-branch API
        MERGEABLE       → arm consensus vote (broadcast FEEDBACK kind=vote-request corr_id=pr-N to N curators)
        BLOCKED + all checks green   → admin-merge bypass via CHUMP_OPERATOR_CONSENSUS_BYPASS (audit-trail emitted)
        BLOCKED + flake-class fail   → rerun failing job
        BLOCKED + real fail          → file follow-up gap with failure signature; tag PR for operator review
        DIRTY                        → escalate to operator-attention queue (PWA cockpit)
        UNKNOWN                      → log + skip; do not act
      Per-PR consensus tracker — keyed by pr-N corr_id; persists votes received; emits consensus_resolved when quorum reached; auto-fires admin-merge.
      Self-throttling — caps action rate per GitHub API budget; honors CHUMP_GH_CALL_CRITICALITY.
      Trunk-red awareness — when trunk_red event in ambient, daemon switches to 'no destructive ops' mode (no reaper, no rebase wave, no admin-merge — except via explicit operator bypass).
    
    DEPENDENCIES (must land first OR in same sweep):
      - PR #2841 INFRA-2274 (gate exists in shadow mode) — daemon's consensus path depends on the gate being callable
      - PR #2858 RESILIENT-041 (trunk-red rescue) — prerequisite for #2841 landing
      - RESILIENT-050 reaper guard — prerequisite for daemon's safety during trunk-red
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. Daemon script scripts/coord/pr-shepherd-daemon.sh implemented; runs every CHUMP_PR_SHEPHERD_INTERVAL_S (default 60s); covers 100% of open PRs per tick (no caps)\n2. launchd plist at scripts/setup/install-pr-shepherd-daemon.sh installs StartInterval=60 plist; runs at user-launch session-level scope\n3. Per-tick classification + action dispatch per the description's 6-state table (BEHIND/MERGEABLE/BLOCKED+green/BLOCKED+flake/BLOCKED+real-fail/DIRTY/UNKNOWN)\n4. Per-PR consensus tracker — keyed by pr-N corr_id; integration with chump consensus-tally (post-INFRA-2274); auto-fires admin-merge on quorum\n5. Trunk-red guard — when ambient kind=trunk_red event in last 30m, daemon switches to safe-mode (no destructive ops, no admin-merge)\n6. Ambient events emitted: pr_shepherd_tick, pr_classified, pr_action_taken, pr_consensus_quorum, pr_shepherd_safe_mode_entered, pr_shepherd_safe_mode_cleared (registered in EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml + reserved.txt as needed)\n7. Test: scripts/ci/test-pr-shepherd-daemon.sh with synthetic 6-PR fixture covering each classification path\n8. Operator UX — daemon outcome surfaces to PWA cockpit operator-attention queue ONLY for UNKNOWN/DIRTY/real-fail cases; mergeable/auto-rebased cases never escalate\n9. Cost budget — daemon's GitHub API call rate is capped at CHUMP_GH_MAX_CALLS_PER_MIN (default 60); falls back to cache-first reads (INFRA-1081 pattern); critical-tagged for graphql_exhausted protection\n10. Sub-gaps filed for each major capability: (a) classification engine, (b) per-PR consensus tracker, (c) action dispatcher, (d) trunk-red guard, (e) launchd installer, (f) PWA cockpit operator-attention integration"
  notes: |
    Filed 2026-05-30T16:32Z under operator pain signal. Operator pattern over this session: keeps having to admin-merge manually; substrate exists in shadow mode (#2841); daemon is the missing engine. Marked P0 because the manual-admin-merge load is the rate-limiter on the entire fleet's throughput. Effort=l because the daemon has 10 AC items spanning bash + launchd + tests + cockpit integration; sub-gaps will decompose this into pickable units. Depends on landing PR #2858 (trunk-red), PR #2841 (gate substrate), RESILIENT-050 (reaper guard). Self-throttling + cache-first reads + trunk-red awareness are MANDATORY safety guards — without them this daemon could rage-merge during trunk-red and cause RESILIENT-050-class destruction.
  closed_date: '2026-06-05'
  closed_pr: 2894
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

