- id: META-207
  domain: META
  title: no-operator-escalation protocol — codify in AGENTS.md + CLAUDE.md + SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md; default mode is team consensus via FEEDBACK; operator-escalation has 4 explicit legitimate triggers; add detector + audit event
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    OPERATOR DIRECTIVE 2026-05-30T17:30Z (verbatim): 'Make sure the don't escalate to the human protocol is locked in for agents. I'm not here to babysit. I'm here for results.'
    
    Operator pain pattern over this session (and prior): every time an agent (orchestrator or sub-agent) asks the operator a question that the team can answer via consensus, the operator's attention is wasted. Every AskUserQuestion call where the answer is 'route this to the team' is a discipline failure.
    
    CURRENT STATE: ad-hoc. AGENTS.md mentions 'do not ask the operator first' in the gap-filing context (line 450) but lacks a top-level escalation discipline. CLAUDE.md references 'operator escape hatches' as audit-events but doesn't specify when escalation is legitimate vs not. SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md has no-clarifying-questions for sub-agents but doesn't extend to orchestrator-level escalation discipline.
    
    CODIFICATION needed in 3 docs simultaneously:
      1. AGENTS.md — top-level operator-decision-of-record section
      2. CLAUDE.md — Claude-Code-specific overlay mirroring same rule
      3. SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md — explicit sub-agent inheritance
    
    FOUR LEGITIMATE ESCALATION TRIGGERS (the ONLY ones):
      T1. Irreversible third-party action with no consensus mandate (financial spend, deploy to production beyond chump itself, external communication to partners/customers)
      T2. Credential rotation requiring operator's hands-on-keyboard (cannot be done by any agent; secrets are write-only via gh)
      T3. Operator-explicit-domain decisions: legal/license, partnership, pricing/business model, public branding/messaging
      T4. Halt-class fleet condition where consensus mechanism itself is unsafe to use (e.g., trunk-RED AND auth-storm AND queue-starve simultaneously)
    
    EVERYTHING ELSE → team consensus via FEEDBACK kind=proposal/vote, deliberator-loop tallies, consensus_resolved event drives action.
    
    ENFORCEMENT:
      - Detector emits kind=operator_escalation_unjustified when an agent calls AskUserQuestion / operator-recall outside the 4 triggers
      - Audit leaderboard at scripts/dev/operator-escalation-leaderboard.sh shows agents-per-day with unjustified escalations
      - SLO target: < 1 unjustified escalation per fleet-day
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. AGENTS.md gains a top-level '## No-operator-escalation discipline (operator-decision-of-record 2026-05-30)' section listing the 4 legitimate triggers with examples of legitimate vs illegitimate cases\n2. CLAUDE.md gains a mirrored 'No-escalation (CLAUDE-overlay)' section pointing to AGENTS.md as canonical + Claude-Code-specific guidance about AskUserQuestion tool use\n3. SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md extends 'no-clarifying-questions' to 'no-escalation' — sub-agents must use consensus mechanism (broadcast FEEDBACK kind=proposal) instead of returning 'I need to ask operator'\n4. scripts/dev/operator-escalation-leaderboard.sh — bash script that counts kind=operator_escalation_unjustified events per role per day, prints top-3\n5. EVENT_REGISTRY: kind=operator_escalation_unjustified registered with fields (role, escalation_kind, trigger_matched: T1"
    - T2
    - T3
    - T4
    - "none); detector documented\n6. Smoke test: scripts/ci/test-no-escalation-doctrine.sh — asserts the 3 doc files have the specific anchor headers + example pairs\n7. chump preflight green; raw-gh allowlist for the leaderboard script if needed\n8. Commit subject includes the 4 trigger codes (T1-T4) so the doctrine is searchable"
  notes: |
    Filed 2026-05-30T17:30Z by orchestrator under operator escalation-pain directive. Self-acknowledgement: orchestrator violated this discipline minutes before the operator directive by calling AskUserQuestion on the 4-option restrategy menu when consensus broadcast was the right path. This gap codifies the rule so future orchestrators don't repeat. Scope intentionally tight (3 docs + 1 detector + 1 test). Not a P0 — fleet's been running without explicit rule for months — but P1 because compounding operator-attention waste is real.
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2881
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

