- id: META-225
  domain: META
  title: "Quartermaster auto-fixers: daemon-activator + ghost-pr-closer + main-worktree-drift-detector — never need operator approval for these unwedging moves again"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    Operator just had to manually approve 3 unwedging moves that should have been automatic: (1) install a daemon (INFRA-2295 stale-pr-rebase-bot) whose code shipped to main but plist never loaded; (2) close a ghost PR (#2837 — gap INFRA-2067 status=done but PR still open + CONFLICTING); (3) work around a main worktree with ~150 untracked yaml + state.db drift. Operator-quote: 'automate this for FFS.. these are petty bullshit problems that we should not have to deal with'. Build the three auto-fixers as Quartermaster-extension daemons (META-205 sibling), each ~120 LOC bash. ZERO operator-in-loop. ZERO new fleet plumbing needed — all three patterns are detectable via git+gh+launchctl. Rough shape: (a) daemon-activator-loop.sh polls git log origin/main since 24h for paths matching scripts/setup/install-*.sh OR scripts/launchd/*.plist, derives launchd label from the install script, checks launchctl list — runs installer if absent; robust path: extracts installer via git show origin/main path so main-worktree dirty state never blocks; (b) ghost-pr-closer.sh queries gh pr list open, extracts gap_id regex, runs chump gap show for status — closes any PR where gap.status=done AND PR.mergeStateStatus in DIRTY or CONFLICTING with one-line comment; (c) main-worktree-drift-detector.sh runs from main worktree, counts untracked yaml + commits-behind, files an ALERT-class ambient + reserves a cleanup gap when thresholds breach (untracked greater than 50 OR behind greater than 20).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "scripts/coord/daemon-activator-loop.sh — every 5 min via launchd, scans last 24h of main commits for paths matching scripts/setup/install-*.sh OR scripts/launchd/*.plist; for each new install script: derives label, checks launchctl list grep label, runs installer if missing; uses git show origin/main extraction fallback when local copy missing (robust to dirty main worktree)"
    - Daemon-activator emits kind=daemon_auto_activated with label, install_script, source_pr, ts on success and kind=daemon_activator_failed with label, error on failure
    - scripts/coord/ghost-pr-closer.sh — every 15 min, scans gh pr list state open, extracts gap_id from PR title (regex matches all 10 prefixes INFRA META CREDIBLE RESILIENT EFFECTIVE FLEET DOC MEM VOA SCALE), runs chump gap show; if gap.status=done AND PR.mergeStateStatus in DIRTY or CONFLICTING then closes PR with comment 'Ghost — gap already status=done; closing per META-225 auto-fixer'
    - Ghost-pr-closer emits kind=ghost_pr_closed with pr, gap_id, gap_closed_pr, ts; self-throttle max 5 closes per run (rest deferred to .chump/ghost-pr-deferred.jsonl)
    - scripts/coord/main-worktree-drift-detector.sh — every 30 min, runs from main worktree path; counts (a) untracked .yaml under docs/gaps/, (b) commits between HEAD and origin/main; thresholds untracked greater than 50 OR behind greater than 20 emit kind=main_worktree_drift_detected with untracked_yaml, commits_behind, suggested_action
    - Drift-detector reserves a gap (P1 effort s domain META title 'main worktree cleanup — N untracked yaml + M commits behind') when threshold breached, debounced once per 6h via state file .chump/main-worktree-drift-last.json so it doesn't spam
    - "Three plists in scripts/launchd/: com.chump.daemon-activator.plist (StartInterval 300), com.chump.ghost-pr-closer.plist (900), com.chump.main-worktree-drift-detector.plist (1800); all KeepAlive=false, RunAtLoad=true"
    - "Three installers in scripts/setup/: install-daemon-activator.sh, install-ghost-pr-closer.sh, install-main-worktree-drift-detector.sh — each idempotent, uses scripts/lib/resolve-main-worktree.sh, mirrors install-stale-pr-rebase-bot.sh pattern exactly (INFRA-2295 reference impl)"
    - scripts/setup/bootstrap-manifest.yaml — three new entries so chump-fleet-bootstrap.sh --check verifies they're loaded
    - Ambient kinds registered via scanner-anchor comment pattern in each daemon script (EVENT_REGISTRY.yaml collision-prone, scanner-anchor is canonical safe path)
    - scripts/ci/test-quartermaster-auto-fixers.sh — runs all three daemons against synthetic git/gh state, asserts (a) daemon-activator runs installer when launchctl missing skips when present uses git-show fallback when local missing (b) ghost-pr-closer closes when status=done plus DIRTY leaves open when status=open (c) drift-detector fires above threshold silent below debounces correctly (d) all 3 ambient kinds emit (e) ghost-closer self-throttle caps at 5
    - "Doctrine update: .claude/agents/quartermaster.md gains an Auto-fixers section listing all 3 patterns with detection signal plus action; META-205 lane statement expanded to include detect plus auto-resolve repeat unwedging patterns"
    - "Doctrine update: docs/process/SHEPHERD_AUTONOMY_LADDER.md (new file) codifies when an unwedging move is reversible AND well-bounded skip the operator-approve step; lists the 3 META-225 patterns as approved-without-asking"
    - "Self-bootstrapping: daemon-activator on FIRST tick will detect itself plus ghost-pr-closer plus drift-detector (since they ship together) and validate they're all loaded — recursive coverage proves the pattern works"
    - "PR title: feat(META-225) EFFECTIVE P0 — Quartermaster auto-fixers (daemon-activator + ghost-pr-closer + main-worktree-drift-detector); commit body includes Rust-First-Bypass trailer with reason bash daemons orchestrating launchctl gh git CLIs no canonical store mutation matches INFRA-2295 reference impl"
  closed_date: '2026-05-30'
  closed_pr: 2887
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

