- id: MISSION-005
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION P0: Chump PWA native A2A — agents/sessions/chats in same repo connect through A2A without operator-as-messenger (the actual product differentiator vs Claude Code's single-session poll model)"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: l
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Background — operator at 19:36Z named the constraint precisely — Claude Code sessions don't see new info unless (a) a tool call fires the PostToolUse inbox-poll hook OR (b) the user types in chat. Today's session shipped 6+ workarounds (INFRA-1860 inbox-poll, INFRA-1879 session-id derivation, INFRA-1908 wake template, INFRA-1936 inbox-watcher Monitor pattern, INFRA-1940 orchestrator productization, the fleet-registry.jsonl channel) — all are workarounds for what should be a native PWA capability. The pain proves the demand; the differentiator IS native A2A"
    - PWA hosts the A2A spine — when 2+ Claude Code (or Cursor / Codex / Aider / Continue / opencode-bigpickle) sessions are opened against the same chump repo, the PWA detects them (via filesystem watcher OR session-registration handshake) and lets any session DM any other session without operator routing
    - Wake guarantee — when session A sends message to session B via PWA A2A, session B's harness gets the message in <2s via (a) a websocket / SSE channel the PWA pushes to + the harness consumes OR (b) a harness-tool the PWA injects that polls every N seconds OR (c) for Claude Code specifically — PWA writes to a watched file that the harness's Monitor primitive picks up. ANY of the 3 satisfies the AC; Claude Code path (c) is the only one usable today, others are future-harness work
    - No-operator-routing — operator does NOT have to manually go to a session and tell it to check inbox. The PWA's job is to make that wake happen automatically per (3) above. Operator interaction is BY EXCEPTION (e.g. operator-recall halt-class), not BY DEFAULT for every dispatch
    - Multi-harness fleet — same A2A works across Claude Code + opencode-bigpickle + cursor + any Anthropic-SDK harness via the AGENT_API.md contract (INFRA-1050). PWA is the common bus; each harness has a thin adapter
    - Visible in PWA UI — operator sees a single dashboard with all alive agents + recent A2A traffic + dead-letter queue + role-typed routing status. Replaces today's 'operator stares at 6 Claude Code windows + greps ambient.jsonl' workflow
    - Pairs with — META-061 A2A frontier roadmap, INFRA-1118 through INFRA-1123 (A2A Layer 2 sub-gaps), INFRA-1115 broadcast.sh (the file-based fallback), INFRA-1936 Monitor inbox-watcher (Claude-Code-specific path), and the entire fleet-registry + curator-productization arc from 2026-05-24 (which all become PWA-managed when this lands)
    - "Done definition — operator opens 2 Claude Code windows against the same chump repo; one types 'send ping to peer' and within 2s the other window's session sees the ping without operator switching windows or typing anything; PWA dashboard shows both sessions as alive + the message in the A2A log. Walk-away test: operator can close the PWA dashboard and the A2A still works (PWA is the visualization, not the transport bottleneck — transport is file-watch + Monitor or future websocket)"
  notes: |
    filed 19:37Z 2026-05-24 by wizard after operator articulated the actual product thesis. Today's session shipped 6+ A2A workarounds for what should be a 1st-class PWA feature. This is the differentiator that justifies Chump existing vs raw Claude Code use
  closed_date: '2026-05-25'
  closed_pr: 2552
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

