- id: MISSION-032
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION P1 UMBRELLA: scale to 100s → 10,000s of external repos — per-phase load-bearing substrate, strategy doc, customer/privacy boundaries"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xl
  description: |
    Operator framing 2026-06-05: 'I want this to scale to 100s of repos soon. I alone have 100 repos. So maybe we need 10,000s.' Today's tag-based namespacing (external_repo:<owner>/<repo> in gap.skills_required + ~/.chump/external/<owner>/<repo>/ on disk + single state.db + flat .chump-locks/) is the correct architecture for 1-10 repos and is what BEAST proves. It breaks at known points past that. UMBRELLA breakdown by scale phase: (Phase A, 10 repos — proven by BEAST today) tag-based registry, single state.db, flat lease namespace, manual onboard scans, single mission scoreboard. (Phase B, 100 repos — load-bearing for operator's own portfolio) first-class repos table + lease partitioning + clone GC + scan rotation + scoreboard rollup + onboard scout scheduling. (Phase C, 1000-10000 repos — multi-customer commercial vision) state.db sharding (INFRA-1967 deps), ambient.jsonl partition (INFRA-1973 deps), per-customer cascade-tier privacy enforcement, customer-curator abstraction, repo-affinity picker, shallow-clone strategy, cross-repo dep tracking, onboard scout economic prioritization, multi-machine substrate (Pi mesh / model splitting — operator fleet vision). Decomposes into 6 Phase-B Tier-1 sub-gaps (filed under this umbrella) + 4 Phase-C Tier-2 references (existing INFRA-1721/1742/1967/1973 + new) + strategy doc docs/strategy/MULTI_REPO_SCALE_2026-06-05.md. Pairs with MISSION-010 (the BEAST proof is N=1; this umbrella generalizes to N=10000).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - docs/strategy/MULTI_REPO_SCALE_2026-06-05.md exists with 3-phase model + per-phase substrate decisions + which gaps cover each
    - docs/MISSION.md updated to include Scale section (current phase + next-phase trigger conditions)
    - "Phase B (100 repos) Tier-1 sub-gaps filed: repos-table-first-class + lease-partition + clone-GC + scan-rotation + scoreboard-rollup + onboard-scout-scheduling"
    - "Phase C (1000-10000 repos) Tier-2 cross-refs added to umbrella description: INFRA-1967 state.db scaling + INFRA-1973 ambient.jsonl + INFRA-1721 per-repo capabilities + INFRA-1742 per-repo .chump-config + new multi-customer privacy gap"
  outcome_id: MISSION-032

- id: MISSION-033
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION P1 (MISSION-032 Phase-B Tier-1): first-class repos table — schema + auto-populate from gap-tag scan on chump gap import"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    MISSION-032 Phase-B Tier-1. Today the set of tracked external repos is INFERRED from SELECT DISTINCT skills_required LIKE '%external_repo:%' FROM gaps — a string-scan with no lifecycle (no last_scan_at, last_clone_at, last_ship_at, cascade_tier, status). All Phase-B substrate (clone GC, scoreboard rollup, onboard scheduling) needs a first-class index. Schema: CREATE TABLE repos (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, owner TEXT, name TEXT, added_at INTEGER, last_scan_at INTEGER, last_clone_at INTEGER, last_ship_at INTEGER, cascade_tier TEXT DEFAULT 'dogfood', status TEXT DEFAULT 'active'). Auto-populated by 'chump gap import' from gap-tag scan. Drives MISSION-035/037/038. Decisions: keep tag in skills_required as canonical (this table is derived), no per-repo state mutation through this table.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Schema migration adds repos table with the documented columns
    - "chump gap import auto-upserts a repos row for every distinct external_repo:* tag found"
    - chump repos list / show CLI subcommands work
  outcome_id: MISSION-032

