- id: MISSION-039
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION P1: extend chump outcome bootstrap with pillar outcomes (CREDIBLE-000 / EFFECTIVE-000 / RESILIENT-000 / ZERO-WASTE-000) + add domain-prefix backfill heuristic"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Follow-up from MISSION-030 #3070 (Sonnet's report flagged this). After bootstrap, the dominant unmatched cluster is CREDIBLE-*, EFFECTIVE-*, RESILIENT-*, ZERO-WASTE-* — no mission keyword to match heuristics on. I applied an ad-hoc SQL bootstrap during tick 6 of the musher loop (created the 4 pillar outcomes manually, bulk-linked by domain prefix). Hit a SQL operator-precedence bug (OR ... AND parsed as OR (AND)) that temporarily mis-linked 2329 gaps to CREDIBLE-000; reverted + recovered. Coverage went 5% → 23% of open gaps. The PROPER fix: (a) extend chump outcome bootstrap to seed the 4 pillar outcomes as well as the 4 canonical missions (8 total); (b) add a domain-prefix backfill heuristic (7th rule: gap.id prefix matches outcome.id prefix → link) that's properly parenthesized; (c) test coverage for the heuristic. Pairs with MISSION-030 which shipped the framework.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - chump outcome bootstrap seeds 8 outcomes (the 4 canonical missions + 4 pillar outcomes CREDIBLE-000 / EFFECTIVE-000 / RESILIENT-000 / ZERO-WASTE-000) idempotently
    - chump outcome backfill --apply with domain-prefix heuristic 7 (id prefix matches outcome prefix) links remaining unlinked CREDIBLE-* / EFFECTIVE-* / RESILIENT-* / ZERO-WASTE-* gaps to their pillar outcome
    - Test in scripts/ci/test-chump-outcome.sh covers the domain-prefix heuristic (link + unlink + idempotent re-apply)
    - "Final open-gap coverage rate: >50% (currently 23% after ad-hoc bootstrap)"
  outcome_id: CREDIBLE-000

- id: MISSION-040
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION: active-mission-aware + dependency-ordered picker ranking (mission_rank is binary today)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Picker today (MISSION-028 #3061) treats mission-rank as BINARY: a gap either matches the active mission or doesn't. Two missing dimensions: (a) ACTIVE_MISSION-aware ranking — picker should read ~/.chump/ACTIVE_MISSION (currently MISSION-010) and weight gaps whose outcome_id matches that specific mission higher than gaps linked to other outcomes; (b) DEPENDENCY-ORDERED ranking — gaps with no open depends_on should rank higher than gaps blocked by other open gaps (don't pick a gap whose dependencies aren't done). Today both decisions are missing → fleet picks gaps that are mission-linked-in-theory but depend on stuff that isn't done. Pairs with MISSION-030 outcomes FK (gives picker a real signal to rank by) and MISSION-008 outcome FK schema (the column the picker reads). NOTE: this gap's description was briefly corrupted during MISSION-040 vs MISSION-041 confusion in musher tick 7 (2026-06-05 16:50Z); restored via CHUMP_ALLOW_GAP_REWRITE=1 to match the original title.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - Picker reads ~/.chump/ACTIVE_MISSION and prefers gaps with outcome_id matching that mission over gaps with other (or no) outcomes, at same priority/effort tier
    - Picker deprioritizes a gap if any of its open depends_on entries are themselves unclosed (deps_first rule)
    - "Live regression test: 2 same-pri/effort gaps, A linked to ACTIVE_MISSION + no deps, B linked to a different outcome + has open dep → picker chooses A"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: MISSION-041
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION P0: backfill gap.skills_required with external_repo: tags — picker can't see BEAST gaps because the routing field is empty (description text doesn't route)"
  status: closed
  priority: P0
  effort: s
  description: |
    VERIFIED 2026-06-05 16:50Z (musher tick 7, Sonnet finding from MISSION-033 #3073). After shipping MISSION-018 (flag) + MISSION-028 (picker mission-rank) + MISSION-033 (repos table auto-populate), discovered the picker has nothing to act on because gap.skills_required is EMPTY on the BEAST execution slices (MISSION-016/017/019…025) and other BEAST-tagged gaps. The 'external_repo:repairman29/BEAST-MODE' tag is only in DESCRIPTION text, which is informational and not consumed by capability.rs:130 or any picker logic. Verified: sqlite SELECT id, skills_required FROM gaps WHERE (skills_required LIKE '%external_repo:%' OR title LIKE '%BEAST%') AND status='open' returns 10+ rows with empty skills_required, 0 with the tag. ROOT CAUSE: gap-filing convention drifted — operators put 'external_repo:' in description for human readability, but never copied to skills_required (the routing field). FIX: (a) write a one-shot backfill script (similar to MISSION-030 backfill pattern) that scans gap description + title for 'BEAST', 'repairman29/BEAST-MODE', 'BEAST-MODE', external_repo: phrases, and adds 'external_repo:repairman29/BEAST-MODE' to skills_required; (b) optionally add a chump gap reserve --external-repo <owner/repo> shortcut that sets skills_required correctly; (c) audit other external_repo: gap classes (ehippy/derelict etc per scout output) and backfill them too. Until this lands, MISSION-018 + MISSION-028 + MISSION-033 produce 0 net value.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "After backfill: sqlite SELECT COUNT(*) FROM gaps WHERE skills_required LIKE '%external_repo:repairman29/BEAST-MODE%' AND status='open' returns >= 5 (the BEAST execution slices)"
    - chump repos list (after MISSION-033 lands + gap import re-runs) shows repairman29/BEAST-MODE in the list
    - "Optional: chump gap reserve --external-repo <owner/repo> shortcut wires skills_required directly so this drift doesn't recur"
  notes: |
    [2026-06-05T18:49:48Z] Shipped #3078 via Sonnet dispatch. 99 gaps tagged, 15 open BEAST. The MISSION-018/028/033 chain now has data to route.
  closed_pr: 3078
  skills_required: "external_repo:repairman29/BEAST-MODE"
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

