- id: MISSION-044
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION UMBRELLA: Cut the Friction — eliminate the toil + papercuts that slow every agent and the operator"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Friction — the toil/papercuts that slow every agent AND the operator — is a first-class bug class, not background noise. This 2026-06-08 session alone, friction caused: (a) ~30 turns of confused hand-grinding before the real root surfaced; (b) a 13h SILENT fleet stall from a dead-flag auth probe (claude --once removed by a CLI update) — RESILIENT-134; (c) a 60-line docs commit taking 5 attempts through a stacked, non-fail-fast commit-gate gauntlet — RESILIENT-137; (d) every fresh-gap manual ship hitting bot-merge not-found until the YAML is hand-copied — RESILIENT-138; (e) fleet launch blocked by silent PTY exhaustion (527>511) — RESILIENT-139; (f) bot-merge wedges: cold-build timeout / lease-corruption / post-fmt hang — RESILIENT-132/133; (g) agents drowning in 1584-line core docs + 545 total, fixed by a north-star — META-287; (h) the fleet-brief lying healthy through a silent stall — fixed by fresh-eyes comparator_6 (META-287). PRINCIPLE: every gate must FAIL FAST and list the FULL remediation up front (no discover-one-blocker-per-retry); no non-tty hangs; no stacked surprises; a legitimate small change lands in one clean pass. This umbrella collects friction sub-gaps and drives down attempts-per-ship + turns-to-first-ship.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - every commit/ship gate fails fast, listing ALL required remediation in ONE message (no serial discover-and-retry)
    - no gate hangs on non-tty stdin in headless mode
    - a legitimate small (1-file/docs) change lands in ONE commit attempt + one ship
    - RESILIENT-132/133/134/137/138/139 tracked under this umbrella; new friction filed here
    - a friction metric (attempts-per-ship or turns-to-first-ship) is surfaced so the trend is visible

- id: MISSION-045
  domain: MISSION
  title: "MISSION-008 follow-up: outcome_id REQUIRED at reserve for P0 (parallel to CREDIBLE-107 --evidence gate); picker tie-breaks toward traced; --status=done flip requires outcome_id"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "`chump gap reserve --priority P0` REQUIRES --outcome <id> where id is a valid row in outcomes table; refuses without it (mirrors CREDIBLE-107 --evidence gate). Bypass: CHUMP_GAP_RESERVE_NO_OUTCOME=1 + emit kind=outcome_gate_bypassed audit event."
    - "`chump gap set <ID> --status done` (or `chump gap ship`) for P0/P1 gaps refuses to close without outcome_id set. Bypass: same env var. Mirrors how MISSION-008 HARD CONSTRAINT permits — only the P0/P1 path is gated; P2/P3 stay permissionless."
    - "Picker tie-break: when multiple pickable gaps have equal priority/effort, prefer the one with outcome_id over the one without (encourages tracing without breaking permissionless picking)."
    - "roadmap-status --exit-on-drift gains TEETH: untraced_open_p0 > 0 → exit 1 (today: signal only, no action). Now that the FK landed (MISSION-008) and reserve is gated (this gap), the original HARD CONSTRAINT in MISSION-008 description (\"do NOT wire roadmap-status --exit-on-drift until AFTER the FK lands\") is satisfied."
    - "Backfill sweep: audit current 232 untraced open gaps; for each, propose the most likely outcome via heuristic (title/domain pattern matching against the 8 outcomes); operator reviews and bulk-applies. Target: untraced < 30 after one sweep."
    - "CLAUDE.md gains a Mission-Tracing section: \"Every P0/P1 gap belongs to an outcome. Filed without one → blocked at reserve. Closed without one → blocked at ship.\""
  notes: |
    Origin: operator 2026-06-09T04:45Z "WTF I thought all gaps belong to missions and we worked them top to bottom?" Diagnosis: MISSION-008 shipped the SCHEMA but HARD CONSTRAINT explicitly forbade enforcement until follow-up. Current state: 1159 open gaps, 232 untraced (20%), 5 untraced open P0s. The hook tells us; nothing acts. This gap closes that loop. The CREDIBLE-107 pattern (--evidence gate just shipped) is the template. Untraced gaps that pre-date this enforcement: backfilled via heuristic + operator review (no migration retroactive ban).
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

