  title: "PRODUCT: PWA PR diff renderer — render PR diff inline in PWA with AC-fit check alongside"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today reviewing a fleet PR requires switching to GitHub. With PR list
    (PRODUCT-084) shipping, the next step is inline diff. Bonus: render
    AC-fit check alongside so operator sees 'did this PR satisfy its gap's
    AC?' at a glance (preview of CREDIBLE-026 enforcement).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - PWA /prs/{N} detail view renders syntax-highlighted diff using gh pr diff <N> output + a JS syntax highlighter (highlight.js or Shiki, whichever is smaller for the file types in this repo)
    - "AC-fit panel: parse PR title for gap ID; pull gap's AC from state.db; render each AC bullet with a check/cross/unknown marker (heuristic: AC keyword present in diff = check; absent = unknown; explicit anti-match = cross). Mirrors COG-052 audit-ac logic"
    - "Side-by-side toggle: 3 modes — Unified (default), Split, AC-fit-only (just the AC panel + which files satisfy each bullet)"
    - Per-file collapse/expand; long diffs paginated at 1000 lines
    - Backend /api/prs/{N}/diff endpoint streams the diff (large diffs)
    - Backend /api/prs/{N}/ac-fit endpoint returns the per-AC-bullet check result
    - "scripts/ci/test-pwa-pr-diff.sh: fixture PR with known AC; assert renderer + AC-fit results"
    - Pairs with CREDIBLE-026 (scope detector) — diff renderer surfaces the scope-divergence flags inline so operator sees them at review time, not post-merge
    - Pairs with PRODUCT-084 (PR list) — list is the index; this is the detail
    - Pairs with PRODUCT-086 (action panel) — diff is the context; action panel is the actuator
  notes: |
    [2026-05-15T04:28:26Z] PWA phase: 2 (Inbox & PR Loop) — see docs/product/PWA_ROADMAP.md (PRODUCT-121)

- id: PRODUCT-086
  domain: PRODUCT
  title: "PRODUCT: PWA PR action panel — approve/revise/revert/comment from PWA via gh, eliminating GitHub round-trips"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Once PR list (PRODUCT-084) + diff (PRODUCT-085) are in PWA, the last
    step is acting on PRs from inside chump. Approve, request changes,
    revert, comment — all via gh CLI from the backend, no GitHub UI.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "PWA /prs/{N} detail view (post-PRODUCT-085) adds action panel with 4 primary buttons: Approve, Request changes, Revert, Comment"
    - "Approve: POST /api/prs/{N}/approve → server runs `gh pr review {N} --approve --body \"<optional comment>\"`; on success refresh PR state in UI"
    - "Request changes: opens textarea modal; POST /api/prs/{N}/request-changes with body → `gh pr review {N} --request-changes --body ...`"
    - "Revert: confirm-modal warning that this opens a NEW PR via `gh pr revert {N}` (gh has no native revert; use a sibling script that branches + reverts the merge commit)"
    - "Comment: textarea + submit; POST /api/prs/{N}/comment → `gh pr comment {N} --body ...`"
    - "Auth: server-side gh uses GH_TOKEN env var or keychain; PWA never sees the token"
    - "Audit log: every action emits ambient kind=operator_pr_action with type, pr, operator_session"
    - Action buttons disabled when PR state can't accept them (e.g., can't approve a closed PR)
    - "Mobile-friendly: action panel collapses into a 'Actions' button that opens bottom sheet on narrow viewports"
    - "scripts/ci/test-pwa-pr-actions.sh: mock gh calls; assert each action invokes the right gh subcommand"
    - Pairs with PRODUCT-085 (diff) — actions follow context; you don't approve without seeing the diff
    - Pairs with PRODUCT-079 (Needs your judgment) — judgment queue's per-item link routes here for action
  notes: |
    [2026-05-15T04:28:26Z] PWA phase: 2 (Inbox & PR Loop) — see docs/product/PWA_ROADMAP.md (PRODUCT-121)

- id: PRODUCT-087
  domain: PRODUCT
  title: "PRODUCT: PWA local-only onboarding wizard — guide solo dev through CHUMP_WORK_BACKEND=ollama setup with zero Anthropic creds (depends on EFFECTIVE-017/018)"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    Per CHUMP_FIRST_DOCTRINE, the mission is offline solo devs on local
    LLMs. Today the PWA assumes default chump config (Anthropic backend).
    This gap is the PWA-side of the universalization: a wizard that
    sets up Ollama + chooses a model + verifies chump can run without
    Anthropic credentials.
    
    DEPENDS ON: EFFECTIVE-017 (WorkBackend trait) + EFFECTIVE-018
    (pluggable auth) — both filed but not shipped. P2 until they land.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - New PWA view /onboard/local launched from PRODUCT-082 welcome flow when user picks 'I want to use local LLMs only'
    - "Step 1: detect Ollama at default http://localhost:11434/api/tags; if absent, show install instructions (`brew install ollama` for mac, `curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh` for linux) + 'Probe again' button"
    - "Step 2: list installed Ollama models (`ollama list`); if empty, suggest `ollama pull qwen2.5:7b` as a tested-stable default per memory project_model_dogfood.md"
    - "Step 3: pick model from list (default = qwen2.5:7b if present, else first available); set CHUMP_WORK_BACKEND=ollama + OLLAMA_DEFAULT_MODEL in .chump/config.toml"
    - "Step 4: verify by running a smoke gap (the same fixture from CREDIBLE-046 'chump without Anthropic' CI gate); assert worker spawned + commit produced"
    - "Step 5: confirmation page — 'You're set up. Anthropic credentials NOT required. Your fleet runs entirely locally.'"
    - Backend /api/onboard/local/probe (step 1), /api/onboard/local/models (step 2), /api/onboard/local/configure (step 3), /api/onboard/local/verify (step 4)
    - "scripts/ci/test-pwa-local-onboard.sh: fixture Ollama mock; walk all 5 steps; assert config.toml written correctly + smoke gap completes"
    - Documented in docs/process/EXTERNAL_REPO_USAGE.md (per DOC-022 when shipped) as the canonical local-only setup path
    - Pairs with EFFECTIVE-017/018 (WorkBackend + pluggable auth) — onboarding is the UI; those are the runtime. Cannot meaningfully ship this until they ship.
  notes: |
    [2026-05-15T04:28:26Z] PWA phase: 4 (Demo Mode) — see docs/product/PWA_ROADMAP.md (PRODUCT-121)

