- id: PRODUCT-138
  domain: PRODUCT
  title: "EFFECTIVE: offline PWA — IndexedDB mirror + stale-while-revalidate + service-worker cache invalidation"
  status: open
  priority: P3
  effort: l
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Backlog-promoted 2026-05-16, DEFERRED to Q3: today the PWA hits backend API for every read. Offline = no signal. Strategic for the air-gapped solo-dev tier-3 audience but NOT needed for Marcus or 50/hr push. Park as P3 until post-50/hr stabilization."
    - "Read path: stale-while-revalidate (SWR). Each GET caches into IndexedDB on success; subsequent calls return cache immediately and revalidate in background. Cache miss + offline → return last-known with stale=true UI badge."
    - "Write path: writes (claim gap, ship, comment) queue locally in IndexedDB pending-ops table if offline. On reconnect, replay in order. Server returns conflict-detection result; operator UI flags any rejected write."
    - "Conflict resolution: NOT last-write-wins. Server is arbiter. claim is CAS — first online write wins. Ship is idempotent (PR number is identity). For pure-read state, SWR is sufficient."
    - "Service worker (web/v2/sw.js) manages cache invalidation: subscribes to ambient.jsonl stream, busts matching cache keys on relevant kinds (gap_state_changed, pr_merged, lesson_added)."
    - "Honest scope: PWA without internet = read recent state, queue pending writes. CANNOT claim a gap (needs server CAS), CANNOT open a PR (needs GitHub). Document this in docs/process/OFFLINE_PWA_SEMANTICS.md."
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-pwa-offline.sh: dev server up, fetch /api/gaps then take network down (mock), assert subsequent /api/gaps from PWA returns cached + stale flag."
    - "DEPENDENCY: Marcus M-B canonical demo + 50/hr plan must be done first. This is post-Q2 work."
    - "Out of scope: full P2P sync between operators offline (separate gap if ever wanted)."

