  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Backlog-promoted 2026-05-16: PRODUCT-108 shipped the Tauri-desktop first-run wizard (detect+init checklist: brain / autopilot / repo / model). Browser visitors to chump --web see an empty Dashboard — no onboarding. The persona kit (docs/strategy/commercial/PERSONAS_VALIDATION.md) literally points evaluators at github.com/repairman29/chump with no marketing site; the in-browser wizard IS the marketing site."
    - Reuse the same 4-stage checklist (brain, autopilot, repo, model) from PRODUCT-108 but render in the PWA at /onboard route. State management identical (chump-init backend endpoints already exist).
    - "Browser-equivalent for Tauri-only steps: (a) detect repo → operator pastes git remote URL OR uploads .git/config; (b) install runner → instruction page with copy-paste command (\"bash scripts/setup/install-self-hosted-runner.sh\") + verification poll on /api/fleet/runners; (c) provision OAuth → standard browser OAuth flow through chump backend acting as relay."
    - "Steps that genuinely cant work in browser (e.g. write launchd plist) become inline \"do this in your terminal\" code blocks with a verify-button that re-polls when done."
    - "Replace empty Dashboard for fresh visits: if no .chump/initialized=true cookie, redirect to /onboard."
