- id: RESEARCH-001
  domain: RESEARCH
  title: "CREDIBLE: EVAL-094 and RESEARCH-026 are phantom IDs cited in RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md eval-awareness mandate — not in gap registry"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    We are failing at eval-awareness methodology enforcement. RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md requires citing EVAL-094 or RESEARCH-026 for mechanism analysis with |delta|>0.05. Neither gap exists in the public gap registry.
    
    Evidence:
    - find docs/gaps -name 'EVAL-094*' -> empty
    - find docs/gaps -name 'RESEARCH-026*' -> empty
    - docs/process/RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md:87-97: 'must cite either (a) a paired naturalized-framing comparison from the RESEARCH-026 / EVAL-094 result set...'
    - docs/process/RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md:97: 'Until EVAL-094 ships its n=50/cell paired comparison, the Validated Findings table carries a standing caveat'
    
    The eval-awareness sandbagging directive (added 2026-05-02, referencing arXiv:2508.00943) names a specific gap that every mechanism claim must clear — but that gap does not exist in the registry agents and pickers can act on. The mandate is un-enforceable. RED_LETTER#12 (2026-05-18).
    
    Falsifying condition: EVAL-094 and RESEARCH-026 exist in chump-proprietary (private companion repo) and are not expected in the public gap registry — the public RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md references are intentionally pointing off-repo.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - EVAL-094 gap YAML exists in docs/gaps/EVAL-094.yaml with concrete AC for the n=50/cell paired naturalized-framing eval
    - RESEARCH-026 gap YAML exists in docs/gaps/RESEARCH-026.yaml OR RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md is updated to replace the phantom ID with the correct current gap ID
    - The mechanism-kappa pre-commit hook (referenced in RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md §4) has a CI test that verifies its phantom-ID references resolve to real gap files
    - chump gap audit-priorities missing-dep check covers phantom IDs in RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md (not just in gap depends_on fields)
  opened_date: '2026-05-18'
  closed_pr: 2516

- id: RESEARCH-026
  domain: RESEARCH
  title: "CREDIBLE: fixture taxonomy for evaluation-awareness — classify the 20 EVAL-094 fixtures by susceptibility to lab-context discrimination (preamble density, rubric markers, role-header presence)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Companion qualitative analysis to EVAL-094. Before the paired naturalized-framing sweep
    runs, each fixture must be classified by its structural susceptibility to evaluation-
    awareness bias. This taxonomy (a) predicts which cells will show the largest B−A delta
    in EVAL-094, (b) informs fixture redesign if the eval finds confounding, and (c) gives
    a reusable rubric for all future fixture design in the chump eval suite.
    
    Susceptibility signals: explicit task IDs, numbered rubrics, "evaluate / assess / score"
    imperatives in preamble, "assistant / user" role headers, markdown tables with
    "expected output" columns, benchmark-style framing ("test case N of M").
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Taxonomy doc at docs/eval/fixture-taxonomy-eval-awareness.md with a rubric table: signal, weight (1-3), example, how to naturalize"
    - "Each of the 20 EVAL-094 fixtures scored against the rubric: susceptibility score (0-15), predicted B−A magnitude (low/medium/high), naturalization notes"
    - "Rubric validated against ≥ 2 published datasets from arXiv:2508.00943 or IAPS 2026 — documented in the taxonomy doc with citations"
    - "Output includes a redesign checklist: for each high-susceptibility fixture, concrete edit to reduce lab markers (used as input to EVAL-094 naturalized framing condition)"
    - Cross-links EVAL-094 result doc once available; taxonomy supersedes the standing caveat in RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md once EVAL-094 decision-rule passes
    - "Review: taxonomy doc reviewed by ≥1 operator before EVAL-094 sweep launches (recorded as a co-author or reviewer note in the preregistration)"
  notes: |
    Cited by: docs/process/RESEARCH_INTEGRITY.md §4 (phantom-ID fix: RESEARCH-001)
    Companion: EVAL-094 (quantitative paired eval using this fixture set)
    This is a lightweight qualitative deliverable — the main measurement is in EVAL-094.

- id: RESILIENT-006
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: PR-stale auto-rebase — if a MERGEABLE+BLOCKED PR has CI failures on checks that have since passed on main >Nh, scripts/coord/pr-rescue.sh auto-rebases + force-pushes + re-arms auto-merge; would have unwedged #1433's 17h stall"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/coord/pr-rescue.sh exists and is invocable as `pr-rescue.sh <PR-N> [--dry-run]`
    - "Pre-flight checks before acting: (a) PR mergeable=MERGEABLE+state=BLOCKED, (b) auto-merge armed, (c) no active sibling lease on the gap (check .chump-locks/*.json), (d) failing CI checks have green counterparts on origin/main HEAD"
    - "Rescue sequence: disarm auto-merge → fetch + git worktree add /tmp/rescue-<N> → rebase origin/main → force-with-lease push → re-arm auto-merge → cleanup worktree"
    - "Abort with non-zero exit + structured ambient event when: (a) rebase produces conflicts, (b) net diff after rebase deletes >100 lines (delegates to CREDIBLE-027), (c) sibling lease detected"
    - Emits ambient kind=pr_rescue_attempt with pr, outcome (success/conflict/skipped/aborted), reason
    - Wraps as a launchd job dev.chump.pr-rescue (4h interval, ThrottleInterval=900) that scans open PRs and rescues eligible ones autonomously
    - scripts/ci/test-pr-rescue.sh creates a fixture PR that's MERGEABLE+BLOCKED on a since-fixed flake, asserts pr-rescue.sh promotes it to PENDING within one invocation
    - CLAUDE.md ship-pipeline section updated to reference pr-rescue.sh as the canonical recovery for stalled-but-mergeable PRs (today the manual disarm-push-rearm loop is documented but not scripted)
    - "Idempotent: running twice on the same PR within 30min is a no-op; second invocation emits skipped_recent_rescue"
  closed_pr: 1475
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-007
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: fleet dispatcher refuses to ship a gap whose acceptance_criteria contains TODO-placeholder lines — surfaces the gap for AC-fix instead of bare-minimum interpretation"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "scripts/dispatch/worker.sh and/or _pick_and_claim_gap.py refuses to claim a gap whose state.db row has any acceptance_criterion matching the regex /^TODO:/i or empty/null AC field"
    - Refusal emits ambient kind=gap_skipped_todo_ac with gap_id, ac_count, todo_count so the operator (or PM-curator role) can prioritize fixing the AC
    - scripts/coord/gap-preflight.sh gains the same check — exits non-zero with named error when a gap's AC is all-TODO; documents the fix command (chump gap set <ID> --acceptance-criteria '...')
    - "Today PR #1457/1458/1459 (CREDIBLE-025/027/028) all shipped against AC that had been stale-binary-regen-wiped to TODO placeholders. Worker saw TODO, shipped bare-minimum interpretation of title, closed. This gap stops that pattern."
    - Pairs with INFRA-825 (hard-fail destructive bulk-YAML ops) — INFRA-825 prevents the wipe; RESILIENT-007 catches whatever wipe happened pre-INFRA-825 and refuses to ship against the resulting TODO AC
    - "Test: synthetic state.db with a gap whose AC is ['TODO: foo', 'TODO: bar'] — worker pickup attempt logs kind=gap_skipped_todo_ac and moves to the next gap"
    - "Operator override: CHUMP_DISPATCH_ALLOW_TODO_AC=1 (very loud, audited) for the rare case where the operator explicitly wants to ship against TODO AC (e.g. exploratory work)"
    - Documents the policy in scripts/dispatch/worker.sh header + AGENTS.md per-worker contract section
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

