- id: RESILIENT-030
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: typed dispatch contract for Opus→Sonnet sub-agent calls — wizard's Agent tool dispatches go through DispatchContract serializer instead of free-form markdown prompts (mirrors handoff curator's CodeFixContract pattern, but for sub-agent dispatch)
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today's wizard sub-agent dispatches are free-form markdown prompts (~80-100 lines each). They include WORKFLOW, EXPECTED FIX, CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS, REPORT BACK sections — but the SHAPE varies per dispatch and the verification is in human-readable prose. The handoff curator's typed contracts (crates/chump-handoff/src/contracts.rs — DecomposeContract / CodeFixContract / GapReviewContract) solve this for curator-to-curator handoffs. Mirror that pattern for Opus-to-Sonnet sub-agent dispatch.\n\nFIX: define crates/chump-handoff/src/dispatch_contract.rs with DispatchContract struct fields: gap_id (required), allowed_paths (Vec<PathBuf>, required), expected_commit_prefix (String, required: format 'fix|feat|chore(<GAP-ID>):'), budget_minutes (u32, default 90), bot_merge_timeout_s (u32, default 600), background_run (bool, default true), require_self_check (bool, default true). \n\nProvide a serializer: DispatchContract::to_sonnet_prompt() -> String that produces a canonical markdown prompt with required sections (CONTRACT block, GAP, WORKFLOW, SELF-CHECK, REPORT BACK). The CONTRACT block at top is machine-readable YAML so sub-agent can parse + verify before every commit/push.\n\nSelf-check block instructs sub-agent: 'Before every commit, verify .git/COMMIT_EDITMSG mentions  AND all staged files are subset of . If not, abort the commit and replan.'\n\nAlso provide a wrapper helper scripts/coord/dispatch-sonnet.sh that takes JSON contract on stdin + emits the rendered prompt + calls the Claude Agent tool (when invoked from Opus). Bridge today's free-form Opus calls to the contract.\n\nGoal: every Opus-to-Sonnet dispatch goes through the contract. Audit via kind=sub_agent_dispatched ambient event with contract field.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - crates/chump-handoff/src/dispatch_contract.rs defines DispatchContract struct with fields gap_id, allowed_paths, expected_commit_prefix, budget_minutes (default 90), bot_merge_timeout_s (default 600), background_run (default true), require_self_check (default true)
    - "DispatchContract::to_sonnet_prompt() serializer produces a canonical markdown prompt with CONTRACT (YAML, machine-readable), GAP, WORKFLOW, SELF-CHECK, REPORT BACK sections"
    - Self-check section instructs sub-agent to validate commit_msg mentions gap_id AND staged files are subset of allowed_paths BEFORE every commit (pairs with RESILIENT-025+026 hook checks for defense-in-depth)
    - "scripts/coord/dispatch-sonnet.sh wrapper: reads JSON DispatchContract on stdin, validates required fields, renders + prints the prompt (for piping into Agent tool or chump --execute-gap)"
    - Existing handoff curator's CodeFixContract gains a from_dispatch_contract() conversion so the two patterns interoperate
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-dispatch-contract-render.sh: synth 3 fixtures (minimal, full-field, missing-required), assert serializer produces expected output / errors appropriately"
    - "Documented in docs/process/SUBAGENT_DISPATCH.md with example invocation: 'cat contract.json | scripts/coord/dispatch-sonnet.sh | <Agent tool>'"
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-031
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "scripts/ops/admin-merge-cycle.sh: refuse to drop required_status_checks unless --noise-class flag is passed AND failing checks match a documented noise pattern in scripts/ops/known-noise-classes.yaml"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Today (2026-05-27) I (wizard) ran ~7 admin-merge cycles for the same wedge (INFRA-2044 docs-delta-trailer test broken). Each one was justified individually, but the COUNT is concerning and one cycle was premature (#2638 had 0 failures, only pending checks; should have waited). The admin-merge-cycle.sh wrapper (INFRA-2041) shipped with no discipline gate — anyone can drop required_status_checks for any reason. Add a discipline gate: --noise-class flag mandatory + a YAML allowlist of documented noise patterns. If failing check names don't match the declared class, REFUSE the cycle. Operator can still bypass via --force-admin --reason for true emergencies, but the default path requires accountable noise classification.\n\nExample noise classes file scripts/ops/known-noise-classes.yaml:\nclasses:\n  - id: infra-2044-docs-delta\n    matches: ['test', 'fast-checks-required']\n    pattern: 'test-infra-124-docs-delta-trailer'\n    upstream_fix_gap: INFRA-2044\n    expires_after_ship: true   # auto-removed once INFRA-2044 lands\n  - id: workspace-wide-scope-drift\n    matches: ['fast-checks']\n    pattern: 'md_links_|fleet_pulse_|dispatch_'\n    upstream_fix_gap: INFRA-682
  acceptance_criteria:
    - scripts/ops/admin-merge-cycle.sh accepts --noise-class <id> flag, looks up the class in scripts/ops/known-noise-classes.yaml, fetches failing check names, refuses cycle if they don't match the class's matches+pattern
    - "--force-admin flag bypasses the class check but requires --reason and emits kind=admin_merge_forced ambient event (audit trail)"
    - "Auto-expire: when class.expires_after_ship is true AND class.upstream_fix_gap status is done, mark the class as 'expired' (refuse to use it)"
    - "Operator-facing CLI: scripts/ops/admin-merge-cycle.sh --list-classes prints active noise classes with their match patterns"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-admin-merge-cycle-noise-class.sh: 4 fixtures — class-match passes, class-mismatch refuses, force-admin overrides, expired-class refuses"
  closed_date: '2026-05-27'
