  title: "RESILIENT P0: curator-supervisor circuit breaker — cap Sonnet spawns + halt auto-remediation on flapping"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Risk 1 of 10 from operator-requested risk inventory 2026-05-30T06:00Z. curator-supervisor in Aggressive mode (operator default) can fork-bomb: detect failure → spawn Sonnet → next tick detect slightly-different fingerprint → spawn another. Flapping errors produce N distinct fingerprints over time, bypassing sentinel dedup. Also tmux respawn-loop: respawn fires → new pane has same bug → heartbeat lands by luck → declared 'respawned' → next tick detects same failure → respawn.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "Per-role hard cap: CHUMP_CURATOR_SUPERVISOR_MAX_SPAWNS_PER_HOUR (default 3). If exceeded, supervisor stops auto-remediating this role + emits ambient kind=curator_supervisor_circuit_broken + broadcasts WARN to operator"
    - "Detection cap: if same role triggers detection 3+ times in 30min (across ANY fingerprint), the FOURTH detection halts auto-remediation + broadcasts WARN with 'flapping role — operator review required'"
    - "Respawn-success criterion tightened: pane must heartbeat AND show one successful (non-error) work line within 90s, not just heartbeat"
    - "Smoke test in scripts/ci/test-curator-supervisor.sh: synth 4 consecutive failures with different fingerprints for same role; assert 4th does not spawn Sonnet AND emits circuit_broken"
    - chump preflight green
  depends_on: [INFRA-2239]
  closed_pr: 2829
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-036
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT P1: fleet-wire reaction-cooldown — per-role corr_id-react-dedupe (anti wire-storm + echo-chamber)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Risk 3 of 10. Curator A broadcasts FEEDBACK → B reads → B reacts + broadcasts → A reads → A reacts → wire-storm. Even with EFFECTIVE-028 corr_id threading there's no react-cooldown.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "ambient-context-inject --tick-preamble adds per-role react cooldown: sentinel .chump-locks/<role>-reacted/<corr_id>.sentinel; if exists AND mtime < CHUMP_REACT_COOLDOWN_M (default 30min), digest SUPPRESSES that corr_id"
    - First-react per corr_id is fine; second-react within cooldown gets suppressed silently
    - "Parent_corr_id chains: cooldown applies to root corr_id (chase parent links) so reacting to a reply to your own broadcast also dedupes"
    - "Smoke test: synth FEEDBACK with corr_id X; tick preamble for role A; assert digest contains X; second tick within 30min asserts digest does NOT contain X"
  depends_on: [EFFECTIVE-028, INFRA-2262]
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

