- id: RESILIENT-047
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: chump auto-resumes dispatch after trunk-RED recovery — verify 3 consecutive green merges + lift dispatch-halt without operator manual permission"
  status: open
  priority: P3
  effort: xs
  description: |
    Filed 2026-05-30T10:00Z. The §7 trunk-RED handler in CHUMP_PLAYBOOK.md says 'wait for 3 consecutive green main merges before re-opening dispatch firehose.' Currently this is operator-discretion (operator must notice the 3 greens + manually un-halt). Should be substrate-managed: chump detects 3 consecutive green merges post-trunk-red_recovered event → auto-lifts dispatch-halt → emits kind=dispatch_resumed. No operator hands needed.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - When kind=trunk_red_detected fires → ambient state HALTED set (file flag at .chump-locks/dispatch-halted.flag); fleet workers respect this flag (refuse to claim new gaps while halted)
    - When kind=trunk_red_recovered fires (e.g., from hotfix-merged event OR ci-health-gate cluster cleared) → enter VERIFYING state; observe next-N main merges
    - After 3 consecutive merges on main with all required gates green → clear HALTED flag, emit kind=dispatch_resumed, ambient log notes recovery duration
    - If any of the 3 verification merges fails → re-enter HALTED state, do NOT silently resume
    - "Workers reading the dispatch-halt flag: extend scripts/dispatch/worker.sh + chump-coord worker to check flag at top of claim loop; emit kind=worker_halted_skip if flag set"
    - "Smoke test: scripts/ci/test-dispatch-halt-resume.sh — fires synthetic trunk_red_detected → checks halt; fires 3 synthetic gap_shipped → checks resume; injects 1 failure → asserts re-halt"
  notes: |
    [2026-05-30T10:11:54Z] [2026-05-30T10:17Z] SUPERSEDED by INFRA-2226 'ci-runner-saturation throttle' which already covers auto-resume-when-avg-merge-gap-recovers semantics. Demoting P1→P3; operator can close or fold any unique-aspect AC into INFRA-2226. Another FAFO instance — RESILIENT-048 (auto-FAFO-check at file time) is the META fix that prevents this.
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-048
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT P0: chump gap reserve / claim auto-FAFO-check — surface prior closed gaps + merged PRs + abandoned branches matching new gap scope BEFORE filer commits to it"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Filed 2026-05-30T10:13Z after curator-opus repeatedly proposed work that was ALREADY SHIPPED — most recently claiming INFRA-2237 (rotate-sccache-r2-token script) was 'unbuilt' when PR #2793 merged it 2026-05-30T03:48Z (~6h before the trunk-RED that supposedly needed it). The substrate has no automatic check for 'have we tried this already?' at gap-file or gap-claim time. Every curator who lacks operator's memory will re-file shipped work, propose redundant ACs, and waste fleet cycles. Operator's framing: 'What are we doing to validate that we've already FAFO on stuff?' This gap codifies the answer.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "chump gap reserve --domain X --title 'T' performs an auto-FAFO check BEFORE writing the gap: (a) similarity-search closed gaps in state.db by title/AC overlap (Jaccard >=0.5); (b) git log --all --oneline -i --grep='<title-keywords>'; (c) gh pr list --state all --search '<key terms>'; (d) ambient.jsonl grep for related kinds. Surfaces top 5 matches with status (done/in-flight/abandoned) before final commit."
    - "If any closed gap matches with similarity >=0.85: BLOCK reserve unless --force-fafo-bypass with a reason, log kind=fafo_bypass_used to ambient (audit trail)"
    - "chump claim <GAP-ID>: ALSO runs FAFO check + surfaces matches before the worktree is created — even a 5-second pause to read 'this looks like INFRA-2237 which shipped 6h ago in PR #2793' would have caught today's curator-opus error"
    - "New chump verb: chump gap fafo-check <title-or-id> — standalone command for pre-file investigation. Returns JSON: { similar_closed_gaps: [], related_prs: [], git_commits: [], ambient_signals: [] }"
    - "Pre-commit hook for docs/gaps/*.yaml: any new yaml file triggers FAFO check before commit succeeds (blocks if high-similarity prior gap exists without bypass trailer)"
    - "Smoke test scripts/ci/test-fafo-check.sh: <30s, creates synthetic prior-gap fixtures, asserts new-gap-reserve with similar title surfaces them AND blocks at 0.85 threshold without --force"
    - "Cross-references: INFRA-2237 (the cycle 7 incident where this would have caught my error), CHUMP_PLAYBOOK §0.7 TRIAGE FIRST (the broader discipline this implements at gap-file layer)"
    - "This gap is META — implementing it teaches the substrate to teach itself. Per operator framing 2026-05-30T10:08Z: 'we've tried this already and it doesnt f'n work... cant you see this in the ambient stream or logs?'"
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-049
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "audit + ban Stdio::null() on git/external commands — silent failures hide test regressions"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: s
  description: |
    tokio::process::Command::....stderr(Stdio::null())....status() silently swallows command failures. This blocks the surrounding code from learning about (or asserting on) git/external-binary errors.
    
    Discovered 2026-05-30 during PR #2866 trunk-RED diagnosis: chump-integrator's test helper init_repo_with_commits() called git init then git checkout main, both with .stderr(Stdio::null()). On CI runners with init.defaultBranch=master, git init created a 'master' branch; the subsequent 'git checkout main' silently failed; branch B was then created off branch A instead of off main; the test's expected conflict didn't happen; test failed in a way that took human debugging to root-cause (4+ months later, when it finally surfaced).
    
    Anti-pattern: Stdio::null() should never be used for STDERR of error-checked commands. If we want to suppress noise, use a buffered Stdio::piped() and only print on failure.
    
    PROPOSAL:
    1. Scan crates/**/*.rs for .stderr(Stdio::null()) preceded by a Command. Audit each: is the exit code checked? Is failure-mode reachable?
    2. For each unchecked-stderr-and-status case: refactor to capture stderr to a buffer; on non-zero exit, propagate it.
    3. Add clippy lint or custom check (regex over .rs files in CI) that flags this combination.
