- id: RESILIENT-092
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT P0: Chump must MANAGE pty exhaustion — detect + mitigate before forkpty fails machine-wide (the Claude Code pty leak DoS'd the fleet + terminals 2026-06-04)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    VERIFIED 2026-06-04: a long Claude-Code /loop session leaked 505 master ptys (held by the main Claude.app pid 34081) -> kern.tty.ptmx_max=511 EXHAUSTED -> forkpty 'Device not configured' MACHINE-WIDE -> terminals unusable + Chump fleet down ~2h (tmux/workers can't allocate ptys). Upstream root: Claude Code (2.1.156) leaks ~1 pty per Bash-tool call; a tight Bash-heavy loop exhausts the limit (being reported to Anthropic separately). Chump must MANAGE this so it never causes an outage again — this is substrate health (infra-watcher's lane): (a) infra-watcher monitors allocated-ptys vs kern.tty.ptmx_max each tick and emits operator_recall/scream when usage >80% of the limit, BEFORE forkpty fails; (b) raise kern.tty.ptmx_max to >=4096 PERSISTENTLY (operator one-time: sysctl -w + persist via /etc/sysctl.conf or a boot launchd) for headroom; (c) on imminent exhaustion, scream + page the operator to restart the leaking Claude Code app (or, if a narrow sudoers entry exists, raise the ceiling dynamically). Complements RESILIENT-087 (fleet must not fatally depend on ptys). Without this, the next long session silently DoS's the whole machine again. MISSION-010 substrate-health dependency.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - infra-watcher detects pty usage approaching kern.tty.ptmx_max and emits operator_recall/scream BEFORE forkpty fails (threshold e.g. 80%)
    - kern.tty.ptmx_max is raised + persisted to >=4096 headroom (survives reboot)
    - a pty-exhaustion trend triggers mitigation (scream + operator action), never a silent machine-wide outage
    - "repro/test: simulated high pty usage fires detection before exhaustion"
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-093
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "Audit: source scrub-git-env.sh in remaining 5 test scripts that create git commits"
  status: done
  priority: P2
  effort: m
