    - scripts/ci/test-trunk-sentinel-daemon.sh has new test exercising 3-step recovery path
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-098
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: stuck-pr-filer auto-close blocked by INFRA-2423 auto-fetch gate — 23 stale zombies accumulated
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: xs
  description: |
    scripts/ops/stuck-pr-filer.sh:261 calls 'chump gap ship <ID> --closed-pr N --update-yaml' inside auto_close_resolved_filings(). But 'chump gap ship' enforces INFRA-2423 auto-fetch gate: refuses when local main is N commits behind origin AND working tree dirty. Daemon runs from main worktree where one or both are usually true. Result: filer detects every resolved zombie, attempts ship, fails with 'cannot auto-pull with uncommitted changes', logs WARN, leaves gap open. Today's evidence: /tmp/chump-stuck-pr-filer.out.log has 23 consecutive 'WARN: chump gap ship XXX failed (PR #N MERGED/CLOSED)' lines from a single cycle. Compounding: filer ALSO exits early on disk_critical (legitimate), so for ~3 days zombies accumulated unaddressed. FIX: replace 'gap ship' call with 'gap set <ID> --status closed --add-note <msg> --closed-pr N' — state.db direct mutation, no auto-fetch needed. The auto-fetch gate protects HUMAN shippers from accidentally shipping over stale base. Daemon just wants to flip status; it's not actually merging anything. Rough shape: (a) edit scripts/ops/stuck-pr-filer.sh:255-269 case branch; (b) prefer 'gap set --status closed' over 'gap ship'; (c) update note to reflect auto-close action; (d) keep ambient kind=pr_auto_closed_for_respawn semantics. Pairs with RESILIENT-097 (trunk-sentinel sibling).
  acceptance_criteria:
    - stuck-pr-filer auto-close path succeeds when local main is behind origin AND working tree has changes (no auto-fetch precondition)
    - "Test: simulate stale local main + open dirty file, call auto_close_resolved_filings() with a synthetic resolved-PR gap, assert gap moves to closed"
    - scripts/ci/test-stuck-pr-filer.sh covers the dirty-main case
  outcome_id: RESILIENT-000

- id: RESILIENT-099
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: stale-worktree-reaper reaps an ACTIVELY-LEASED 0-commits-ahead worktree (misreads 'branch merged into origin/main'); active lease must hard-block reap"
  status: done
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    2026-06-05T13:32:36Z: while editing INFRA-2744 in /tmp/chump-infra-2744 (active lease claim-infra-2744-26441-...), the stale-worktree-reaper REAPED the worktree with reason='branch merged into origin/main'. The branch chump/infra-2744-claim was NOT merged — it had 0 commits ahead because the work was still UNCOMMITTED (working-tree edits). The reaper read '0 ahead' as 'merged' and removed the worktree. It DID auto-stash first (kind=worktree_work_stashed_before_reap -> commit 5e0bb0c9c on wip/ branch; work recovered), but it should not have reaped at all: an ACTIVE LEASE was held (ambient showed it). Compare: it correctly SKIPPED a sibling worktree the same cycle with reason=git_index_fresh. So the active-lease + uncommitted-work guards were bypassed by the 'merged (0 ahead)' code path. Evidence: .chump-locks/ambient.jsonl around 2026-06-05T13:32:31-37Z (kind=commit auto-stash, worktree_work_stashed_before_reap, worktree_reaped).
  acceptance_criteria:
