    - a freshly-claimed branch with 0 commits ahead of origin/main is NOT classified as 'merged' when the worktree has uncommitted working-tree changes or an active lease
    - "regression test: worktree on a 0-ahead claim branch + active lease + dirty working tree is NOT reaped (skipped with an explicit reason)"
    - the auto-stash safety net is retained as defense-in-depth, not the primary guard
  notes: |
    Surfaced shipping INFRA-2744. The .chump-no-reap opt-out works but is manual; the active-lease guard should be automatic. Reaper: scripts/ops/stale-worktree-reaper.sh + scripts/coord/worktree-prune.sh (guards: wt_has_active_lease, .git/index freshness, unpushed commits, untracked files) — the 'branch merged' path apparently precedes/overrides these.
