- id: RESILIENT-112
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: sccache-reaper concurrency lock + live-cache prune safety"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: s
  description: |
    Two scripts/coord/sccache-reaper.sh --execute ran concurrently (NO lock guard), pruning the live sccache cache out from under in-flight builds. Result: corrupted reads ('failed to parse process output' / 'sccache: encountered fatal error'), a 2-daemon split-brain on port 4226, and EVERY fleet Rust build wedged for ~unknown duration on 2026-06-05. Triggered when disk-pressure-reaper fired sccache-reaper during the disk_critical crisis. Manual recovery: pkill -f sccache-reaper + killall -9 sccache + single restart (only one LISTEN daemon should hold 4226). Rough shape: (a) flock/lockfile guard at top of sccache-reaper.sh so a 2nd concurrent run exits 0; (b) skip cache entries with atime/mtime within CHUMP_SCCACHE_REAPER_MIN_AGE_S (default 600s) so active builds aren't raced; (c) back off if 'sccache --show-stats' shows active in-flight requests; (d) emit kind=sccache_reaper_tick on completion.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "flock/lockfile guard: only one sccache-reaper.sh runs at once — a 2nd concurrent invocation exits 0 with 'already running' (test launches two, asserts exactly one prunes)"
    - reaper skips cache files whose atime/mtime is within CHUMP_SCCACHE_REAPER_MIN_AGE_S (default 600s) so it never deletes an entry an active build is mid-read on
    - reaper backs off (exits 0, logs) when sccache --show-stats reports active in-flight compile requests rather than racing the live server
    - regression test scripts/ci/test-sccache-reaper-safety.sh asserts the lock + skip-recent behavior with a synthetic cache dir
    - on completion emit kind=sccache_reaper_tick to ambient.jsonl with files_pruned + bytes_freed

- id: RESILIENT-113
