    - "Root cause identified — one of: (a) inode reuse (mutex file deleted+recreated keeps prior fd valid for siblings), (b) /tmp -> /private/tmp symlink path confusion (INFRA-779 family), (c) sccache process inherits the flock fd across worktrees, (d) chump-commit's mutex path resolution incorrect"
    - "Fix: chump-commit's flock target uses repo-absolute git-dir path resolved via git rev-parse --git-dir without /tmp symlink interference; OR moves the mutex to a repo-rooted .chump-locks/index-mutex-<worktree>.lock"
