- id: RESILIENT-140
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: bot-merge push/PR-create stage hangs + heartbeat mislabels it as prior stage (cargo fmt)
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Diagnosed 2026-06-08 during META-287 manual ship (wedged 3x). In bot-merge.sh, AFTER rebase (31s with 1200s budget — validates RESILIENT-133: the 300s default was strangling rebase) + fmt (15s) + skip-tests/clippy (DOC_ONLY diff), the push / gh-pr-create stage HANGS >210s and NEVER creates a PR. During the hang the per-stage heartbeat still prints 'step=cargo fmt' (stale step label) — so it looks like fmt is hanging when the real stall is push/pr-create. Manual ships have no farmer-retry, so one hang = permanent wedge; the fleet survives only because the farmer re-runs the worker. Part of MISSION-044 (Cut the Friction). Two distinct bugs to fix.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. bot-merge heartbeat prints the ACTUAL current stage (push / pr-create / merge), never a stale prior label like 'cargo fmt'. 2. The push/pr-create stall is root-caused (candidate: pre-push hook, gh pr create GraphQL, force-with-lease) and either fixed or fail-fast with a clear error + tight budget — no silent 210s+ hang. 3. A clean doc-only branch ships through to PR-create + auto-merge-arm within stage budget on the first attempt."

- id: RESILIENT-141
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: bot-merge RECOVERY_MODE push blocked by its own INFRA-719 guard — fast-path doesn't signal bot-merge-initiated
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Observed 2026-06-08 shipping INFRA-2826 (audit-unjam keystone). 'CHUMP_BOT_MERGE_RECOVERY_MODE=1 bash scripts/coord/bot-merge.sh --gap INFRA-2826 --auto-merge' does fast-path push+PR+auto-merge but its push does NOT set the bot-merge-initiated signal (CHUMP_BOT_MERGE_IN_PROGRESS=1) that pre-push Guard 4 (INFRA-719) requires. The pre-push hook BLOCKED bot-merge's OWN push as a manual direct push ('BLOCKED (INFRA-719): direct push of gap branch ... to a new PR', hook aborted line 1047, exit 1). So the documented recovery path for a wedged bot-merge is itself broken — cannot ship a new gap branch without a forbidden bypass. Part of MISSION-044; reinforces RESILIENT-140.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - 1. bot-merge RECOVERY_MODE push sets the bot-merge-initiated signal so pre-push Guard 4 (INFRA-719) allows it. 2. A recovery-mode ship of a NEW gap branch reaches PR-create + auto-merge-arm with no INFRA-719 block. 3. Regression test asserts the signal is exported on the recovery push path.

- id: RESILIENT-142
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "run-fleet auth DURABLE: OAuth-first detection (operator 2026-06-08) + claude -p probe fix — end the recurring stomp"
  status: done
  priority: P0
  effort: m
  description: |
    Recurring fleet-death root cause + operator decision 2026-06-08. (A) run-fleet.sh INFRA-621 probe used the REMOVED 'claude --once' flag -> always failed (mislabeled 'auth failed') -> fleet wouldn't launch (the 13h-stall bug). The fix kept getting STOMPED because it was only ever a main-checkout edit, never committed. (B) run-fleet auth-path detection was pure precedence (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY-wins-if-set) and NEVER consulted CHUMP_AUTH_MODE, so an out-of-credit API key in .env permanently shadowed a working OAuth token. Operator decision: OAuth-FIRST, API-key SECONDARY. This gap commits the fix to origin/main so it survives checkout refresh.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - "1. run-fleet.sh probe uses 'claude -p' (no removed flags). 2. run-fleet auth detection is OAuth-first: CHUMP_AUTH_MODE=api-key forces key; else prefer OAuth (CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN env, then ~/.chump/oauth-token.json) loading the file token + unsetting ANTHROPIC_API_KEY; ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is fallback only when no OAuth exists. 3. scripts/ci/test-fleet-auth-check.sh uses 'claude -p'. 4. Regression test asserts OAuth is preferred when both a set API key and an oauth-token.json exist with CHUMP_AUTH_MODE!=api-key. 5. Lands on origin/main (no stomp)."
  notes: |
    Superseded by RESILIENT-143 (#3119, cc319b85b — durable re-file of force-recover-lost RESILIENT-142), merged to main. Stale-open P0 de-inflation.
  closed_pr: 3119
  outcome_id: MISSION-010

- id: RESILIENT-143
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "run-fleet auth durable v2: OAuth-first detection + claude -p probe (re-file of force-recover-lost RESILIENT-142)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  description: |
    Durable run-fleet OAuth-first auth fix — re-file of RESILIENT-142 (lost to --force-recover before landing). Recurring fleet-death root cause: (A) run-fleet.sh INFRA-621 probe used removed 'claude --once' flag → always failed; (B) auth detection was api-key-first (never consulted CHUMP_AUTH_MODE), so an out-of-credit ANTHROPIC_API_KEY shadowed a working OAuth token. Operator decision 2026-06-08: OAuth-first, API-key secondary.
  acceptance_criteria:
