- id: RESILIENT-144
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: pr-rescue-false-close reopens intentional PR closes (no intentional-close signal) — daemon close/reopen oscillation; only branch-deletion is terminal"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    scripts/coord/pr-rescue-false-close.sh (INFRA-1406) reopens ANY closed PR whose head branch still exists on remote (it only skips on state=MERGED or branch-deleted). So an intentional close (redundant/superseded/broken PR) is silently reverted within ~60s — the curator's terminal action becomes a no-op. Worse: observed close/reopen OSCILLATION on PR #3117 at 2026-06-09T01:29:32Z closed then 01:30:07Z reopened, 35s apart, NO human involved — an auto-closer and pr-rescue-false-close.sh fighting over the same PR, burning gh API. The only terminal close today is to delete the remote branch first (then the rescue refuses). Evidence: #3108 + #3117 had to be branch-deleted via 'gh api -X DELETE git/refs/heads/<b>' to make the close stick this cycle.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - pr-rescue-false-close.sh honors an intentional-close signal (do-not-reopen/wontfix/superseded label, close-comment marker, or gap status closed/superseded) and does NOT reopen such PRs.
    - "Oscillation guard: if a PR flapped closed<->open >=2x in <10m, stop and emit kind=pr_close_reopen_oscillation instead of reopening."
    - Document terminal-close procedure (close + delete branch, or the do-not-reopen signal) in the shepherd playbook.
    - "Smoke test: a closed PR carrying the do-not-reopen signal is NOT reopened by the rescue."

- id: RESILIENT-145
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: pre-push bypass-trailer validator (INFRA-2407) over-scans already-merged main commits on force-push of a rebuilt branch"
  status: open
  priority: P2
  effort: m
  description: |
    The pre-push bypass-trailer validator (INFRA-2407) scans the git-standard range remote_sha..local_sha. When you rebuild a PR branch cleanly on CURRENT origin/main and force-push over a remote tip based on OLDER main, that range includes the main commits that merged in between — and re-flags ANY of them whose body has a bypass token but lacks the 4 trailers. Live: rescuing #3124 (rebuilt on origin/main) was blocked on merged commit 20d890500 ('close INFRA-777'), which is already on main and unfixable. The validator penalizes correct hygiene (rebuild-from-current-main) and false-positives on merged commits. Fix: exclude commits that are ancestors of origin/main from the bypass-trailer scan (git rev-list local_sha --not origin/main), so only NOT-yet-merged commits are validated.
  acceptance_criteria:
    - bypass-trailer validator scans only commits NOT reachable from origin/main (e.g. 'git rev-list <local> --not origin/main'), so already-merged commits are never re-flagged on a force-push.
    - Rebuilding a PR branch on current origin/main and force-pushing does NOT trip INFRA-2407 on merged commits.
    - A genuinely-new commit carrying a bypass token WITHOUT the 4 trailers is still blocked.
    - "Smoke test covers: rebuilt-branch force-push (pass) + new-commit-with-bare-bypass-token (block)."

- id: RESILIENT-146
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: fleet-paused auto-resume keys off 7d-cumulative waste % so a recovered/idle fleet never un-pauses (3-min blip -> multi-day outage)"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - The mechanism that clears .chump/fleet-paused computes recovery on a CURRENT-WINDOW waste rate (e.g. last 30-60min), not a 7d cumulative, so an idle/recovered fleet un-pauses within 2 checks.
    - "A pause written by an SLO breach (reason:slo_breach) is cleared when that SLO recovers, not only via the waste-rate path."
    - "Failsafe: a fleet-paused sentinel older than CHUMP_MAX_PAUSE_AGE_S (default e.g. 2h) with trunk green is auto-cleared + emits fleet_resumed, so a stale pause cannot cause a multi-day outage."
    - "Regression test: write sentinel + idle waste -> detector removes it within N checks."

- id: RESILIENT-147
  domain: RESILIENT
  title: "RESILIENT: farmer check_auth pages AUTH_DEAD on oauth token-FILE-AGE not validity — false-positive on long-lived (1yr setup-token) tokens; wire to auth-status.sh validity probe"
  status: open
  priority: P1
  effort: m
  acceptance_criteria:
    - farmer.sh check_auth OAuth path decides AUTH_DEAD via scripts/coord/auth-status.sh (validity probe) — pages only when the probe reports the fleet cannot transact, NOT on token-file age.
    - A valid long-lived token (1yr setup-token) whose file is >1h old does NOT emit farmer_auth_dead / page AUTH_DEAD.
    - If auth-status.sh is absent, fall back to the existing age check (backward compatible).
    - Test covers valid-but-stale-file token -> no page, and genuinely-invalid token -> page.

